<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Markets West - stockTALK - Oct 24, 1995</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR=#C0C0C0><CENTER><IMG SRC="../mw.gif"></CENTER><HR>
<FONT SIZE=+2><B>stockTALK Special Report</B></FONT><BR>
 March 25, 1996
<P>
<H2>Loumic Resources (VSE:LOO) - 500% Gain Possible </H2>
<P>
Could Loumic Resources appreciate in value like Mountain Province did... ?
<P>
With a 300% increase in price since the end of January 1996,  Loumic Resources looks posed to advance again.  Hitting a high of $.60 cdn and falling back to $ .50 cdn per share during the week March 18th to 21st , investors saw the stock gain $ .05 per share to close at $ .55 cdn per share on 168,000 shares of volume on Friday March 22, 1996.  Trading was strong on Monday morning with Loumic moving up to $ .60 cdn per share again  in the first several hours of market trading to end the day at $ .59 up $ .04 cdn per share on a volume 220,000 shares.  
<P>
Upon the closing of the markets Friday the company announced, that the it has entered into an
agreement with a  Coquitlam, B.C., based company to acquire an undivided 70% interest in additional offshore mineral  concessions  comprising  approximately  300  square kilometres in Sierra Leone. These concessions are beside the mineral concessions in which the company is reacquiring an interest from Orion  Resources as reported in company news releases of February 16 and 21 1996.   
<P>
What makes this small resource company on the Vancouver Stock Exchange so exciting to watch is that the mineral concessions that it has obtained in Sierra Leone are the only offshore properties available in the region and that the concessions are located beside concessions held by De Beers, the worlds largest diamond producing and marketing conglomerate.
<P>
In approximately (3) to (4) weeks Loumic Resources will release results from current dredge sampling  operations on its recent acquired offshore concessions.  The sampling operations are being undertaken by the Malaysia Mining Corporation.  Note extensive sampling of these concessions reveal a large diamond count  positive enough that the Malaysia Mining Corporation to continue exploration. 
<P>
Previous bulk samplings have shown the distribution of small and larger stones  indicates good  potential  to  locate  significant diamond reserves on the offshore leases.  Exploration and bulk sampling on  adjacent  offshore  leases  to  the northwest being  tested  by  a  subsidiary  of  DeBeers,  is reportedly spending 
$13 million on a bulk sampling program, a clear indication that they might have found something of value.
<P>
Early indications of the current bulk sampling program are that the results will be excellent   However the results could be released in a conservative form to prevent small locally owned prospecting ships in the area from dredging illegally on the concessions.  
<P>
Continue to watch for news releases on this stock.  Volumes and trading activities of the past several days indicate that this junior could be a clear winner.  If it performs as other such diamond plays on the Vancouver and Alberta stock exchanges have, (ie: Mountain Province Mining ) then the possible appreciation if further
diamond counts are good is tremendous. Investors can call the company investor relations at (604) 688-2012 
for complete details.
<P>
<P>
