<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Markets West - stockTALK - Oct 24, 1995</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR=#C0C0C0><CENTER><IMG SRC="../mw.gif"></CENTER><HR>
<FONT SIZE=+2><B>stockTALK Special Report</B></FONT><BR>
March 10, 1996
<P>
<H2>International Panorama Resources Corp.</H2>
<P>
<B>Leading the development of  "The Golden Land"</B>
<P>
<P>
International Panorama Resources Corp. (VSE:ILP), is one of the few mining companies selected by the 
government of Myanmar (formerly Burma) to develop the country's rich mineral resources.  Following in the
footsteps of renowned mining entrepreneur, Robert Friedland, International Panorama successfully launched
operations in Myanmar after the introduction of political and economic reforms.
<P>
International Panorama is developing a gold deposit with the potential for an open-pit, bulk mining 
operation at Thayetkone, in Central Myanmar .  Identified by the company as being at least 1.5 km by 1.5 km, the deposit is located adjacent to the 50 tons/day pilot gold recovery plant at Thayetkone.  Veins up to 1 km
long and 1.5 km wide, carry gold grades to 1 ounce/ton.  The deposit has ready access to water, hydropower
and rail transportation.  The 1,400 sq km property is situated on the Shan Fault, a major 2000 km long fault
zone which is closely associated with gold mineralization over a 1,200 km strike length in Myanmar.
<P>
Significant changes have taken place in the global mining scene over the past few years.  Currently at the forefront of change is Myanmar.  The government's stated economic objectives include the establishment of a
sound market-oriented economic system, with reduced state involvement and increased foreign investment.
<P>
It is likely that Myanmar will be admitted as a full member of ASEAN over the next few years.  Foreign investment in Myanmar is accelerating, with over US $3 billion in investment projects approved to October 31.  
Thailand, Singapore and the United Kingdom are the leading contributors.  Japan may resume official lending
to Myanmar soon, while very substantial Japanese private-sector investment is already in the pipeline.
<P>
With approximately 4.5 million shares issued and a strong management group in place, International
Panorama Resources vast land position in Myanmar has positioned the company as a major participant in the
development of Myanmar's mineral wealth.  Continuing success in Myanmar will have a significant impact on the price of International Panorama's share price.
<P>
For a complete information package on International Panorama Resources Corp., please Email the company at
<A HREF="mailto:panorama@mindlink.bc.ca">Investor Relations</A> or phone Mr. Gary Freeman at (604) 687-7294 or 1-800-931-1818.
<P><HR><P>
