<center><font size=6><b>EMERGING GROWTH
STOCKS</b></font><br>
<font size=3><i>Covering the V.S.E., Junior Gold Stocks, and
Special Situations - Volume IV, No. 4</i></font></center>
<hr>
<center><h3>MARKET COMMENTARY<br>
-VSE Index Recovering From Voisey Bay Sell-Off, Separation Jitters 
-</h3></center>

While the major markets continue setting all time record highs, 
the V.S.E. composite index is only now just beginning to recover from a 
decline that started in August, when several high profile newsletter 
writers were urging investors to take profits in the higher
priced Voisey Bay area play stocks.  Selling resumed during the 
referendum on separation in Quebec in late October.  And now we are 
seeing a third wave of selling, the traditional year-end tax-loss 
selling season, combined with a general lull in exploration and 
promotional activity by V.S.E. listed companies.<p>

We haven't made a single buy recommendation since the beginning of 
this decline, because I could see it would last.  However, this 
series of corrections has taken a great deal of price speculation out 
of the market.  For example, <b>Prime Equities (PQE.V)</b>, a large 
claimholder in Voisey Bay which ran up to $6.00 shortly after we 
mentioned it at $2.36 in July is now back down to $1.30 or so.  
Another Murray Pezim company, <b>Goldnev Res. (GNZ.V)</b> has fallen to a 
multi-year low of $0.38 from a high of $2.94 in June!  We have no 
idea exactly when, but you can bet these two will be trading at much 
higher prices, sometime in 1996 (whenever Pezim decides it's time to 
run them again).<p>

Now, we feel the index has thoroughly corrected from the sharp rise we 
saw in the first half of 1995, and has formed a solid base from which it 
will rally from, very likely early in the new year. <b>Accordingly, we are 
enclosing our top three buy recommendations for year end bargain hunters 
on page 2.</b> Read why our favourite nickel-copper prospect is a property 
which is actually a few hundred kms outside Voisey Bay.  Also learn why 
<b>Montello Res. (MEO.C)</b> tripled to $0.65 after we mentioned it at 
$0.22 in 
our July sneak preview section, and why we expect to see a similar move 
like this in the very near future.<p>

<table width=100%>
<tr><td nowrap colspan=3><b>INTERNATIONAL BUTEC - IB.V</b></td>
