<td>

IB's main asset is a hot nickel-copper property located in the Ungava 
region of Quebec, approximately half way between Voisey Bay and the 
Falconbridge Raglan Deposit.  Base metal values exceeding 20% have shown 
up in trenching, and the property is being drilled right now.  I 
understand that at least one extremely influential newsletter writer has 
recently taken a very substantial position in the company, and that a 
Swiss group will be doing the same in the new year.  Do they know 
something we don't - could this be the next big discovery after Voisey 
Bay?  Be careful buying this one as it had already started to move, 
however I do see IB trading well above $1.00 sometime early in the new 
year.  You can contact the company at 681-4421 in Vancouver, or 
1-800-889-2280 for further information.</td>

<tr><td nowrap colspan=3><b>MONTELLO RESOURCES - MEO.C</b></td>
