$0.30 or less</td>
<td>

Montello is a great stock to trade.  It's main asset is a lamphorite 
diamond pipe prospect near Hinton, Alberta.  In October, the stock ran up 
to $0.65 on the news of a $4 million joint venture deal with Kennecott. 
The price fell off immediately afterwards, in part due to market 
conditions, but also due to a decision by the company to delay a drilling 
program until February (the market was expecting drilling immediately). 
Chuck Fipke, the founder of DIAMET, who made the first diamond discovery 
in Canada is convinced the property contains a lamphorite pipe (this 
would be the first of it's kind in Canada).  This is a "no-brainer" trade 
- buy right now in the $0.25 range, sell half on the drilling hype in 
February, and hold the rest in case drilling is successful - you could 
see a move to $1.50 - $2.00 if that occurs.  Contact the company at 
1-604-689-7199 for further information.</td>

<tr><td nowrap colspan=3><b>PACIFIC RIM MINING - PFG.V</b></td>
