<td>
One tactic I have been using successfully is to try and time my purchases 
just prior to a substantial financing by the company.  This is a prime 
candidate.  PFG has what are believed to be two "company making" gold 
prospects in Argentina.  The company wasted an entire year (1994) waiting 
for an Arabian group to finance them.  That fell through, however this 
year Barrick Resources has signed a potential $14 million letter of 
intent with them, and is deciding whether or not to proceed.  The company 
is also discussing financing at this time with various brokerage houses.  
This time lag however has done damage to shareholder confidence, causing 
the stock to fall to a 52 week low.  With financing possibly just around 
the corner, this could be an excellent time to pick-up a few shares.  You 
can reach the company at 1-604-689-1976 for more information.</td>
</table>

<h3>IPC - INT. PROFIT CONCEPTS</h3>

For those of you who are interested in commodities and global 
investments, I encourage you to check out this company.  It's operated by 
Mr. Ron Weibe, a seasoned options trader who has high level contacts 
throughout the globe, and the backing of R.K. Financial, a venture 
capital firm.  Right now, Ron is offering a guaranteed 18% on the 
smallest of investments, and is currently investigating opportunities 
arising from the Japanese banking crisis.  To learn more about these and 
other opportunities, contact Ron at 1-800-294-6850 Ext. D119, to receive 
an information package and subscribe to his newsletter.


<h3>INTERNET STOCKS</h3>

As you are probably well aware by now, Internet stocks are all the rage 
and are likely to stay that way for some time.  I figured something was 
up when my good friend, Robert Spiers (author of Small-Cap Stock Analyst) 
was calling me from the other side of the country to get me to look at 
some new NASDAQ IPO that was about to come out called Netscape.  Of 
course, now we need to be careful considering the astronomical P.E. 
ratios these stocks are commanding.  Still though, internet has enormous 
future growth potential and EGS is going to start researching the ones 
that are not already trading over $100.00!  One is I.D. Internet Direct 
(IDX.V), $2.25 previously Arling Resources (name changed December 6).  
Another is a new listing in Calgary, Cybersurf Corp.  (CY.C), $0.80.  It 
traded as high as $1.40 when it opened on December 8, but has fallen back 
below $1.00 since then.  More on this play to come in future issues of 
EGS.<p>

