<H2><CENTER>BEST BET SCORECARD..... </CENTER></H2>
<BR>
Best Bets for the 4th Quarter were announced on October 18th. Initially,
SEVEN (7) &quot;Best Bet&quot; companies were selected. A new one was added
on November 11th. One was removed on November 17th. Another was removed
this week. There is important commentary following this scorecard.<BR>
<P>
<PRE>COMPANY			TICKER / EXCH.		OCT 18		NOV 22 		% CHG.

Primo Resources*  	PRI / Vancouver		0.61		0.87		+ 44%

Fairmile Gold		FLA / Alberta		3.10		2.22		- 28%

Strathmore Resources	SMR / Vancouver		0.83		1.85		+ 96%

Sino-Forest		TRE.A / Toronto		1.51		1.35		-  11%

Asquith			ASQH / Toronto OTC	2.40		2.80		+ 02%

Enterprise Development	ED / Alberta		0.50		0.80		+ 60%

Anvil Resources**		ANV / Alberta		0.60		0.82		+ 36%

Canada Payphone   	CPY / Vancouver		2.80		2.20		- 21%
    (Added on November 11th at C$2.80/share)	

Leigh Resources (VSE:LRC) is hereby included in the Best Bets 
scorecard, effective November 23rd, at future percentage changes 
will be calculated at the November 22nd closing price of 
C$2.35/share.
	</PRE>
<P>
<H2><CENTER>COMMENTARY.....</CENTER></H2>
<BR>
*Primo (VSE:PRI) replaced Vior Explorations on November 17th. For a BREAK-EVEN
on this replacement on the Scorecard, PRI must gain another C$0.22/share
between now and December 31st, to offset VIO's loss. Initially featured
as a Wild Card at C$0.61/share, PRI was upgraded to a Best Bet on November
18th.<BR>
<BR>
** Anvil (Alberta:ANV) replaced an OTC BB stock (non-reporting issuer),
of which I am discontinuing all Internet coverage, until the company becomes
a &quot;reporting issuer.&quot; For a proportionate BREAK-EVEN on this replacement
on the Scorecard, ANV must gain an additional C$0.23/share. If one carefully
analyzes ANV's stockchart, it should become abundantly clear that, historically,
ANV leaps above C$1/share during their drilling programs.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<H2><CENTER>DEVELOPMENTS.....</CENTER></H2>
<BR>
<BR>
Asquith Resources should be starting to drill in the very near future. Anvil
Resources has already started drilling their BC copper property. FLA announced
their drilling program should start soon -- this may be a minor drill program,
with a bigger one to follow after the New Year. Primo's joint venture partner,
Golden Peaks, should soon announce a drill program -- more trenching assays
are expected. Enterprise Development may soon start drilling one of their
Tunisian oil concessions. Canada Payphones may have significant news for
us in mid-December.<BR>
<BR>
One should keep their eyes open on the other Wild Card Stocks I selected.
Companies such as Leigh Resource (VSE:LRC) and Miranda (VSE:MAD) may soon
be &quot;stocks to watch.&quot;<BR>
<P>
<H2><CENTER>--OLDIES, BUT GOODIES......</CENTER></H2>
<BR>
I was pleased that several previously featured companies in Hot Stocks Review
continued advancing in share price this past week and set record highs.
Shareholders should pat themselves on the back for the superb gains they
have realized in these stocks.<BR>
<BR>
Vantage Enterprises (VSE:VEC), initially featured at C$2.50/share this past
summer, closed at a record high of C$7.40/share -- up 196%. Dil Gujral has
repeated his CLP success with VEC as he personally guaranteed me he would.
Mr. Gujral has always kept his word to me. I consider him to be miles above
most of the Howe Street players. (See Hot Stocks FLASH, September 12th 1996
or find the story on your Bloomberg terminal, published 16 September 1996).<BR>
<BR>
Morgain Minerals (VSE:MGM), which I brought to your attention nearly a year
ago at C$1.05/share, closed at a record high of C$2.65/share -- up 152%.
Last winter, an editor at The Venture Capital Update promised me that MGM
might repeat MPV's success. <BR>
<BR>
National Healthcare Manufacturing (VSE:NHM), which was initially featured
this past Spring at C$2.80/share, closed at a record high of C$6.75/share
-- up 141%. I met with Mac Shahsavar, NHM's CEO, several times. He repeatedly
insisted that NHM was not another &quot;VSE deal&quot; and that it was a
&quot;real deal.&quot; He was right and NHM currently trades on NASDAQ,
as well as the VSE. (See Hot Stocks FLASH, April 10 1996 or find the story
on your Bloomberg terminal, published 16 April 1996.)<BR>
<P> 
