    <TITLE>HOT STOCKS FLASH</TITLE>
</HEAD>
George Chelekis' HOT STOCKS REVIEW -- Copyright 1996
<P>
<I>George Chelekis'</I>
<P>
<H1><CENTER>HOT STOCKS FLASH</CENTER></H1>
<P><CENTER><I><STRONG>October 22, 1996</STRONG></I><BR>
<BR>
ADVERTISING SALES/CIRCULATION: (813) 254-5599<BR>
FAX: (813) 254-4142 * RECORDED HOTLINE:813-251-0030<BR>
<P>
</CENTER>
<P>
<H2><CENTER>ENTERPRISE DEVELOPMENT....</CENTER></H2>
<BR>
I began telling you about Enterprise Development (Alberta:ED) over the
past year. I recently placed ED on my Top Ten &quot;Best Bets&quot; List
(Number #7). It has recently come to my attention that a very bullish analyst
report may soon be released, citing the engineer's report on the recently
acquired Tunisian oil properties. One source tells me that those oil properties
may add C$2/share to ED's share price. On Monday, ED was the second most
actively traded stock on the Alberta stock exchange, closing at C$0.60/share
(bid: 60/ask:62), with 467,222 shares trading hands. Contact Garry Kilbourn
at 403-237-6950 for additional information.<BR>
<P>
<P>
<H2><CENTER>INTERVIEW WITH <BR>
PRIOR RESOURCES' GEOLOGIST....</CENTER>
</H2>
<BR>
I spoke by telephone with Ron Tammekand, geologist for Prior Resources
(Alberta:PQL). The first words out of his mouth were, &quot;We got some
good results.&quot; Followed by, &quot;Better structure near the surface&quot;
and &quot;Have to do infill drilling.&quot;<BR>
<BR>
Keep in mind that Tammekand was handed the task of drilling 18 itsy-bitsy
teeny shallow holes into fairly mysterious Mexican terrain about the size
of 20 football fields......yet he did come up with a five foot section in
Hole #7, which turned up better than 1/2 ounce of gold/ton and 1 ounce of
silver/ton. The rest was ahhh, a start, if one looks at these things with
any ray of hope. Yes, the Internet rumors on Silicon Investor are true,
but this time, the shoe is on the other foot, it is PQL that does NOT want
to talk to the majors right now.......... (that would just delay any imminent
infill drilling!)<BR>
<BR>
What Tammekand now needs to do is convince his bosses that they should
raise another few bucks to put some more money into the ground; C$500,000
is the figure he tossed out. PQL has around C$300,000 in the till (as I
have been led to believe), so they may soon commit to 10,000 feet of Reverse
Circulation (R/C) drilling. In other words, Tammekand would like to poke
about 100 holes in this property so he can properly size it up. He even
wants to re-drill all of the previously drilled holes with R/C drilling....
more trenching, more mapping, etc. He stressed to me, &quot;It's not a sure
thing, there is still a lot of risk to it.&quot; Interesting.....most PQL-watchers
would tend to believe that PQL was more of a &quot;sure risk&quot; than
a &quot;sure thing.&quot; Yet now, PQL's geologist is, in his own way, more
optimistic than before.<BR>
<BR>
Which, I guess, is why is he designing a drilling program to &quot;prove
up&quot; roughly 200,000 ounces of gold (his words, not mine). PQL still
has another 8 holes to release, yet now even Tammekand is talking about
infill drilling.... sooner rather than later. I now understand why Dalton
DuPasquier got excited a few weeks ago and publicly started discussing an
infill drilling program. Perhaps, I was right, in some earlier remarks,
that perhaps this time PQL may come up with the goods. Stranger things have
happened.<BR>
Suggestion: Badger their IR people at 800-972-6564 and find out when infill
drilling is to start....<BR>
<P>
<P><I>COPYRIGHT &copy; 1996 by George Chelekis. ALL RIGHTS RESERVED. The
