<H2>London Taylor Group</H2>
<H4>U.S. Financial Market Access Program</H4>
<P>
<P>
<A NAME="Ab"><H3>About the London Taylor Group and LTG's monthly Client Companies Update.</H3>
<P>
The London Taylor Group offers a variety of services to publicly traded companies, primarily in the natural resource sector.  These services include investment banking, assistance with legal and regulatory compliance, corporate development and broker/shareholder communications
<P>
The London Taylor Group is extremely selective about its clients.  Before being accepted as a client, each company must meet strict criteria to insure that they have skilled management; a clear and viable business plan; substantial assets; and; a share price the LTG believes is significantly undervalued.
<P>
Each month London Taylor issues its LTG Client Companies Update to the community of financial professionals, including investment bankers, institutional analysts and brokers, retail brokers, financial planners and selected members of the financial press.  Additionally, LTG makes its Update available to a limited number of shareholders in client companies who have indicated an interest in keeping closely in touch with their investment.
<P>
Financial professional carefully follow developments announced each month in the LTG Client Companies Update, in order to keep current with high quality LTG clients, and to prompt investment action.  For those who wish to receive fast breaking news on LTG client companies as it becomes available, a complimentary fax service is also available.  To take advantage, simply call in your fax number to the London Taylor Group at 
1 (800) 485 - 0108 Or, you may fax us at (619) 350-0650.
<P>
<b>NEW! London Taylor Group Announces Website</b>
<P>
The London Taylor Group is pleased to announce the introduction of a new website which you can access at the Internet address : http://www.londontaylor.com. Once there, you'll find the monthly client company update, as well as a link to the APL Quote Server which allows you to access quotes on both U.S. and Canadian exchanges. If you're on the Internet, pay us a visit!
<P>
<HR>
<P>
<H3>October, 1996</H3>
<P>
<P><CENTER>
<H3>A Publication of the London Taylor Group</H3>
<P>
<H2>The London Taylor Group Client Company Update Service.</H2>
<H4>Time-dated information for financial professionals and shareholders</H4></CENTER>
<P>
<P>
<P>
<HR>
<P>
<H2>A Word About Guyana Gold Corp.</H2>
<P>
<I>
In a recent development, Guyana Gold (TSE Symbol: GUY) has concluded negotiations whereby the Zimbabwean government will assume its interest in the Sabi Gold Mine for $11,000,000, the proceeds of which the company is reinvesting in three highly prospective concessions in Brazil. GUY now trades at C$0.75 per share and, following the settlement, has C$0.45 per share in cash and significant blue sky potential from its new Brazilian properties.
<P>
It is our belief that, due to the caliber of Guyanas management and the quality of their Brazilian concessions, the Company has a very promising future.  However, the contract between London Taylor and Guyana Gold matures on October 3, 1996 and during Guyana&s restructuting period the affiliation between our two companies will be interrupted. Even so, this is a company that we will continue to watch closely, albeit on an informal basis and not in the pages of the LTG Client Company Update. For investors also interested in staying in touch with Guyana, contact the company direct at 1-604-687-3992. </I>
<P>
<P>
<HR>
<P>
<A NAME="Ad"><H2>Adrian Resources</H2>
Nasdaq Symbol:  ADLRF      TSE & VSE Symbol:  ADL<BR>
 $ US $3.20,  CDN $ 4.30<BR>
<P>
Adrian Resources owns a 52% interest in one of the worlds largest undeveloped copper and gold deposits: The Petaquilla Mineral District in Panama. The total geologic resource stands at 3.74 billion tons containing 31.8 billion pounds of copper, 9.8 million ounces of gold, and 962 million pounds of molybdenum. A scoping study conducted by Flour Daniel Wright has estimated the present value of the concession to be 
US$955 million at US$1.00lb copper.
<P>
<I>The company recently announced its commencement of a Normal Course Issuer Bid through the facilities of the Toronto Stock Exchange. Adrian will purchase up to 500,000 shares of its stock which is approximately 1.64% of its outstanding share float.  This buy back is in addition to the 1,160,200 shares of ADLRF that the company bought in 1995.  The decision to buy back shares was prompted by managements belief that the current market price is well below fair value.</I>
<P>
<HR>
<P>
<A NAME="Bo"><H2>Boron Chemicals International</H2>
Vancouver, Symbol: BHI<BR>
C$ 2.70<BR>
<P>
Boron is scheduled to become a leading supplier of industrial minerals when it takes its Aguas Blancas concession in Northern Chile into production in 1998. This concession contains the worlds largest proven deposits of high grade iodine, and large quantities of sodium sulfate and sodium nitrate, the later being used in the manufacturing of upscale potassium fertilizers. Revenues in its first year of operation are estimated to be US$51 million. LatInvest Securities Limited, a specialist investment bank, is serving as financial advisors with the goal of raising US$60 million to construct Borons iodine, sodium sulfate, and potassium nitrate processing plant on Borons Aguas Blancas property.
<P>
<I>The company has received a commitment from ABN Amro Bank N.V. to underwrite a US$46 million debt financing for Borons development of the Aguas Blancas project.  ABN Amro, a major international bank based in Amsterdam, has a strong presence in Chile and is one of the leading providers of mining project finance in the world.  This package, which provides US$37 in debt financing with working capital of US$4 million and a cost overrun provision of US$5 million, is expected to be completed by the end of 1996.  Borons management is now focusing on the construction details for its industrial chemical plant and the establishment of a market for its products.</I>
<P>
<HR>
<P>
<A NAME="Ch"><H2>Chase Resources / Delta Gold Mining Corp</H2>
Chase: Toronto, Symbol: CQS, Delta: Vancouver, Symbol; DTG.<BR>
Chase (CGS): C $ 2.80,   Delta (DTG): C $ 1.45 
<P>
<P>
Over the past five years, Chase Resources and its affiliated exploration company, Delta Gold Mining Corp., have engaged in an intensive exploration and land acquisition program in the Philippines, Chile and, most recently, Indonesia. This has paid off with the acquisition of a number of highly prospective properties, including the Cikondang Gold Mine in Indonesia and the Taysan deposit in the Philippines. Taysan alone is estimated to contain an estimated resource of 2.5 million ounces of gold and 3.6 billion pounds of copper. Mining giant BHP is a major shareholder in Chase/Delta and is involved in the joint development of the Taysan deposit. For more information, call Chases Audio Text Number, 1-800-836-4012
<P>
<I>Chase has recently commenced its drill program at the El Paso prospect within the Batangas F.T.A.A. in the Philippines.  This drill program will test the Abasan Ridge area, where previous trench samples indicated values of 28 meters with grades of 0.92% copper and 0.26% gold.  Also in the Philippines, Delta Gold has acquired 100% interest in the Trinidad Project.Deltas ongoing exploration of this project has uncovered indicators of three new gold zones.  The previous owners of the Trinidad identified  a reserve of 109,000 tonnes containing a grade of 16 grams per tonne.  The amalgamation of Chase and Delta has been delayed because the exchange ratio of Delta shares for the new Chase shares must still be determined.  The formal establishment of this exchange ratio is imminent.</I>
<P>
<HR>
<P>
<A NAME="Go"><H2>Goldbelt Resources</H2>
Vancouver, Symbol: GDB<BR>
C $ 1.27<BR>
<P>
<P>
Since 1992, Goldbelt Resources has, through a series of strategic partnerships, built a substantial presence in the mineral rich former Soviet Republic of Kazakstan. With four primary concessions in the companys coffers, and the financing of production facilities at their Leninogorsk gold project well advanced, investors can look for Goldbelt to transition from an exploration company into a producer within the next 18 months. For more information, call Goldbelts Audio Text Service, 1-800-836-4013.
<P>
<I>Goldbelts geologists, accompanied by senior Kazak geologists, have completed field checking 50% of the 314 known prospects and mines located on Goldbelts two exclusive exploration licenses in north central Kazakstan.  Thus far, eight areas have been identified to have the geologic potential for large tonnage gold deposits (greater than 50 million tonnes).  Ground and airborne electromagnetic surveys are in progress to look for additional deposits.  The engineering pre-feasibility study phase has begun at the Abyz Deposit.  This study should be completed by the end of October 1996.</I>
<P>
<HR>
<P>
<A NAME="In"><H2>International Panorama Resources</H2>
OTC.BB, Symbol: IPNRF; Vancouver, Symbol: ILP<BR>
C $ 2.95<BR>
<P>
<P>
International Panorama is a Canadian exploration firm with a global portfolio of gold, nickel, copper and cobalt properties.  The Company is focusing on its recently acquired US$6 billion copper/cobalt tailings project in Zaire.  The agreement has been ratified by the Zaire government
<P>
<I>The company has retained the firm of Dump and Dune Drillers of South Africa to begin a 300 hole drill program on the Zaire copper/cobalt properties.  This drill program is expected to be completed by the end of October 1996 and is in the first phase in support of theCompanys feasibility study.  Agreements with world renowned engineering firms are being finalized to complete a bankable feasibility study by March 1997.  This document will define the scope of the project, confirm reserves and metals grades, establish plant design and determine capital operating costs.  Concurrent with the drilling program metallurgical tests are conducted on the tailings samples to find the most efficient recovery techniques for the potential 255 million pounds of cobalt and 1.3 billion pounds of copper, currently valued at over US$6 billion.  International Panorama owns a 51% interest in this project joint venture with Zaires state-owned mining enterprise Gecamines.</I>
<P>
<HR>
<P>
<A NAME="Si"><H2>Silver Standard Resources.</H2>
(Nasdaq, Symbol: SSRIF, Vancouver, Symbol: SSO)<BR>
US $5.30  C $ 7.40<BR>
<P>
<P>
Silver Standard is a silver exploration with a corporate mandate to secure a portfolio of properties containing a minimum total defined in-ground resource of 250,000,000 ounces of silver by 1997, and to become a significant silver producer within four years. Silver Standard, which has multi-million ounce concessions in Bolivia, Mexico and the Russian Far East is a top recommendation of a number of leading analysts, including Doug Casey, Jim Blanchard, Adrian Day and Rick Rule
<P>
<I>Satisfactory progress has been reported by Silver Standard on its due diligence work and feasibility study at the Lunnoe property in the Russian Far East.  This property contains nine known mineralized zones on which proven,  probable and possible  resource  of 120 million ounces of silver and 500,000 ounces of gold have been outlined thus far.
<P>
Underground cross-cut sampling across the Number 9 zone, which contains much of this resource, has confirmed grades ranging from 8.69 ounces of silver per ton over 101.4 feet to 13.28 ounces of silver per ton over 119.8 feet, plus significant gold values. An additional $4 million of working capital has been added to Silver Standards treasury from the recent exercise of warrants by Teck Corporation.   The company has also added a fourth project to its operations in Mexico with the recent option agreement to explore the 84 hectare La Morelense concession in the state of Veracruz.  In Bolivia, Silver Standard is about to commence a 5,000 meter diamond drill program at El Asiento. Other potential acquisitions are being reviewed.</I>
<P>
<HR>
<P>
<A NAME="Yu"><H2>Yuma Gold Corp.</H2>
Vancouver, Symbol: YUM<BR>
C $ 2.75<BR>
<P>
<P>
Yuma is an exceptionally well managed company pursuing a three-tiered strategy for copper production from its Chilean Sierra Gorda Project.  The first stage, now completed, involved the acquisition of the Dona Ada copper processing facility.  The second phase will involve the construction of copper sulphate facilities at Sierra Miranda, Tuina and Dona Ada.  The final phase will consist of the construction of a Solvent Extraction - Electrowinning (SX-EW) plant at Sierra Miranda for the annual production of 40,000 metric tonnes 
(88 million pounds) of copper cathodes.  During construction, production will continue at Dona Ada and will be increased as the additional copper sulphate facilities are introduced >
<P>
<I>Yuma assumed operation of the Dona Ada copper processing plant on September 1, 1996 by making a US $2.0 million payment to the Chilean owner.  This entitles Yuma to 100% of the plants estimated US$200,000 monthly pre-tax profits from the production of approximately 880,000 pounds of copper.  This copper will be produced in the form of an enriched leach solution and sold to Anglo Americas Mantos Blancos SX-EW facility for conversion into copper cathodes.
<P>
The recent granting of the water rights for the Tuina Mine by the Chilean government has allowed Yuma to obtain a 74% interest in the project from International Mahogany Corp. and North Lily Mining.  This clears the way for the construction and start-up of operations at Tuina.
<P>
The feasibility study of the Sierra Gorda Project, being performed by Bateman Engineering of Tucson, Arizona is advancing.  A program of approximately 15,000 metres of reverse circulation drilling is under way for the definition of the ore reserve at Sierra Miranda.</I>
<P>
<P>
