<H2>London Taylor Group</H2>
<H4>U.S. Financial Market Access Program</H4>
<P>
<P>
<A NAME="Ab"><H3>About the London Taylor Group and LTG's monthly Client Companies Update.</H3>
<P>
The London Taylor Group offers a variety of services to publicly traded companies, primarily in the natural resource sector.  These services include investment banking, assistance with legal and regulatory compliance, corporate development and broker/shareholder communications
<P>
The London Taylor Group is extremely selective about its clients.  Before being accepted as a client, each company must meet strict criteria to insure that they have skilled management; a clear and viable business plan; substantial assets; and; a share price the LTG believes is significantly undervalued.
<P>
Each month London Taylor issues its LTG Client Companies Update to the community of financial professionals, including investment bankers, institutional analysts and brokers, retail brokers, financial planners and selected members of the financial press.  Additionally, LTG makes its Update available to a limited number of shareholders in client companies who have indicated an interest in keeping closely in touch with their investment.
<P>
Financial professional carefully follow developments announced each month in the LTG Client Companies Update, in order to keep current with high quality LTG clients, and to prompt investment action.  For those who wish to receive fast breaking news on LTG client companies as it becomes available, a complimentary fax service is also available.  To take advantage, simply call in your fax number to the London Taylor Group at 
1 (800) 485 - 0108 Or, you may fax us at (619) 350-0650.
<P>
<HR>
<P>
<H3>August, 1996</H3>
<P>
<P><CENTER>
<H3>A Publication of the London Taylor Group</H3>
<P>
<H2>The London Taylor Group Client Company Update Service.</H2>
<H4>Time-dated information for financial professionals and shareholders</H4></CENTER>
<P>
<P>
<P>
<P>
<A NAME="Ad"><H2>Adrian Resources</H2>
Nasdaq Symbol:  ADLRF      TSE & VSE Symbol:  ADL<BR>
 $ US $3.50,  CDN $ 4.75<BR>
<P>
Adrian Resources currently owns a 52% interest in one of the world's largest undeveloped copper and gold deposits: 
<P>
<B>The Petaquilla Mineral District in Panama.</B> The total geologic resource stands at 3.74 billion tons containing 31.8 billion pounds of copper, 9.8 million ounces of gold, and 962 million pounds of molybdenum. A scoping study conducted by Flour Daniel Wright has estimated the present value of the concession to be US$955 million at US$1.00lb copper. Adrian trades on the Toronto & Vancouver Stock Exchange under the symbol, ADL and on the Nasdaq, symbol ADLRF.
<P>
<I>Management has formally announced that Bunting Warburg, inc., and Yorkton Securities have been retainedas its joint financial advisors. With the approaching release date of Teck's bankable feasibility study on the Petaquilla project and the growing interest in the senior mining community for a tender offer on 
Adrian's share of the project, Adrian's management felt that the guidance of these two respected institutions in the mining finance  sector was important. Bunting Warburg and Yorkton are currently evaluating the company's strategic options in order to maximize value for shareholders. It is expected that their recommendations will be released within the next few weeks.</I>
<P>
<HR>
<P>
<A NAME="Bo"><H2>Boron Chemicals International</H2>
Vancouver, Symbol: BHI<BR>
C$ 1.70<BR>
<P>
Boron is scheduled to become a leading supplier of industrial minerals when it takes its Aguas Blancas concession in Northern Chile into production in 1998. This concession contains the world's largest proven 
deposits of high grade iodine, and large quantities of sodium sulfate and sodium nitrate, the later being used in the manufacturing of upscale potassium fertilizers. Revenues in its first year of operation are estimated to be US$51 million. Latlnvest Securities Limited, a specialist investment bank, is serving as financial advisor with the goal of raising US$60 million to construct Boron's iodine, sodium sulfate, and potassium nitrate processing plant on Boron's Aguas Blancas property.
<P>
<I>The company has completed two private placements of special warrants for a total of C$23 million finalizing  yet another phase of the US$60 million financing  package for the Aquas Blancas project. Latlnvest, Boron's financial  advisor, is working in conjunction with the Chilean investment bank of Asset-Chile Ltda., to secure the 70% debt financing  portion of the project. In the near-term, Adolf H. Lundin will 
officially assume the position of Chairman of the Board of Boron Chemicals International.</I>
<P>
<HR>
<P>
<A NAME="Co"><H2>Cornucopia Resources</H2>
Nasdaq, Symbol: CNPFG : Toronto, Symbol: CNP<BR>
US $ 1.50,  C $ 2.00<BR>
<P>
<P>
Cornucopia is a junior mining company with a wealth of high potential concessions in North America and Africa. The company is currently developing a 350,000 oz gold deposit at it's Mineral Ridge concession in 
Nevada, and anticipates entering production in early 1997. Cornucopia is in the process of identifying a joint venture partner to assist in the development of their Ivanhoe property, situated in the gold rich Carlin 
Trend, where numerous gold occurrences have been discovered including an intercept grading 37 ounces of gold per ton over an approximate width of 3 feet. Cornucopia's extensive exploration activities in Africa are 
conducted through their affiliate, Carlin Resources (CLM, V.) For more information, call Cornucopia's Audio Text Number, 1-800-558-9035, or contact their web site:<BR>
<B>HTTP:\\ INFOMINE.COM\CORNUCOPIA</B>
<P>
<I>During its active association with London Taylor, CNPGF was introduced to over a million new investors in the U.S. and the share price moved from C$0.75 to the C$2.00 level. Although the company will no longer be followed in the monthly London Taylor Client Company Update, the long-term investment merits of CNPGF are still intact. Shareholders can expect the company's mine at Mineral Ridge to be financed and 
constructed in time to begin production in the first quarter of 1997.  Additionally, Cornucopia expects its substantial groundwork on its Ivanhoe property in Nevada's prolific Carlin Trend to pay off in the 
form of a new joint venture with a senior producer. The company also expects to reap significant rewards from its Strategic Alliance Agreement with Inco to explore the vast mineral deposits the company is currently pursuing on the African continent.</I>
<P>
<HR>
<P>
<A NAME="Ch"><H2>Chase Resources / Delta Gold Mining Corp</H2>
Chase: Toronto, Symbol: CQS, Delta: Vancouver, Symbol; DTG.<BR>
Chase (CGS): C $ 3.91,   Delta (DTG): C $ 2.25 
<P>
<P>
Over the past five years, Chase Resources and its affiliated exploration company, Delta Gold Mining Corp., have engaged in an intensive exploration and land acquisition program in thePhilippines, Chile and, most recently, Indonesia.  This has paid off with the acquisition of a number of highly prospective properties, including the Cikondang Gold Mine in Indonesia and the Taysan copper-gold deposit in the Philippines. Taysan alone is estimated to contain an estimated resource of 2.5 million ounces of gold and 3.6 billion pounds of copper.  By September 1996, Chase and Delta will be amalgamated into a single company. Mining giant BHP is a major shareholder in Chase/Delta and is involved in the joint development of the Taysan deposit. For more information, call Chase's Audio Text Number, 1-800-836-4012.
<P>
<I>Chase continues to expand its drilling program on the Mejilliones Project in northern Chile. Two of the eight holes drilling in the "VT" area of the project identified parallel zones with intercepts of 0.58% 
copper over 6m and 1.03% copper over 8m respectively. Three channel samples from Delta's recent acquisition of Samar Island, Philippines returned average values of 3.16% copper, 427% lead, 8.8% zinc, 
3.23 g/t gold and 595 g/t silver over a 3m exposure.</I>
<P>
<HR>
<P>
<A NAME="Go"><H2>Goldbelt Resources</H2>
Vancouver, Symbol: GDB<BR>
C $ 1.00<BR>
<P>
<P>
Since 1992, Goldbelt Resources has, through a series of strategic partnerships, built a substantial presence in the mineral rich former Soviet Republic of Kazakstan. With three primary concessions in the 
company's coffers, and the financing of production facilities at their Leninogorsk gold project in its final stages, investors can look for Goldbelt to transition from an exploration company into a sizable producer within the next 18 months. For more information, call Goldbelt's Audio Text Service, 1 -800-836-4013.
<P>
<I>Litigation between Goldbelt and Black Swan Mines has officially been concluded, with approximately 3.1 million shares of Goldbelt being issued to Black Swan. While this event, in conjunction with generally 
weak market conditions, has temporarily resulted in a pull-back in share price, the company's assets remain intact and are more undervalued in comparison to share price than ever In other news Mark A. Wilson has 
been appointed Senior Vice-President and Chief Financial Officer. Mr. Wilson has over sixteen years of finance and management experience in the mining industry, and was formally a Vice-President, Business 
Development for Cyprus Amax Minerals Company.</I>
<P>
<HR>
<P>
<A NAME="Gu"><H2>Guyana Gold Corporation</H2>
Toronto, Symbol: GUY<BR>
C $ 0.58<BR>
<P>
<P>
Guyana Gold Corporation is a moderate-sized producer from its Sabi Gold Mine in Zimbabwe. An upgrade is underway, slated for completion by 1998, that will increase production to a significant 40,000 ozs a year at a projected cost of less than $226  per ounce. The company has also begun an exploration program on its Sabi concession designed to double the resource of 1,200,000 ounces during six months of drilling. For an audio update on Guyana, call their Audio Text Number, 1-800-334-2191. Or, visit their web site at: <B>HTTP:\\WNN.GUYANAGOLD.COM.</B>
<P>
<I>Recently, Guyana has entered discussions with its partners concerning the future of its partnership in the Sabi Mine in Zimbabwe. These discussions are amicable and the end result will be to the benefit of 
shareholders. During these discussions, the company's gold production at the Sabi Mine continues. As well, exploration is continuing utilizing diamond drills and the upgrade program is progressing.</I>
<P>
<HR>
<P>
<A NAME="In"><H2>International Panorama Resources</H2>
OTC.BB, Symbol: IPNRF; Vancouver, Symbol: ILP<BR>
C $ 2.70<BR>
<P>
<P>
International Panorama is a Canadian exploration firm with a concession of over 150,000 acres -- one of the largest -- in Canada's Voisey Bay region, near the site of the massive nickel discovery by Diamond Fields Resources. The company's portfolio also includes properties in South East Asia and the United States. In the Union of Myanmar (formerly Burma), the company has been granted exclusive exploration rights to an area potentially rich in gold covering 1,400 sq.km. They are currently negotiating to acquire additional high potential properties in Africa.
<P>
<I>The company will soon release the details of its final negotiations for an advanced mineral project in Africa. International Panorama recently announced the completion of a private placement that saw 1 million units placed and $2.42 million raised for use in its various activities.</I>
<P>
<HR>
<P>
<A NAME="Me"><H2>Metallica Resources</H2>
Toronto, Symbol: MR<BR>
C $ 4.50<BR>
<P>
<P>
Metallica Resources, with one of the most respected management teams in the mining exploration industry, is in the process of developing the Cerro San Pedro gold/silver concession in Mexico. An extensive drill 
program on the property has so far identified a resource of 2.5 million ounces of gold and 68 million ounces of silver... ranking Cerro San Pedro among the three largest gold/ silver deposits in Mexico. A bankable feasibility study is currently in the works. Once it is released, the decision to enter production should quickly follow.
<P>
<I>The company entered the London Taylor program in January, 1996 when its shares were trading at C$2.85. Since then, MR stock has traded as high as C$6.50, attained full US20-F federal, state and local level blue-sky registration, and completed the requirements for a NASDAQ listing.  As a consequence, the secondary market among U.S. investors has been substantially expanded. In the near-term, Metallica shareholders can 
expect the full feasibility study for the Cerro San Pedro gold-silver project to be completed in the First  quarter of 1997.</I>
<P>
<HR>
<P>
<A NAME="Si"><H2>Silver Standard Resources.</H2>
(Nasdaq, Symbol: SSRIF, Vancouver, Symbol: SSO)<BR>
US $ 4.15 C $ 5.60<BR>
<P>
<P>
Silver Standard is a silver exploration with a mission to secure a group of properties with a minimum total defined in-ground resource of 25O,OOO,OOO ounces of silver by 1997, and to become a significant silver 
producer within four years. Silver Standard, which has multi-million ounce concessions in Bolivia, Mexico and the Russian Far East is a top recommendation of a number of leading analysts, including Doug Casey, 
Jim Blanchard, Adrian Day and Rick Rule.
<P>
<I>The most advanced of Silver Standard's rapidly growing inventory of silver properties is the Lunnoe property in the Russian Far East, an exploration license that has proven and probable reserves of 120 million 
ounces of silver and 500,000 ounces of gold. A 500 ton per day processing plant has already been partially constructed on the property, and is scheduled to commence production in 1998. In the interim, Silver 
Standard continues to use its considerable cash position - over C$10 million - to acquire new concessions and to explore its existing concessions. For a comprehensive Corporate profile  on this exciting way 
to leverage the potential for strong gains in silver prices in the coming years, call 1-800-485-0108.</I>
<P>
<HR>
<P>
<A NAME="Yu"><H2>Yuma Gold Corp.</H2>
Vancouver, Symbol: YUM<BR>
C $ 3.60<BR>
<P>
<P>
Yuma is an exceptionally well-managed company that is pursuing a two-tiered strategy that will result in its becoming a mid-tier copper producer in the near future. 
<P>
The first part of the strategic plan is to make the first main payment towards the purchase of the Dona Ada copper cement facility, thus giving Yuma a 100% ownership of the plant's cashflow, estimated to be $15O,000 
- 20O,OOO per month. Concurrently Yuma will commence construction of copper sulphate plants at Tuina and at the recently acquired Sierra Miranda site.
<P>
The second part of the strategy will result in the building of a Solvent Extraction Electrowinning (SX-EW) plant at Sierra Miranda for the production of copper cathodes. Once the SX-EW plant is operational, the 
copper sulphate plant will be moved to Dona Ada. Both Dona Ada and Tuina will continue to produce copper sulphate crystals for shipment to Sierra Miranda and conversion into copper cathodes. Total production of copper cathodes at the Sierra Miranda plant is estimated at 4O,OOO tonnes (88 million pounds) per annum.
<P>
<I>While a major portion of the finance package for Yuma's SX-EW plant nears completion, the company has successfully expanded its total proven reserves of copper and has dramatically increased the percentage grades 
of copper within its overall geological reserves. This data from the Sierra Miranda concession is currently being completed for public release.
<P>
Yuma is currently poised to become a positively cash-flowing copper producer within the next 6 weeks. Inspite of the recent fall in the price of copper all of the projects within the Yuma's "stable" are still 
anticipated to be profitable table.</I>
<P>
<P>
