<H3>July 1996</H3>
<P>
<P><CENTER>
<H3>A Publication of the London Taylor Group</H3>
<P>
<H2>The London Taylor Group Client Company Update Service.</H2>
<H4>Time-dated information for financial professionals and shareholders</H4></CENTER>
<P>
<P>
<P>
<P>
<A NAME="Ad"><H2>Adrian Resources</H2>
Nasdaq Symbol:  ADLRF      TSE Symbol:  ADL<BR>
 $ US $4.00,  CDN $ 5.35<BR>
<P>
Adrian Resources currently owns a 52% interest in one of the world's largest undeveloped copper and gold deposits: 
<P>
<B>The Petaquilla Mineral District in Panama.</B> The total geologic resource stands at 3.74 billion tons containing 31.8 billion pounds of copper, 9.8 million ounces of gold, and 962 million pounds of molybdenum. A scoping study conducted by Flour Daniel Wright has estimated the present value of the concession to be US$955 million at US$1.00lb copper. Adrian trades on the Toronto Stock Exchange under the symbol, ADL and on the Nasdaq, symbol ADLRF.
<P>
<I>The Teck Corporation, Adrian's strategic partner in the Petaquilla, continues to work on its bankable feasibility study. This study is on schedule for release in November of 1996. Teck's study has identified yet another mineral in Petaquilla's massive reserves: In addition to copper, gold and molybdenum, a significant amount of recoverable silver has been identified within the copper concentrate. Based on $5.00 silver, the silver reserves identified thus far translates into an estimated $6 million of additional net annual revenue.</I>
<P>
<HR>
<P>
<A NAME="Bo"><H2>Boron Chemicals International</H2>
Vancouver, Symbol: BHI<BR>
C$ 1.60<BR>
<P>
Boron is scheduled to become a leading supplier of industrial minerals when it takes its Aguas Blancas concession in Northern Chile into production in 1998. This concession contains the world's largest proven deposits of high grade iodine, and large quantities of sodium sulfate and sodium nitrate, the later being used in the manufacturing of upscale fertilizers.  Revenues in its first year of operation are estimated to be 
US$51 million-2E.  LatInvest Securities Limited, a specialist investment bank, is serving as financial advisors with the goal of raising US$60 million to construct Boron's iodine, sodium sulfate, and potassium nitrate processing plant on Boron's Aguas Blancas property.
<P>
<I>The company has recently completed a C$20 million financing. This represents the 30% equity portion of the total financing package required to put the Aguas Blancas project into production. Using commodity prices below current levels, the Bateman Bankable Evaluation study projects annual revenues from the Aguas Blancas to be approximately $51 million against annual operating costs of $21.3 million. Boron President Bob Oliverio confirms that commercial production is now possible by the first quarter of 1998.</I>
<P>
<HR>
<P>
<A NAME="Co"><H2>Cornucopia Resources</H2>
Nasdaq, Symbol: CNPFG : Toronto, Symbol: CNP<BR>
US $ 1.40,  C $ 2.00<BR>
<P>
<P>
Cornucopia is a junior mining company with a wealth of high potential concessions in North America and Africa. The company is currently developing a 350,000 oz gold deposit at its Mineral Ridge concession in Nevada, and anticipate entering production in early 1997. Cornucopia is in the process of identifying a joint venture partner to assist in the development of its Ivanhoe property, situated in the gold rich Carlin Trend, where numerous gold occurrences have been discovered including an intercept grading  37 ounces of gold per ton over 3 feet. Cornucopia's extensive exploration activities in Africa are conducted through its affiliate, Carlin Resources (CLM, V.) For more information, call Cornucopia's Audio Text Number, 1-800-558-9035, or contact their web site: HTTP:\\ INFOMINE.COM\CORNUCOPIA.
<P>
<I>The final approval from the Bureau of Land Management regarding the permitting required to proceed with development of Cornucopia's Mineral Ridge property is expected shortly. Cornucopia has already been granted qualified acceptance for the $15 million of project financing that will be required for mine construction at Mineral Ridge. The company is on schedule to begin production at this mine during the first quarter of 1997, a major change in status which should attract the attention of both institutional and individual resource investors.</I>
<P>
<HR>
<P>
<A NAME="Ch"><H2>Chase Resources / Delta Gold Mining Corp</H2>
Chase: Toronto, Symbol: CQS, Delta: Vancouver, Symbol; DTG.<BR>
Chaes (CGS): C $ 4.40,   Delta (DTG): C $ 2.40 
<P>
<P>
Over the past five years, Chase Resources and its affiliated exploration company, Delta Gold Mining Corp., have engaged in an intensive exploration and land acquisition program in the Philippines, Chile and, most recently, Indonesia. This has paid off with the acquisition of a number of highly prospective properties, including the Cikondang Gold Mine in Indonesia and the Taysan copper-gold deposit in the Philippines.  Taysan alone is estimated to contain an estimated resource of 2.5 million ounces of gold and 3.6 billion pounds of copper. By September 1996, Chase and Delta should be amalgamated into a single company. Mining giant BHP is a major shareholder in Chase/Delta and is involved in the joint development of the Taysan deposit. For more information, call Chase's Audio Text Number, 1-800-836-4012.
<P>
<I>* Additional trench results from the El Paso prospect --  located within the Batangas FTAA in the Philippines --  has identified two new zones of mineralization containing significant percentages of gold and copper. These results add to the substantial copper content discovered in late May along El Paso's three large copper and gold mineralization zones where soil sampling has already uncovered values of 0.58% copper. 
<P>
* Delta Gold recently entered into an option agreement to acquire large mineral concessions on Samar Island, Philippines, which will effectively double Chase's property assets upon completion of the pending Chase/Delta amalgamation.  
<P>
*In other news, drilling at the Mejilliones Project in Northern Chile has reported encouraging results. As only a very limited portion of the property, of which Chase has the right to acquire 75%, has been explored thus far, and additional drilling is scheduled for this summer, you'll want to watch for more news in the weeks and months ahead.</I>
<P>
<HR>
<P>
<A NAME="Go"><H2>Goldbelt Resources</H2>
Vancouver, Symbol: GDB<BR>
C $ 1.51<BR>
<P>
<P>
Since 1992, Goldbelt Resources has, through a series of strategic partnerships, built a substantial presence in the mineral rich former Soviet Republic of Kazakstan. With three primary concessions in the company's coffers, and the financing of production facilities at their Leninogorsk gold project in its final stages, investors can look for Goldbelt to transition from an exploration company into a sizable producer within the next 
18 months. For more information, call Goldbelt's Audio Text Service, 1-800-836-4013.
<P>
<I>* As part of a larger program designed to expand the known resource base of Goldbelt's Kazakstan concessions, drilling has commenced on the company's massive sulphide target in Kakbit to the south of the Abyz, as well as on its Ozerny porphyry copper deposit. In Ozerny the deposit consists of a large low grade deposit of over 140 million tons containing 0.39% copper. * At its Mykubinshoe license area Goldbelt has identified 179 prospects, deposits and mines. The company is on schedule to produce a preliminary feasibility study on their Abyz concession by mid-September, 1996.</I>
<P>
<HR>
<P>
<A NAME="Gu"><H2>Guyana Gold Corporation</H2>
Toronto, Symbol: GUY<BR>
C $ 1.15<BR>
<P>
<P>
Guyana Gold Corporation is a moderate-sized producer from its Sabi Gold Mine in Zimbabwe. An upgrade is underway, slated for completion by 1998, that will increase production to a significant 40,000 ozs a year at a projected cost of less than $226  per ounce. The company has also begun an exploration program on its Sabi concession designed to double the resource of 1,200,000 ounces during six months of drilling. For an audio update on Guyana, call their Audio Text Number, 1-800-334-2191. Or, visit their web site at: <B>HTTP:\\WNN.GUYANAGOLD.COM.</B>
<P>
<I>Guyana's on-site team of geologists is planning to expand the extensive drilling program that began in March at the Sabi mine to also include property adjacent to the Sabi which the company recently acquired. Guyana is anticipating near-term release of results from its current drill programs at the Sabi.</I>
<P>
<HR>
<P>
<A NAME="In"><H2>International Panorama Resources</H2>
OTC.BB, Symbol: IPNRF; Vancouver, Symbol: ILP<BR>
C $ 2.80<BR>
<P>
<P>
International Panorama is a Canadian exploration firm with a concession of over 150,000 acres -- one of the largest -- in Canada's Voisey Bay region, near the site of the massive nickel discovery by Diamond Fields Resources. The company's portfolio also includes properties in South East Asia and the United States. In the Union of Myanmar (formerly Burma), the company has been granted exclusive exploration rights to an area potentially rich in gold covering 1,400 sq.km. They are currently negotiating to acquire additional high potential properties in Africa.
<P>
<I>The company has entered into an agreement with Veto Resources by which Veto will purchase a 75% interest in 244 out of the 2,227 claims that make up International Panorama's massive land position in Canada's Voisey's Bay. This move is being made to allow company management to concentrate time and resources on only the most prospective of the Voisey's Bay claims, as well as to focus on considerable opportunities which the company is currently pursuing elsewhere in the world.</I>
<P>
<HR>
<P>
<A NAME="Me"><H2>Metallica Resources</H2>
Toronto, Symbol: MR<BR>
C $ 4.80<BR>
<P>
<P>
Metallica Resources, with one of the most respected management teams in the mining exploration industry, is in the process of developing the Cerro San Pedro gold/silver concession in Mexico. An extensive drill program on the property has so far identified a resource of 2.5 million ounces of gold and 68 million ounces of silver... ranking Cerro San Pedro among the three largest gold/silver deposits in Mexico. A bankable feasibility study is currently in the works. Once it is released, the decision to enter  production should quickly follow.
<P>
<I>The first drill results from the 1996 ore reserve expansion program at the Cerro San Pedro gold-silver project have returned grades of 1.10 grams per ton gold and 31.2 grams per ton silver over a 160 meter interval. This 50  meter step-out hole is located north of the previously defined reserve area and will be followed up with at least 8-10 additional drill holes in July.  The full feasibility study for the Cerro San Pedro is underway, and the company expects completion in the first quarter of 1997. The C$11.65 million of net proceeds from the financing completed in April has been received in Metallica's treasury.</I>
<P>
<HR>
<P>
<A NAME="Yu"><H2>Yuma Gold Corp.</H2>
Vancouver, Symbol: YUM<BR>
C $ 4.07<BR>
<P>
<P>
Yuma is an exceptionally well-managed company that is pursuing a two-tiered strategy that will result in its becoming a mid-tier copper producer in the near future. 
<P>
The first part of the strategic plan is to complete the acquisition of the Dona Ada copper cement plant on September 1, 1996, thus allowing for the production of 5,100 tonnes (11 million pounds) of copper per annum.  In conjunction with the copper cement production that will provide a positive cash flow to the company, Yuma will construct copper sulphate plants at the Tuina and the recently acquired Sierra Miranda sites to produce copper sulphate crystals for shipment to the cement plant at Dona Ada.
<P>
The second part of the strategy will result in the building of a Solvent Extraction Electrowinning (SX - EW)
plant at Sierra Miranda for the production of copper cathodes.  Once the SX-EW plant is operational, the copper sulphate plant will be moved to Dona Ada.  Both Dona Ada and Tuina will continue to produce copper sulphate crystals for shipment to Sierra Miranda and conversion into copper cathodes.  Total production of copper cathodes at the Sierra Miranda plant is estimated at 40,000 tonnes (88 million pounds) per annum.
<P>
<I>* Yuma has made significant progress on the financing for its SX-EW and copper sulphate plants.  In the near future the company is planning to announce the details regarding the equity portion of its total financing package.  If you have not yet received a comprehensive corporate profile on Yuma Gold Corp., then call 
the London Taylor Group at (619) 431-5135.</I>
