<A NAME="Ad"><H2>Adrian Resources</H2>
Nasdaq Symbol:  ADLRF      TSE Symbol:  ADL<BR>
 $ US $4.50,  CDN $ 6.40<BR>
<P>
Adrian Resources currently owns a 52% interest in one of the world's largest undeveloped copper and gold deposits:
<P>
<B>The Petaquilla Mineral District in Panama.</B>  The total geologic resource stands at 3.74 billion tonnes containing 3.1 billion pounds of copper, 9.8 million ounces of gold, and 962 million pounds of molybdenum.  A scoping study conducted by Fluor Daniel Wright has estimated the present value of the concession to be US $ 1.54 billion at US $1.20 lb copper, and US $ 955 million at US $1.00 lb copper.  Adrian trades on the Toronto Stock Exchange under the symbol ADL and on the Nasdaq, symbol ADLRF.
<P>
<I>The Teck Corporation continues to prepare its bankable feasibility study on the Petaquilla.  Inmet, owners of 48% of the concession, have raised over $ 400,000,000 in recent months in a move, many believe, is designed to allow them to finance their share of bringing the massive deposit to production.  Based on a copper price of $ 1.00 per lb, the Fluor Daniel study estimates Adrian's value at Cdn $ 11.74 per share.</I>
