<A NAME="Bo"><H2>Boron Chemicals International</H2>
Vancouver, Symbol: BHI<BR>
C$ 1.60<BR>
<P>
Boron is scheduled to become a leading supplier of industrial minerals when it takes its Aguas Blancas concession in Northern Chile into production in 1998.  The concession contains the world's largest proven deposits of high grade iodine, and large quantities of sodium sulfate and sodium nitrate, the later being used in the manufacturing of upscale fertilizers.  Revenues in its first year of operation are estimated to be US $ 51 million.  LatInvest Securities Limited, a specialist investment bank, is serving as financial advisors with the goal of raising US $ 60 million to construct the iodine, sodium sulfate, and potassium nitrate processing plant on Boron's Aguas Blancas property in Chile.
<P>
<I>On May 23rd stock trading was interrupted after it was announced that well-known financier Adolf H. Lundin, Chairman of the Board of International Petroleum Corporation, will purchase two million out of three million units being issued by Boron as part of a private placement.  The company has also announced that Mr. Lundin will join the company as a director.  The balance of the private placement has been purchased by Trans America Industries, bringing tht company's total ownership to 23.8% of the issued shares of Boron.  The strong market prices of the industrial minerals Boron will produce continues to increase the company's net present value.  If you have not yet received a copy of the Corporate Profile prepared for this unique company, call London Taylor toll-free 
at 800-485-0108</I>
