<P>
<I>In late breaking news, it was announced that Chase and Delta have entered into a partnership to acquire control of the Cikondang Gold Mine in Indonesia. Based on work done in 1992, proven and probable reserves at Cikondang were estimated to be a minimum of 430,000 tonnes with a grade of 13.4 g/t gold. The deposit remains open and diamond drilling has confirmed that significant high grade zones are present. This move into Indonesia resents an exciting new dimension to Chase/Delta.  Pay close attention forfurther announcements on this project. In other news, Mr. Lee Browne II was elected to the board of directors. Mr. Browne has been a Vice President of BHP Copper Nevada Mining Company and a general manager for Magma's subsidiary in Peru. Delta Gold Mining Corp., which will soon amalgamate with Chase, recently appointed Mr. James Robertson to its board of directors. 
Mr. Robertson is the principal of Midas Management, Inc., which provides financial, corporate, and technical services to the mining industry.</I>
