Guyana Gold Corporation is a moderate-sized producer (12,000 ounces annually) from its Sabi Gold Mine in Zimbabwe. An upgrade is underway which is slated for completion by the latter half of 1998. This upgrade is anticipated to increase production to a significant 40,000 ozs a year at a projected cost of less than $226  per ounce. The company has also begun an exploration program on its Sabi concession which is designed to double the present resource of 1,200,000 ounces during the first six months of drilling. For an audio update on Guyana, call their Audio Text Number, 1-800-334-2191. Or, visit their web site at: <B>HTTP:\\WNN.GUYANAGOLD.COM.</B>
<P>
<I>Guyana's on-site team of geologists continues the drilling program which began in March at the Sabi mine. So far, this program has already identified additional reserves of 300,000 ounces of gold, bringing total reserves to 1.5 million ounces. As part of their expansion, it was recently announced that they have acquired additional property adjacent to their Sabi mining lease. This new property contains a small established mine and an estimated resource of at least 100,000 ounces of gold. The drilling program at the Sabi is at a very exciting stage, and additional results should be released in June.</I>
