<A NAME="Me"><H2>Metallica Resources</H2>
Toronto, Symbol: MR<BR>
C $ 5.00<BR>
<P>
<P>
Metallica Resources, with one of the most respected management teams in the mining exploration industry, is in the process of developing the Cerro San Pedro gold/silver concession in Mexico. An extensive drill program on the property has so far identified a resource of 2.5 million ounces of gold and 68 million ounces of silver... ranking Cerro San Pedro among the five largest gold/silver deposits in Mexico. A bankable feasibility study is now scheduled to be completed in the fourth quarter of 1996, after which a decision to enter production should quickly follow.
<P>
<I>In addition to progressing on the bankable feasibility study on their Cerro San Pedro gold-silver deposit, the company has recently taken steps to widen its exploration program by entering into a joint venture agreement with Compania Minera Taura, a private Chilean mining company. The purpose of this agreement is to explore and develop the 1,780 hectare Los Choros copper-gold project located in north-central Chile. Metallica's initial exploration plan consists of detailed ground magnetic and IP surveys followed by a "first pass" drilling program. A <B>Special Note:</B>  In May, profit taking brought Metallica's shares back to an extremely attractive level when compared to underlying assets and to the caliber of its management. We do not expect Metallica to remain at these levels for long.</I>
