<HR>
<P>
<A NAME="Yu"><H2>Yuma Gold Corp.</H2>
Vancouver, Symbol: YUM<BR>
C $ 4.10<BR>
<P>
<P>
Yuma is an exceptionally well managed company which is pursuing a two-tiered strategy that will result in its becoming a mid-tier copper producer in the near future. The first part of the strategic plan calls for putting  the Tuina and Dona Ada mines into production in 1996.  It is estimated that the Tuina alone will generate up to 13,200,000 pounds annually of high quality copper cathode once production commences. The second part of the strategy calls for the building of a large processing facility on the Dona Ada, and "contract processing" copper sulphide crystals and copper oxide ores for other mines in the region. This will boost production to over 80,000,000 pounds of copper per annum. 
<P>
<I>Yuma has officially completed its acquisition of the Tuina copper mine from International Mahogany Corp., and North Lily Mining Ltd. Additionally, the company has signed an agreement to acquire the Dona Ada copper-cement plant, a producing mine with some US8.5 million in annual production. The centrally located Dona Ada will be the site of a far larger processing facility, including a large electrowinning (EW) where final processing of copper sulfate crystals into copper cathodes is done. Negotiations are now well underway for the financing needed to build the $80 million facilities at the Dona Ada.</I>
<P>
<P>
<P>
<P>
<CENTER>
