<HR>
<P>
<TITLE>TOP TEN BOOK #5</TITLE> 
<P>
<P>
<H2> Investment Biker</H2>
<P>
 Jim Rogers, 402pp, 
<P>
Item #6055 -- $25.00US<BR>
<P>
<P>
In the 1970's Wall Street legend Jim Rogers made what he describes as "more money than I knew existed in the world" managing the Quantum fund with George Soros. At age 37 he retired. In 1990 he and his girlfriend set off on a motorcycle trip around the world, not only to travel, but to learn about the world's developing countries and investment markets by actually going to them. Twenty-two months and 65,076 land miles later and after talking to businessmen, bankers, investors and regular people all over the globe, he tells you who's sinking and who's swimming and where you can make a million and where you can lose your shirt.
<P>
<P></BODY>
</HTML>


