<CENTER><H2>Laurence McKinley Gould Library Exhibit</H2></CENTER>

<DL>
<DD>Take a tour of this cyberspace version of an exhibit currently on display in our Library lobby.  In October of 1995,
the Carleton Library was renamed the Laurence McKinley Gould Library in honor of this former polar explorer, Carleton faculty member,
and revered Carleton College president. (Note: This exhibit is best when viewed with Netscape and a monitor which is set to display
at least 64,000 colors.)
</DL>
