<HTML> 
<TITLE>Circulation Policy Summary</TITLE> 
<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF" LINK="#004000"> 
<CENTER><H2>Circulation Policy Summary</H2></CENTER><P><P>



<STRONG>Telephone numbers</STRONG><BR><BR>  
<UL> 
<LI>Main Library Circulation Desk: 646-4260  
<LI>Main Library Reserves Desk: 646-4263 
</UL>

<CENTER>

<STRONG>
<A HREF="#ID">Library Barcodes/ID</A> |
<A HREF="#PERIODS">Loan Periods</A> |
<A HREF="#RENEWALS">Renewals</A> |
<A HREF="#H&R">Holds & Recalls</A> |
<A HREF="#OVERDUES">Overdues</A> |
<A HREF="#NONCIRC">Non-Circulating Material</A>

</STRONG>
</CENTER>
<BR>
<BR>

<HR> 
<HR>
<A NAME="ID">
<IMG SRC="idcard.jpg" height=90 width=150 vspace=5 hspace=5 align=right> 
<BR CLEAR=left><STRONG>Library Barcode ID</STRONG><BR><BR>

To borrow material from the Carleton library you must be
registered in the library's circulation computer system and have been issued a
library barcode ID.<BR><BR>

You must present your library barcode ID for any circulation or reserve
transaction. No other form of identification is acceptable.<BR><BR>

Carleton students, faculty and staff are registered automatically and may
pick up their library ID card at the library's circulation desk.  St. Olaf students,
faculty & staff may register the first time they use the
Carleton library.

All others should inquire about their eligibility for a library barcode at the circulation desk.  
A form of identification, such as a driver's license or campus food service card, may be required 
to secure the library card.
<BR><BR>


<HR><A NAME="PERIODS">
<TABLE> 
<STRONG>Loan Periods</STRONG><BR><BR> 
<TD>Carleton faculty<TD>365 day loan<TR> 
<TD>Carleton students & staff<TD>Term loan<TR>
<TD>Carleton alums & family members <TD>5 week loan <TR> 
<TD>St. Olaf students, faculty & staff<TD>5 week loan <TR> 
<TD>Northfield residents<TD>2 week loan <TR> 
<TD>periodicals<TD>1 week loan <TR> 
<TD>open reserve material<TD>2 day loan  <TR> 
<TD>videotapes on reserve<TD>3 hour loan <TR> 
<TD>closed reserve material<TD>2 hour loan 
</TABLE><BR><BR>



<HR><A NAME="RENEWALS">
<STRONG>Renewals</STRONG><BR><BR> 

Renewals are permitted for renewable items that do not have a hold placed on them. Renewable items are reserve items, term loans, and five week loans.

General collection and open reserve items may be renewed:
<UL>
<LI>before the item is overdue by viewing your circulation record 	on Muse and selecting renew
<LI>by writing "please renew" on the reminder notice and returning the notice to the circulation desk
<LI>in person at the circulation desk
<LI>by e-mail to circadmin@muse.library.carleton.edu
</UL>
Closed reserve items may be renewed:
<UL>
<LI>before the item is overdue by viewing your circulation record 	on Muse and selecting renew
<LI>in person at the circulation desk
</UL> 
Sorry, but we cannot accept renewal requests by telephone.
<BR> <BR> 



<HR><A NAME="H&R">
<STRONG>Holds & Recalls</STRONG><BR><BR> 

A hold may be placed on material that is already checked out. Placing a hold on an item is the 
equivalent of being placed on a waiting list for that item. 
<BR><BR>  
Material is subject to recall if the current borrower has had it for more than two weeks. 
<BR> <BR> 
If an item is recalled it must be returned within four days of the date of recall. 
<BR> <BR> 
Recalled material must be picked up within four days of the date of the notice of availability.
<BR> <BR> 



<HR>
<STRONG>Overdues - General Collection</STRONG><BR><BR> 

The day after an item is due the library's computer system will send a<STRONG> reminder notice.
</STRONG> At this time you should renew or return this item. A week later, if you have not renewed 
or returned the item, an <STRONG>overdue notice </STRONG>will be sent. Two weeks after the item 
was due, a second overdue notice will be sent and your account will be blocked from further 
transactions. A month after the due date you will be billed for the replacement cost of the item.
<BR> <BR> 
You are responsible for the timely return of all materials, whether or not you receive any 
reminder or overdue notices from the library.
<BR><BR> 

<A NAME="OVERDUES">
<STRONG>Overdues - Reserves</STRONG><BR><BR> 
The process for overdue open reserve material is similar to that for general collection material, 
except the interval between overdue notices is three days.
<BR><BR>
The process for closed reserves is different because a system of fines applies. The fine for an 
item being 10 minutes to 60 minutes late is $1.00. An item that is more than one hour late but 
less than two hours late has a fine of $2.00. There is an additional $5.00 fine for each hour 
after that, up to a maximum of $27.00.
<BR><BR>
In addition to the fine incurred, students who keep closed reserve material overdue for more than 
7 hours are referred to the Academic Standing Committee for disciplinary action.
<BR><BR>



<HR><A NAME="NONCIRC"></A>
<STRONG>Non-circulating Material</STRONG><BR><BR> 

The following types of
materials do not usually circulate. Special permission may be given for a
special need. Consult a librarian.<BR> 
<UL> 
<LI>Reference books 
<LI>Special collection books (consult the College Archivist) 
<LI>Microfilm, microfiche
<LI>Books marked "non-circulating" or "not to leave the library" 
<LI>Newspapers 
<LI>Bloch Western Americana books 
<LI>maps from level 3</UL>
However special permission may be given for a special need, so consult a librarian.

<BR CLEAR=LEFT>
<HR>
<br>
<STRONG><a href="/studentworkers/jobs/circjob.html">Student Employment Opportunites with 
Circulation</a></strong> 
<p>
<hr>
Any questions about Circulation and the services they offer should be addressed to 
<A href="mailto:jedwins@carleton.edu">Jennifer Edwins</a>.  She may be reached by e-mail, 
by phone at 507-646-4259, or in her office between 8 am and 3 pm Monday through Friday.
<P>
<HR>
<P>
