<a name="firstsearch">
<h2 align=center>InterLibrary Services</h2>

<p>
InterLibrary Services may be used to obtain library materials for study and research which are not available at Carleton or St. Olaf, but are available from other North American libraries willing to lend. 

<blockquote>
<IMG SRC="/images/new.gif" ALT="[New!]">Many materials identified on the <a href="/electronic/online/firstsearch.html">FirstSearch</a> database service can now be requested through ILS electronically, within FirstSearch.  Simply choose the <strong><tt>Order</tt></strong> or <strong><tt>Get Item</tt></strong> option (when present), then select the <strong><tt>Interlibrary Loan (ILL)</tt></strong> method for requesting the item, and follow the instructions.  <em>Please provide all information prompted for.</em>  Your request is instantly transmitted directly to a terminal in the ILS office in the Libe.
</blockquote>
<br>
<h3 align=center><IMG SRC="/images/new.gif" ALT="[New!]"><br><a href="summary.html"><strong>InterLibrary Services Policy and Overview</strong><br> (answers to most frequently asked questions about ILS)</h3> </a>
<br>
