<CENTER><H1>Laurence McKinley Gould<BR>Online Exhibit</H1></CENTER>
<HR SIZE="3">
<P>
<IMG ALIGN="LEFT" HSPACE="5" SRC="ImagesIV/gouldplans.gif" ALT="[President Gould at his desk]">
<P>
The Carleton College Library has been renamed for former College President Laurence McKinley Gould. The renaming of the library was announced in this Oct. 13, 1995 <A HREF="http://www.carleton.edu:80/news/Gould.library.html">Press Release</A>.
<P>
Links to related Web sites:
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://http2.sils.umich.edu/Antarctica/Bibliography/Internet.html">Antarctica-Related Internet Information Resources
<LI><A HREF="http://www.city.net/regions/antarctica/">Antarctica Facts and Maps</A>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.vni.net/~kwelch/misc/blue_ice.shtml">Blue Ice:  Focus on Antarctica</A>
<LI><A HREF="http://www-bprc.mps.ohio-state.edu/">Byrd Polar Research Center Home Page</A>
<LI><A HREF="http://icair.iac.org.nz/">Gateway to Antarctica</A>
<LI><A HREF="http://139.132.40.31/NSPT/NSPThomePage.html">The New South Pole Times</A>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.vni.net/~kwelch/penguin.shtml">The Penguin Page</A>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.theplanet.net/soloantarctica/">Solo Antarctica</A>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.terraquest.com/">Virtual Antarctica</A>
<LI><A HREF="http://icair.iac.org.nz/reports/nz/visitor.html">Visitor's Guide to Antarctica</A>
</UL>
The following exhibit is an online version of the one currently on display at the Laurence McKinley
Gould Library at Carleton College to commemorate the occasion of its renaming. <BR>(N.B.: It is best when viewed with Netscape and
a monitor which is set to display at least 64,000 colors.)
<BR CLEAR="ALL">
