<head>
<title>The Unsung Webslingers of the Carleton Libe</title>
<base href="http://www.library.carleton.edu/studentworkers/">
</head>

<body bgcolor="#ffffff">
<center><img src="Webslingers.jpeg"></center>
<P>
Out here on the Electronic Frontier, folks don't always get credit for their work.  This
group of faithful student workers helps maintain the Carleton Library's WWW site.  Therefore, Terry Metz has
encouraged them to stake their claim to a small chunk of cyberspace to talk about themselves a bit.  So 
if you're curious about what today's small liberal arts college students are up to, interested 
in making new 'net friends, or just plain bored, take a look at their home pages.
<p>
<hr>
<p>
<UL>
<LI><A href=aaron/aaron.html>Aaron Bostwick</a> '96 (Physics/Astronomy) from
Prescott, AZ 
<li><a href=jeremy/index.html>Jeremy A. Bled</a> '97 (American Studies) from 
Berkeley, CA
<LI><A HREF="peter/peter.html">Peter Goss</A>  '96 from Concord, NH
<LI><A href=josh/josh.html>Josh Mitchell</A> '97 (Classical
Languages) from Auburn, ME 
<LI><a href=celena/celena.html>Celena Peet</A> '97 (History) from Hubbard, IA
<LI><a href=ed/index.html>Ed Zamora</a> '97 (Biology) from Albuquerque, NM
</UL>
<p>
