<head>
<title>Terry Metz</title>
</head>

<body BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">
<IMG vspace=3 hspace=10 align=right SRC=terry.GIF border=2 ALT="Terry at his desk.">
<H2>Terry Metz</H2>
<P>
Terry is Carleton's <strong>Loan Services &amp; Instruction Librarian</strong>.  
He arrived in April of 1992 and has overseen a lot of technological changes in the 
library during the past four and one-half years.
<P>
From 1986-1992, Terry served as Consortium Manager for Cooperating Libraries in Consortium (CLIC),
a non-profit consortium of seven private liberal arts college libraries in the Twin Cities of Minneapolis/
St. Paul, Minnesota:
<P>
<CENTER>
<A HREF="http://www.augsburg.edu/">Augsburg College</A> |
<A HREF="http://www.bethel.edu/">Bethel College</A> |
<A HREF="http://www.stkate.edu/">College of St. Catherine</A> |
<A HREF="http://www.csp.edu/">Concordia College</A> |
<A HREF="http://www.hamline.edu/">Hamline University</A> |
<A HREF="http://www.macalester.edu/">Macalester College</A> |
<A HREF="http://www.stthomas.edu/">University of St. Thomas</A>
</CENTER>
<BR>
<P>
His first library employment was at <A HREF="http://www.hamline.edu/library/index.html">Hamline University's Bush Library</A> in St. Paul, Minnesota, between 1981-1986.
<P>
Terry received B.A. degrees in business administration and geography from <A HREF="http://www.gac.edu/">
Gustavus Adolphus College</A> in 1980, and an M.A. in library science from the <A HREF="http://www.umn.edu/tc/">
University of Minnesota</A> in 1985.
<P>
Terry is a military history enthusiast who can tell you a lot about aerial and naval warfare, particularly in WWI and WWII.  His favorite naval interest is WWII naval combat in the Pacific Theater, although he can tell you a fair amount about the war in the Atlantic, too, such as the pursuit and sinking of the German battleship <I>Bismarck</I>.
<P>
Behind his back, we say that Terry's a bathtub admiral who missed his calling as a naval intelligence officer.
<P>
Terry is also an American Civil War buff.  He's visited and tramped over many Civil War battlefields.
<p>
See Terry's cats, <a href="scout&flower.html">Scout and Flower.</a>
<p>
<CENTER><A HREF="mailto:temetz@carleton.edu">Send E-mail to Terry</A>
<p>
<HR>
<p>
<a href="terry.html">Return to Terry's Professional Home Page</a></CENTER>
