<html>

<head>
<title>The Laurence McKinley Gould Library Building</title>
</head>

<body bgcolor=#fffff>
<img src="/images/outside.GIF">
<p>
<CENTER><H2>The Laurence McKinley Gould Library Building</H2></CENTER>
<p>
<LI><A HREF="hours.html">Hours</a>
<LI><A HREF="#lockers">Lockers</A>
<LI><A HREF="#phones">Public Telephones</A>
<LI><A HREF="#food">Food & Drink Policy</A>
</UL>
<p>
<HR>
<A NAME="lockers"><H3>Lockers</H3></A>
<UL>
<LI>Library lockers are located on the lower three levels of the main library.  Students may sign up for a locker and get a key at the circulation desk.  
<LI>Lockers are to be used for the storage of personal items and library materials that HAVE BEEN CHECKED OUT.
<LI>Lockers are subject to periodic searches.  Students are responsible for whatever is found in their lockers.
<LI>Students should keep their lockers locked.  The College is not responsible for stolen articles.
<LI>Students should empty their lockers before turning in the key.
<li>Keys must be returned before Commencement Day each year.  A $10 lock replacement fine is applicable to those who do not turn in their keys.
</UL>
<HR>
<A NAME="phones"><H3>Public Telephones</H3></A>
Public phones are available throughout the Library.  A payphone is located in the lobby
on the fourth floor, and campus phones are on the landings of the west stairway
on the other floors.  There is also a phone in the computer area on the third floor
Holo Deck.
<p>
<hr>
<A NAME="food"><H3>Food & Drink Policy</H3></A>
Absolutely no food or drink is allowed in the library.  Food and drink are incompatible
with the libary's mission of preserving needed teaching and research materials.  
Spills and food stains cause rapid deterioration of paper materials, resulting in their
loss and significant additional costs to the library for their replacement.  An even
more serious problem is that food and drink attracts insects and other creatures
that infest the books and periodicals and damage paper and glue.  
<P>
The College has gone to considerable effort and expense to provide a library
environment that is not only aesthetically pleasing, but also provides optimum
conditions of temperature and humidity for preservation of resources.  We need
the assistance of all patrons and staff to help keep the the library in top condition.
<P>
<HR>
