<TITLE>STUDENT GOVDOC TECHNOLOGY JOBS</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY>

<H2>OPENINGS AVAILABLE FOR GOVERNMENT PUBLICATIONS STUDENT TECHNOLOGY ASSISTANT DURING 1995-96 ACADEMIC YEAR</H2>

<H3>Job Description:</H3>

Support operation of Government Publications electronic media collection
(CD-ROM, floppy discs, departmental computers, public workstations) as directed
by the Government Publications Librarian.  Typical duties may include (but are not
necessarily limited to):

<UL>
	<LI>analyzing new CD-ROM titles and other electronic media
	<LI>locating, downloading, formatting, and printing documentation for CD-ROM
	    titles
	<LI>loading specified CD-ROM titles and software onto workstations
	<LI>checking that electronic media is functioning properly
	<LI>processing and filing CD-ROMs
	<LI>maintaining the Library's <a href="/govdocs/list/THELIST.html">
	    Government Publications CD-ROM Web Resource</a>
	<LI>keeping electronic media section of the Student Handbook accurate
</UL>
<P>
Schedule: at least 8 hrs. per week
<P>
<H3>Essential Qualifications:</H3>  

<UL>
	<LI>must be thorough and show attention to detail
	<LI>must have ability to work independently and with other library
	    technology student workers
    <LI>must be able to work in a flexible environment and tolerate
        interruptions
	<LI>must have patience and poise in trouble-shooting situations
</UL>

<H3>Other Qualifications:</H3>  

<UL>
	<LI>previous DOS experience required; interest or experience in Macintosh
	    also desirable
    <LI>preference given to those with CD-ROM and/or WINDOWS experience
    <LI>preference given to those with previous experience using Internet
        tools such as:
        
    <UL>
	    <LI>e-mail
	    <LI>telnet
	    <LI>gopher
	    <LI>ftp
	    <LI>wais
	    <LI>World Wide Web
	    <LI>statistical software packages
    </UL>
<P>         
	<LI>preference given to those with HTML experience or interest in learning HTML
	<LI>interest in statistical data helpful
</UL>


<H3>How to Apply:</H3>

Interested applicants should contact:

<UL>
	<LI><A HREF="/staff/carolyn/carolyn.html">Carolyn Sanford</A>,
	    Government Publications & Instruction Librarian<br>
	<LI>Library #466<br>
	<LI>x4266<br>
	<LI>CSANFORD<br>
</UL>
