</ul>

<H3>Selected Web Links for Classics</H3>
<DL>
<DT><A HREF="/studentworkers/josh/classics.html">Josh Mitchell's Classics Page</A>
<DD>Josh, a '97 classics major, offers links to useful classics resources on the World Wide Web.
</DL
<P>
<H3>Newsgroup</H3>
<dl>
<dt><A href=news:sci.classics>Sci.Classics</a><Br>
<dd>There's always something new (or perhaps ancient!) and different in this group.  Discussion topics range from discussions of grammar to how to find true-type Greek fonts for your Mac.  A must see for a classicist. <P><P>
</DL>
<P>
<HR>
<H2>Selected Paper Resources for Classics</H2>
<P>
This list is intended to introduce you to some of the paper materials we have on classics.  
It is not a complete list, but merely a sampling.  All items listed below are located in the Reference
Collection on Level 4 unless otherwise noted.  Please don't hesitate to ask a librarian if your aren't
finding what you need here.
<P>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="#ency">Encyclopedias, Dictionaries, and Guides</A>
<LI><A HREF="#biblio">Bibliographies</A>
<LI><A HREF="#myth">Mythology</A>
<LI><A HREF="#peop">People</A>
<LI><A HREF="#place">Places</A>
<LI><A HREF="#lit">Literature</A>
<LI><A HREF="#in-ab">Indexes and Abstracts
<LI><A HREF="#perio">Annuals and Periodicals</A>
</UL>


<HR ALIGN="center" WIDTH=50%>
<P>
<!--  ################ Dictionaries, Encyclopedias, and Guides.   -->
<a name="ency">
<h3>Background Sources - Encyclopedias, Dictionaries, and Guides</h3>

Use these sources at the beginning of your research to get an overview of a topic or to identify 
synonyms or related terms that will apply to your topic.  Later, return to these sources to clarify 
concepts or define new vocabulary.

<DL>

<DT><kbd>PN 6080 .A67 1984</kbd><br>
compiled by Thomas Benfield Harbottle. <strong>Anthology of Classical Quotations</strong>. 1984.
<DD>*** comments ***

<P>

<DT><kbd>D 57 .A95</kbd><br>
<strong>Cambridge Ancient History</strong>. 3rd ed.
<DD>Chapters individually written by experts. Extensive bibliographies at the back of each volume.

<P>

<DT><kbd>PN 6080 .K5</kbd><br>
King, William Francis Henry. <strong>Classical and Foreign Quotations</strong>. [1958?]
<DD>*** comments ***

<P>

<DT><kbd>PR 508.C68 S63 1984</kbd><br>
Smith, Eric. <strong>A Dictionary of Classical Reference in English Poetry</strong>. 1984.
<DD>*** comments ***

<P>

<DT><kbd>N 7760 .P68 1983</kbd><br>
Preston, Percy. <strong>A Dictionary of Pictorial Subjects from Classical Literature</strong>. 1983.
<DD>*** comments ***

<P>

<DT><kbd>PN 6080 .H2 1958</kbd><br>
Harbottle, Thomas Benfield. <strong>Dictionary of Quotations (Classical) With Author and Subject Indexes</strong>. [1958?]
<DD>*** comments ***

<P>

<DT><kbd>BL798 .A35 1996</kbd><br>
Adkins, Lesley. <strong>Dictionary of Roman Religion</strong>. 1996
<DD>*** comments ***

<P>

<DT><kbd>PN 6081 .S73 1967</kbd><br>
Stevenson, Burton Egbert. <strong>The Home Book of Quotations, Classical and Modern</strong>. 1967.
<DD>*** comments ***

<P>

<DT><kbd>DE 5 .A95</kbd><br>
Michael Avi Yonah and Israel Shatzman. <strong>Illustrated Encyclopaedia of the Classical World</strong>. 1975.
<DD>Provides definitions and brief biographical information. Covers artists, writers, philosophers, some chief 
archaeological sites, architecture, mythology, and more. Also provides bibliographical references, a chronology of 
colonies, and an index.

<P>

<DT><kbd>Main General DE 5 .P33 Suppl. Index</kbd><br>
Murphy, John P.<strong> Index to the supplements and suppl. volumes of Pauly-Wissowa's R.E. </strong>
<DD>Indexes the <i>Nachtr&auml;ge</i> and <i>berichtigunen</i> in vols. I-XXIV of the first series, vols. I-X of the 
second series, and supplementary vols. I-XIV of Pauly-Wissowa's Realencyklop&auml;die.

<P>

<DT><kbd>DE 59 .M25</kbd><br>
McGuire, Martin Rawson Patrick. <strong>Introduction to Classical Scholarship, a Syllabus and Bibliographical Guide</strong>. 1961.
<DD>*** comments ***

<P>
<DT><kbd>DF 220.5 .F48 1996</kbd><br>
Feuer, Bryan Avery. <STRONG>Mycenaean Civilization : a Research Guide</STRONG>. 1996
<DD>*** comments ***

<P>

<DT><kbd>DE 5 .N4</kbd><br>
Edited by Catherine B. Avery. <strong>The New Century Classical Handbook</strong>. 1962.
<DD>*** comments ***

<P>

<DT><kbd>DE 5 .O9 1970</kbd><br>
edited by N. G. L. Hammond and H. H. Scullard. <strong>The Oxford Classical Dictionary</strong>. 1970.
<DD>For quick identification of topics, arranged in alphabetical dictionary format. Contains bibliographical 
references for further reading.

<P>

<DT><kbd>Main General DE 5 .P33</kbd><br>
Pauly, August Friedrich von. and Georg Wissowa. <strong>Paulys Realencyclopadie der classischen Alterumswissenschaft</strong>.
<DD>Encyclopedia published over almost one hundred years in 24 original volumes, a second series of ten volumes, 
followed by a series of supplements. Contains long signed articles (in German) written by specialists with extensive 
bibliographies. First 23 volumes of the original series are indexed in back of vol. 23. For further indexes see the 
index supplement compiled by John Murphy (above).

<P>

<DT><kbd>CB 9 .P46 1993</kbd><br>
edited by Arthur Cotterell. <strong>The Penguin Encyclopedia of Classical Civilizations</strong>. 1993.
<DD>*** comments ***

<P>

<DT><kbd>PA 191 .W4</kbd><br>
Wedeck, Harry Ezekiel. <strong>Short Dictionary of Classical Word Origins</strong>. 1957.
<DD>*** comments ***

<P>

</DL>

<HR ALIGN="center" WIDTH=50%>
<P>
<!-- ###############Bibliographies  -->
<a name="biblio">
<h3>Bibliographies</h3>

Bibliographies are lists of materials on a particular topic.  They should save you time because the author has done
the tedious work of searching catalogs and indexes to find information on the topic. Many bibliographies also contain 
evaluations of the works that they mention.  Listed here are several general titles, but note that we have
bibliographies soley on individual topics as well. (Try a keyword search on Muse to find some.  For example,
type: <STRONG><KBD>homer bibliography</KBD></STRONG> to find some bibliographies on homer.)  

<P>

<DL>

<DT><kbd>PA 29 .M35</kbd><br>
Jules Marouzeau. <strong>L'Annee Philologique : Bibliographie Critique et Analytique de l'Antiquite Greco-Latine</strong>. 1924- .
<DD>*** coments ***

<P>

<DT><kbd>N 5610 .C68</kbd><br>
Coulson, William D. E. <strong>An Annotated Bibliography of Greek and Roman Art, Architecture, and Archaeology</strong>. 1975.
<DD>*** comments ***

<P>

<DT><kbd>PR 561 .N65 1989</kbd><br>
Nokes, David. <strong>An Annotated Critical Bibliography of Augustan Poetry</strong>. 1989.
<DD>*** comments ***

<P>

<DT><kbd>PA 29 .T48</kbd><br>
Thompson, Lawrence Sidney. <strong>A Bibliography of American Doctoral Dissertations in Classical Studies and Related Fields</strong>. 1968.
<DD>*** comments ***

<P>

<DT><kbd>PA 6825 .P44 1969</kbd><br>
Peeters, Felix. <strong>A Bibliography of Vergil</strong>. 1969.
<DD>*** comments ***

<P>

<DT><kbd>PA 3022.E6 S55 1991</kbd><br>
Sienkewicz, Thomas J. <strong>The Classical Epic : an Annotated Bibliography</strong>. 1991.
<DD>*** comments ***

<P>

<DT><kbd>PA 3024 .F67 1989</kbd><br>
Forman, Robert J. <strong>Classical Greek and Roman Drama : an Annotated Bibliography</strong>. 1989.
<DD>*** comments ***

<P>

<DT><kbd>PA 3017.9 .S6</kbd><br>
Smith, F. Seymour. <strong>The Classics in Translation, an Annotated Guide to the Best Translations of the Greek and Latin Classics into English</strong>. 1930.
<DD>*** comments ***

<P>

<DT><kbd>DE 59 .H34 1986</kbd><br>
Halton, Thomas Patrick. <strong>Classical Scholarship : an Annotated Bibliography</strong>. 1986.
<DD>Excellent source for references to citations on all aspects of classical studies. Entries contain critical 
annotations and references to reviews. Skim table of contents for arrangement of topics. One helpful chapter lists 
works about individual authors.

<P>

<DT><kbd>PA 3131 .C53</kbd><br>
by Walter Donlan. <strong>The Classical World Bibliography of Greek Drama and Poetry</strong>. 1977.
<DD>*** comments ***

<P>

<DT><kbd>PA 6003 .C53</kbd><br>
by Walter Donlan. <strong>The Classical World Bibliography of Roman Drama and Poetry</strong>. 1977.
<DD>*** comments ***

<P>

<DT><kbd>PA 6825 .C53</kbd><br>
Walter Donlan. <strong>The Classical World Bibliography of Vergil</strong>. 1978.
<DD>*** comments ***

<P>

<DT><kbd>B 171 .C58 1977</kbd><br>
Walter Donlan. <strong>The Classical World Bibliography of Philosophy, Religion, and Rhetoric</strong>. 1977.
<DD>*** comments ***

<P>

<DT><kbd>DE 8 .C58</kbd><br>
Walter Donlan. <strong>The Classical World Bibliography of Greek and Roman History</strong>. 1977.
<DD>Articles on Greek and Roman historians. Includes bibliographical references.

<P>

<DT><kbd>Folio D 1 .C65</kbd><br>
<strong>Combined Retrospective Index Set to Journals in History, 1838-1974</strong>.
<DD>Use headings, "Ancient history" or "Rome, Ancient" or "Greece, Ancient"  or others of your choice for access to 
articles published between 1838-1974.

<P>

<DT><kbd>N 5610 .C68 1987</kbd><br>
William D.E. Coulson, Patricia N. Freiert. <strong>Greek and Roman Art, Architecture, and Archaeology : An Annotated Bibliography</strong>. 1987.
<DD>*** comments ***

<P>

<DT><kbd>D 57 .B413</kbd><br>
Bengtson, Hermann. <strong>Introduction to Ancient History</strong>. 1970.
<DD>Essays with bibliographies on general areas of ancient history.
 </DL>


<HR ALIGN="center" WIDTH=50%>
<P>
<!-- ############### Mythology  -->
<a name="myth">
<h3>Mythology</h3>

<DL>

<DT><kbd>BL 311 .B82</kbd><br>
Bulfinch, Thomas. <strong>Bulfinch's Mythology</strong>. [1970]
<DD>Compendium of stories of the myths of the Greek and Roman gods. Key words and terms are indexed for locating 
myths mentioning people, places, and events.

<P>

<DT><kbd>NX 650.M9 M38</kbd><br>
Mayerson, Philip. <strong>Classical Mythology in Literature, Art, and Music</strong>. 1971.
<DD>Essays on myths with excerpts from literature and illustrated with examples of art depicting mythological 
characters.

<P>

<DT><kbd>BL 715 .G713 1986</kbd><br>
Grimal, Pierre. <strong>The Dictionary of Classical Mythology</strong>. 1986.
<DD>Brief entries on names, places and terms found in Greek and Roman myths; contains a genealogy of the gods. Also a 
bibliography of ancient authors who refer to classical myths.

<P>

<DT><kbd>BL 715 .B44 1982</kbd><br>
Bell, Robert E. <strong>Dictionary of Classical Mythology, Symbols, Attributes, & Associations</strong>. 1982.
<DD>*** comments ***

<P>

<DT><kbd>BL 715 .S7 1986b</kbd><br>
Stapleton, Michael. <strong>Dictionary of Greek and Roman Mythology</strong>. 1986.
<DD>*** comments ***

<P>

<DT><kbd>BL 25 .M8 v.1</kbd><br>
Fox, William Sherwood. <strong>Greek and Roman [Mythology]</strong>. 1916.
<DD>*** comments ***

<P>

<DT><kbd>N 7760 .L49 1981</kbd><br>
Hans Christoph Ackermann, Jean-Robert Gisler. <strong>Lexicon Iconographicum Mythologiae Classicae</strong>. 1981.
<DD>*** comments ***

<P>

<DT><kbd>NX 650.M9 R45 1993</kbd><br>
Reid, Jane Davidson. <strong>The Oxford Guide to Classical Mythology in the Arts, 1300-1990s</strong>. 1993.
<DD>*** comments ***

<P>

<DT><kbd>BL 715 .B445 1991</kbd><br>
Robert E. Bell. <strong>Women of Classical Mythology : a Biographical Dictionary</strong>. 1991.
<DD>Alphabetical arrangement of women figues in mythology. Some entries have references to classical texts. There is 
also an index to men of classical mythology that refers one to the entries on women in their lives.


</DL>

<HR ALIGN="center" WIDTH=50%>
<P>
<!-- ############### People  -->
<a name="peop">
<h3>People</h3>

<DL>

<DT><kbd>PA 3002 .A5 1982</kbd><br>
T. James Luce, editor-in-chief. <strong>Ancient writers : Greece and Rome</strong> 1982.
<DD>Two volumes of essays on noteworthy authors, historians, philosophers, and poets. Index is in 
back of vol. 2.

<P>

<DT><kbd>PA 83 .C58 1990</kbd><br>
edited by Ward W. Briggs and William M. Calder III. <strong>Classical Scholarship : a Biographical Encyclopedia</strong>. 1990.
<DD>*** comments ***

<P>

<DT><kbd>DF 208 .W48 1982</kbd><br> 1982.
Bowder, Diana, ed. <strong>Who Was Who in the Greek World</strong>.
<DD>In addition to providing short biographies, this source has a chronological outline of events of the Greek works, 
a glossary of Greek terms, and citations to further readings.

<P>

<DT><kbd>DG 203 .W46</kbd><br>
Bowder, Diana, ed. <strong>Who Was Who in the Roman World 753 BC - AD 476</strong>. 1980.
<DD>*** comments ***

<P>

<DT><kbd>HQ 1127 .G66M</kbd><br>
Goodwater, Leanna. <strong>Women in Antiquity</strong>. 1975.
<DD>Annotated bibliography arranged by when works were written (ancient or modern sources).

</DL>

<HR ALIGN="center" WIDTH=50%>
<P>
<!-- ############### Places  -->
<a name="place">
<h3>Places</h3>

<DL>

<DT><kbd>G 1033 .G64 1974</kbd><br>
Grant, Michael. <strong>Ancient History Atlas</strong>. 1974.
<DD>Look here for maps of different time periods. Points out information such as centers of trade or locations of 
important historical events.

<P>

<DT><kbd>G 1046.E15 A8 1976</kbd><br>
edited by M. I. Finley. <strong>Atlas of Classical Archaeology</strong>. 1977.
<DD>*** comments ***

<P>

<DT><kbd>G 1033 .A833 1985</kbd><br>
edited by Richard J.A. Talbert. <strong>Atlas of Classical History</strong>. 1985.
<DD>Maps and explanatory texts on both individual cities and entire regions ranging from the Bronze Age to 
Constantine.

<P>

<DT><kbd>DE 25 .G72 1986</kbd><br>
Grant, Michael. <strong>A Guide to the Ancient World : a Dictionary of Classical Place Names</strong>. 1986.
<DD>Short descriptive entries on geographical names. Contains some maps and bibliographical references.

<P>

<DT><kbd>DE 25 .N48</kbd><br>
Edited by Catherine B. Avery. <strong>The New Century Handbook of Classical Geography</strong>. 1972.
<DD>*** comments ***

<P>

<DT><kbd>DG 68 .R5 1992</kbd><br>
Richardson, Lawrence. <strong>A New Topographical Dictionary of Ancient Rome</strong>. 1992.
<DD>*** comments ***

<P>

<DT><kbd>Folio CB 311 .P44 1983</kbd><br>
<strong>Peoples and Places of the Past: the National Geographic Illustrated Cultural Atlas of the Ancient World</strong>. 1983.
<DD>Like many sources in this section, this work has more than just maps. For general interest.

<P>

<DT><kbd>DE 59 .P7</kbd><br>
Richard Stillwell, editor. <strong>The Princeton Encyclopedia of Classical Sites</strong>. 1976.
<DD>Sites entered under ancient geographical name. Contains historical notes on site and description of excavation 
performed.

<P>

<DT><kbd>Folio DF 77 .L43</kbd><br>
Levi, Peter. <strong>Atlas of the Greek World</strong>. 1980.
<DD>More than an atlas. Richly illustrated source; includes supplemental essays along with pictures on many topics of 
general interest. Chronological table of political, artistic and literary events.

<P>

<DT><kbd>Folio DG 77 .C597 1982</kbd><br>
Cornell, Tim and Matthews, John. <strong>Atlas of the Roman World</strong>. 1982.
<DD>Arranged like <STRONG>Atlas of the Greek World</STRONG> described above. Great for browsing.

</DL>

<HR ALIGN="center" WIDTH=50%>
<P>
<!-- ############### Literature  -->
<a name="lit">
<h3>Literature</h3>

<DL>

<DT><kbd>DE 5 .P36 1896</kbd><br>
edited by Harry Thurston Peck, M. A., Ph. D. <strong>Harper's Dictionary of Classical Literature and Antiquities</strong>. 1896.
<DD>*** comments ***

<P>

<DT><kbd>PA 31 .H69 1989</kbd><br>
edited by M.C. Howatson. <strong>The Oxford Companion to Classical Literature</strong>. 1989.
<DD>Dictionary of authors, characters and literary terms.

</DL>

<HR ALIGN="center" WIDTH=50%>
<P>
<!-- ############### Indexes and Abstracts  -->
<a name="in-ab">
<h3>Indexes and Abstracts</h3>
<P>
Turn to indexes and abstracts to find more information on your topic.   If you want to know whether 
Carleton subscribes to a particular journal, perform a <STRONG><KBD>T > TITLE</KBD></STRONG> search in Muse 
using the exact title of the journal you're looking for.
<P>

<DL>

<DT><kbd>PA 29 .M53</kbd><br>
<strong>L'Ann&eacute;e Philologique: bibliographie critique et analytique de l'antiquit&eacute; greco-latine</strong>.
<DD>Although this is a French title, it does index English articles and books. Includes several helpful indexes: 
index to ancient names, ancient places, modern names, authors, etc. Some of the entries contain brief 
annotations--(English articles have English annotations).

<P>

<DT><kbd>AI 3 .S942</kbd><br>
<strong>British Humanities Index</strong>.
<DD>*** comments ***

</DL>

<!-- ###############put periodicals here  -->
<HR ALIGN="center" WIDTH=50%>
<P>
<a name="perio">
<h3>Annuals and Periodicals</h3>

<DL>

<DT><kbd>Main General DF 10 .J8</kbd><br>
<strong>Journal of Hellenic Studies.</strong> (1882-  ).
<DD>Contains scholarly articles and book reviews. Companion publication is Archaeological Reports, an annual source 
covering excavations during the past year. This journal is indexed in <STRONG>L'Ann&eacute;e Philologique</STRONG>.

<P>

<DT><kbd>Main General DF 11 .E6</kbd><br>
<strong>Annual of the British School of Athens.</strong> (1894-  ).
<DD>Indexed in <STRONG>L'Ann&eacute;e Philologique</STRONG>.

<P>

<DT><kbd>Main General DG 11 .J7</kbd><br>
<strong>The Journal of Roman Studies.</strong> (1911-  ).
<DD>Indexed in <STRONG>L'Ann&eacute;e Philologique</STRONG>.

</DL>

To identify which classics-related periodicals are owned by the Gould Library, perform the following steps on
Muse:
<P>
<OL>
<LI><STRONG><KBD>N > NUMBERS</KBD></STRONG>
<LI><STRONG><KBD>C > CALL numbers (Library of Congress)</KBD></STRONG> (use <STRONG><KBD>PER</KBD></STRONG>)
<LI><STRONG><KBD>L > LIMIT this Search</KBD></STRONG>
<LI><STRONG><KBD>S > Words in the SUBJECT</KBD></STRONG>
<LI>(use <STRONG><KBD>classic*</KBD></STRONG>)
<LI><STRONG><KBD>F > Find items with above limits</KBD></STRONG>
</OL>
<P>



</DL>	
