<P>
<HR>
<H2>Selected Paper Resources for French</H2>
<P>
This list is intended to introduce you to some of the reference materials we have on French literature and literary
criticisms.  It is not a complete list, but merely a sampling.  Please don't hesitate to ask a librarian if your aren't
finding what you need here.
<P>
<ul>
<li><a href="#ency">Encyclopedias, Dictionaries, and Guides</a>
<li><a href="#biblio">Bibliographies</a>
<li><a href="#peop">People</a>
<li><a href="#perio">Periodicals</a>
</ul>

<HR ALIGN="center" WIDTH=50%>
<P>
<!--  ################ Dictionaries, Encyclopedias, and Guides.   -->
<a name="ency">
<h3>Background Sources - Encyclopedias, Dictionaries, and Guides</h3>

Use these sources at the beginning of your research to get an overview of a topic or to identify 
synonyms or related terms that will apply to your topic.  Later, return to these sources to clarify 
concepts or define new vocabulary.

<DL>

<DT><kbd>PQ 41 .C6 1976</kbd><br>
edited by Joyce M. H. Reid. <strong>The Concise Oxford Dictionary of French Literature</strong>. 1976.
<DD>*** coments ***

<P>

<DT><kbd>PQ 41 .D65 1986</kbd><br>
Dolbow, Sandra W. <strong>Dictionary of Modern French Literature : From the Age of Reason Through Realism</strong>. 1986.
<DD>Nearly 300 biographical entries, literary synopses, and summaries of literary movements.  Many entries contain bibliographies.

<P>

<DT><kbd>PQ 305 .B54 1963</kbd><br>
Boisdeffre, Pierre de. <strong>Dictionnaire de Litterature Contemporaine</strong>. 1963.
<DD>The first part of this dictionary has nine essays on French lit of the 20th century.  The second and largest part contains biographical articles on authors with bibliographical references and illustrations.

<P>

<DT><kbd>PQ 41 .B4 1984</kbd><br>
Beaumarchais, Jean-Pierre de. <strong>Dictionnaire des Litteratures de Langue Francaise</strong>. 1984- .
<DD>This 3-volume work is useful for background information on authors and select works.  Famous individual works are entered within the author entry.  Under important authors, chronologies are given showing current events of author's lifetime.

<P>

<DT><kbd>PQ 41 .B42 1994</kbd><br>
Beaumarchais, Jean-Pierre de. <strong>Dictionnaire des Oeuvres litteraires de Langue Francaise</strong>. 1994- .
<DD>4 volumes.

<P>

<DT><kbd>DC 33.7 .F726 1995</kbd><br>
edited by Catherine Savage Brosman. <strong>French Culture, 1900-1975</strong>. 1995.
<DD>*** coments ***

<P>

<DT><kbd>PC 4640's</kbd><br>
<strong>French-English  Dictionaries</strong> many dates.
<DD>French-English dictionaries are found in the call number range <KBD>PC 4640</KBD> both in the reference section on the fourth floor and older editions in the general collection.

<P>

<DT><kbd>PQ 41 .L48 1992</kbd><br>
Levi, Anthony. <strong>Guide to French Literature</strong>. 1992-1994.
<DD>*** coments ***

<P>

<DT><kbd>PQ 103 .B34</kbd><br>
Baker, Robert K. <strong>Introduction to Library Research in French Literature</strong> 1978.
<DD>A thorough handbook for doing library research in French Lit.  Contains an annotated bibliography of useful reference books.  Helpful hints on choosing a research topic.

<P>

<DT><kbd>PQ 119 .N48 1989</kbd><br>
edited by Denis Hollier. <strong>A New History of French Literature</strong>. 1989.
<DD>Book of essays arranged by date describing the historical significance of an event or literary movement prominant in a specific year.  Articles are written by specialists and signed.  Use index  to find information about an author.  Entries contain bibliographies for further reading.

<P>

<DT><kbd>PQ 41 .N48 1995</kbd><br>
edited by Peter France. <strong>The New Oxford Companion to Literature in French</strong>. 1995.
<DD>An excellent one volume dictionary of authors, titles, critics, places and literary terms.

<P>

<DT><kbd>PQ 41 .H3</kbd><br>
Harvey, Paul, Sir. <strong>The Oxford Companion to French Literature</strong>. 1959.
<DD>Excellent one volume dictionary of authors, titles, critics, places and literary terms.

<P>

<DT><kbd>PR 9798 .Z4</kbd><br>
Zell, Hans M. <strong>A Reader's Guide to African Literature</strong>. 1971.
<DD>*** coments ***

<P>

<DT><kbd>PN 41 .E4</kbd><br>
Elkhadem, Saad. <strong>The York Dictionary of English-French-German-Spanish Literary Terms and Their Origin</strong>. 1976.
<DD>*** coments ***

<P>

</DL>

<HR ALIGN="center" WIDTH=50%>
<P>
<!-- ###############Bibliographies  -->
<a name="biblio">
<h3>Bibliographies</h3>

Bibliographies are lists of materials on a particular topic.  They should save you time because the author has done
the tedious work of searching catalogs and indexes to find information on the topic. Many bibliographies also contain 
evaluations of the works that they mention.  Listed here are several general titles, but note that we have
bibliographies soley on individual authors as well. (Try a keyword search on Muse to find some.  For example,
type: <STRONG><KBD>valery bibliography</KBD></STRONG> to find some bibliographies on Paul Valery.)  

<DL>

<DT><kbd>PQ 35 .K55</kbd><br>
begr&uuml;ndet von Otto Klapp. <strong>Bibliographie der Franz&ouml;sischen Literaturwissenschaft</strong>. 1960- .
<DD>Don't be put off by the German title.  Indexes and chapter headings are in French.  This source indexes articles, books and dissertations on French literature.  Arrangement is chronological, from the Middle Ages to the present.  Start with the subject entry in the back of the book which will refer you by entry number to the full citations in the main text.

<P>

<DT><kbd>PQ 265 .C48</kbd><br>
Cioranescu, Alexandre. <strong>Bibliographie de la Litterature Francaise du Dix-Huitieme Siecle</strong>. 1969.
<DD>Look for general subjects in volume one part one and authors beginning in vol. 1 part two continuing through vol. 3.

<P>

<DT><kbd>PQ 239 .C5</kbd><br>
Cioranescu, Alexandre. <strong>Bibliographie de la Litterature Francaise du Seizieme Siecle. Collaboration et pref. de V.-L. Saulnier</strong>. 1959.
