        </UL>
    </DL>
</DD>
<DT>WEEK 9: <U>Dark Soul: Hawthorne and Radical Communitarianism</U> </DT>
<DD><DL>
    <DT>Mon., Mar. 3: <U>Blithedale</U> </DT>
    <DD><UL>
        <LI><IMG SRC="/images/greenball.gif" ALT="*" HIEGHT="14" WIDTH="14"> Nathaniel Hawthorne,
            <U>Blithedale Romance</U> (1852), ed. William E. Cain (1996), read one-third
            of Part One, about 70 pages. Also, read at least one primary document in
            Part Two that has not been assigned in the syllabus. Part Two has four
            sections which give the cultural context of this novel.</LI>
        </UL>
    <DT>Wed., Mar. 5: <U>Blithedale</U> </DT>
    <DD><UL>
        <LI><IMG SRC="/images/greenball.gif" ALT="*" HIEGHT="14" WIDTH="14"> Hawthorne, read
            the second third of Part One, about 70 pages. Also read at least one primary
            document in Part Two that has not been assigned in the syllabus.</LI>
        </UL>
    <DT>Fri., Mar. 7: <U>Blithedale</U> </DT>
    <DD><UL>
        <LI><IMG SRC="/images/greenball.gif" ALT="*" HIEGHT="14" WIDTH="14"> Hawthorne, finish
            the novel. Also read at least one primary document in Part Two that has
            not been assigned in the course.</LI>
        </UL>
    </DL>
