<H2>Selected Paper Resources for Music Research</H2>
<P>
This list is intended to introduce you to some of the paper materials we have on music.  
It is not a complete list, but merely a sampling.  All items listed below are located in the Reference
Collection on Level 4 unless otherwise noted.  Please don't hesitate to ask a librarian if your aren't
finding what you need here.
<P>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="#ency">Encyclopedias, Dictionaries, and Guides</A>
<LI><A HREF="#biblio">Bibliographies</A>
<LI><A HREF="#peop">People</A>
<LI><A HREF="#lit">Literature</A>
<LI><A HREF="#in-ab">Indexes and Abstracts
<LI><A HREF="#perio">Annuals and Periodicals</A>
</UL>


<HR ALIGN="center" WIDTH=50%>
<P>
<!--  ################ Dictionaries, Encyclopedias, and Guides.   -->
<a name="ency">
<h3>Background Sources - Encyclopedias, Dictionaries, and Guides</h3>

Use these sources at the beginning of your research to get an overview of a topic or to identify 
synonyms or related terms that will apply to your topic.  Later, return to these sources to clarify 
concepts or define new vocabulary.

<DL>
<P>

<DT><kbd>ML 156.4.J3 B66 1995</kbd><br>
ed. Kernfeld, Barry.<strong>The Blackwell Guide to Recorded Jazz</strong>. 1995.
<DD>*** comments ***

<P>

<DT><kbd>ML 156.2 .D63 1969</kbd><br>
Godrich, John. <strong>Blues & Gospel Records</strong>. 1969.
<DD>*** comments ***

<P>

<DT><kbd>ML 102.P66 S5 1982</kbd>
Shaw, Arnold. <strong>Dictionary of American Pop/Rock</strong>. 1982.
<DD>*** comments ***

<P>

<DT><kbd>ML 105 .F36</kbd><br>
Feather, Leonard G. and Gitler, Ira <strong>The Encyclopedia of Jazz in the Seventies</strong>. 1976.
<DD>*** comments ***

<P>

<DT><kbd>ML 105 .F35</kbd><br>
Feather, Leonard G. <strong>The Encyclopedia of Jazz in the Sixties</strong>. 1966.
<DD>*** comments ***

<P>

<DT><kbd>ML 102.P66 T9 1985</kbd><br>
Tyler, Don. <strong>Hit Parade : An Encyclopedia of the Top Songs of the Jazz, Depression, Swing, and Sing Eras</strong>. 1985.
<DD>*** comments ***

<P>

<DT><kbd>ML 102.J3 C34</kbd><br>
Case, Brian and Britt, Stan. <strong>The Illustrated Encyclopedia of Jazz</strong>. 1978.
<DD>*** comments ***

<P>

<DT><kbd>ML 156.4.J3 T73</kbd><br>
Tudor, Dean and Nancy. <strong>Jazz</strong>. 1979.
<DD>*** comments ***

<P>

<DT><kbd>ML 128.J3 M33 1995</kbd><br>
Meadows, Eddie S. <strong>Jazz Research and Performance Materials</strong>. 1995.
<DD>*** comments ***

<P>

<DT><kbd>ML 102.J3 C32 1988</kbd><br>
Carr, Ian, et. al. <strong>Jazz : the Essential Companion</strong>. 1988.
<DD>*** comments ***

<P>

<DT><kbd>ML 3561.J3 F39</kbd><br>
Feather, Leonard G. <strong>The New Edition of the Encyclopedia of Jazz</strong>. 1960.
<DD>*** comments ***

<P>

<DT><kbd>ML 102.J3 N48 1988</kbd><br>
ed. Kernfeld, Barry. <strong>The New Grove Dictionary of Jazz</strong>. 1988.
<DD>*** comments ***

<P>

<DT><kbd>ML 156.4.J3 C67 1992</kbd><br>
Cook, Richard, and Morton, Brian. <strong>The Penguin Guide to Jazz on CD, LP, and Cassette</strong>. 1992.
<DD>*** comments ***

</DL>

