<A NAME="in-ab"><H3>Indexes and Abstracts</H3></A>

<DL>
<DT><KBD>GovDocRef JX 1417 .A45</KBD><BR>
<STRONG>American Foreign Policy Index</STRONG>, (CIS) 1993- .
<DD>Detailed indexing of publications from the U.S. government.

<P>

<DT><KBD><A HREF="/electronic/cd-rom/cd-rom.html#ethnic">CD-ROM</A></KBD><BR>
<STRONG>Ethnic News Watch</STRONG>, 1990.
<DD>Index and full text database articles from ethnic and minority publications published in the U.S.; many in Spanish.

<P>

<DT><KBD>Electronic/Networked</KBD><BR>
<STRONG><A HREF="/electronic/online/firstsearch.html">FirstSearch</A></STRONG>
<DD>FirstSearch is an electronic source that provides access to about 40
    databases including Articles First, Economic Literature, Newspaper
    Abstracts, PAIS Decade, and Periodicals Abstracts. The password is changed
    irregularly and can be obtained at the Information Desk , the Reference
    Desk, or on the Library's web page. Access is available on MUSE/Connect to
    Another Resource/ FirstSearch or on the VAX at the $ prompt, type  
	<KBD>telnet fscat.oclc.org</KBD>; or, on the Librarys web page
	<A HREF="http://www.library.carleton.edu/electronic/online/index.html"><KBD>http://www.library.carleton.edu/electronic/online/index.html</KBD></A>.

<P>

<DT><KBD>Ref JA 26 .I5</KBD><BR>
<STRONG>International Political Science Abstracts</STRONG>, 1970- .
<DD>Abstracts of Political Science journal articles.

<P>

<DT><KBD><A HREF="/electronic/cd-rom/cd-rom.html#pais">CD-ROM</A> (1972-  ) &amp;  Ref H 1 .P8 (1915-  ) &amp; <A HREF="/electronic/online/firstsearch.html">FirstSearch</A> (most recent 10 yrs.)</KBD><BR>
<STRONG>PAIS: Public Affairs Information Service/ International</STRONG>, 1915 - .
<DD>Subject index to periodical articles, books, reports, governmental and intergovernmental publications on issues of public policy around the world.

<P>

<DT><KBD><A HREF="/electronic/cd-rom/cd-rom.html#ssci">CD-ROM</A></KBD><BR>
<STRONG>SSCI: Social Science Citation Index</STRONG>, 1986- .
<DD>Huge interdisciplinary index; keyword searching; citation searching; includes book reviews.

<P>

<DT><KBD>Electronic/Networked</KBD><BR>
<STRONG><A HREF="/electronic/online/uncover.html">UnCover</A></STRONG>
<DD>UnCOVER is an electronic index to articles from over 14,000 English language
    periodicals.  This service covers 1988 to date.  Access is available on
    MUSE/ other Resources/ UnCOVER; or on the VAX at the $ prompt, type
    <KBD>telnet database.carl.org</KBD>, then choose UnCOVER; or web access:
	<A HREF="http://www.library.carleton.edu/electronic/online/index.html"><KBD>http://www.library.carleton.edu/electronic/online/index.html</KBD></A>.

<P>

<DT><KBD>CD-ROM</KBD><BR>
<STRONG>USFAC/U.S. Foreign Affairs</STRONG>, 1990.
<DD>Provides full-text access to official transcripts and country info released by the State Dept.

<P>

<DT><KBD>online catalog</KBD><BR>
<STRONG>Wilson Journal Citation Indexes</STRONG>, 1991 - .
<DD>On Muse! Seven periodical indexes.  At the Muse Main Menu screen select <KBD>J &gt; Wilson JOURNAL Citation Indexes</KBD> and search using Muse commands.

<P>

<DT><KBD>Ref HQ 1111 .W65</KBD><BR>
<STRONG>Women Studies Abstracts</STRONG>, 1989 - .
<DD>Indexes scholarly and popular publications not covered by more mainstream indexes.

<P>

<DT><KBD>Ref HQ 1180 .W683</KBD><BR>
<STRONG>Women Studies Index</STRONG>, 1989 - .
<DD>Comprehensive indexing of eighty-two scholarly journals.
</DL>




<A NAME="area"><H3>Area Studies</H3></A>

<DL>
<DT><KBD>Gov Doc D 101.22: 550</KBD><BR>
<STRONG>Country Studies &amp; Background Notes</STRONG>.
<DD>Compiled by the Foreign Area Studies section of The American University and
    published by the Dept. of Defense; covers all aspects of a country; includes
    a bibliography; revisions will appear on USFAC  CD-ROM. 

<P>

<DT><KBD><A HREF="/electronic/cd-rom/cd-rom.html#fbis">CD-ROM</A></KBD><BR>
<STRONG>FBIS Index</STRONG>. 1991- 1996.<BR>
<KBD>Gov Doc Fiche PREX 7.10:</KBD><BR>
<STRONG>FBIS (Foreign Broadcast Information Service)</STRONG>.<BR>
<KBD>Gov Doc Fiche PREX 7.12:</KBD> &amp; <KBD>7.13:</KBD><BR>
<STRONG>JPRS (Joint Publications Reference Service)</STRONG>.
<DD>Microfiche collection of the full text translations of major broadcast media
    and major print media originating in countries around the world; CD-ROM
    index for FBIS, 1991 to date; fiche index for JPRS, 1978- .

<P>

<DT><KBD>Ref F 1408 .H23 &amp; <A HREF="http://www.library.carleton.edu/electronic/online/hla.html">http://www.library.carleton.edu/electronic/online/hla.html</A></KBD><BR>
<STRONG>Handbook of Latin American Studies</STRONG>. 1935- .
<DD>Critical annotations of books, articles, pamphlets, maps, documents; many in Spanish; the basic and most important index for this region; web access for 1990- 1993.

<P>

<DT><KBD>Ref Folio F 1408 .L3865 1992</KBD><BR>
Paula H. Covington, ed. <STRONG>Latin America and the Caribbean: a critical guide to research sources</STRONG>. 1992.
<DD>An interdisciplinary guide to reference and bibliographic sources on these regions.

<P>

<DT><KBD>Ref Folio F 1408 .L388 1990</KBD><BR>
R. A. McNeil and B. G. Valk., eds. <STRONG>Latin American Studies: a Basic Guide to Sources</STRONG>, 2nd edition revised. 1992.
<DD>Annotated listing of resources; arranged by subject; Carleton may not have some sources.
</DL>



<A NAME="topic"><H3>Topical Approach</H3></A>

<DL>
<DT><KBD>Ref HV6431 .M498 1993</KBD><BR>
Mickolus, Edward F. <STRONG>Terrorism, 1988-1991.</STRONG>. 1993.
<DD>A chronology of terrorism and a selectively annotated bibliography.

<P>

<DT><KBD>Ref F 2308 .W32 1990</KBD><BR>
Waddell, D. A. G. <STRONG>Venezuela</STRONG>. 1990.
<DD>Contains annotated entries on works dealing with economy, politics, religion, and culture.

<P>

<DT><KBD>Ref HQ 1870.9.B96 1986</KBD><BR>
<STRONG>Women in the Third World: a historical bibliography</STRONG>. 1986.
<DD>Arranged by broad geographical area; annotated.
</DL>



