<A NAME="othersource"><H3>Other Useful Sources</H3></A>

<DL>
<DT><KBD>Ref HV 6243 .A45 1996</KBD><BR>
<STRONG>Amnesty International Report, 1976, 1978- </STRONG> 1996.
<DD>Reports by country covering human rights information from January to December annually.

<P>

<DT><KBD>Ref J 9.5 .G37 1993</KBD><BR>
<STRONG>Citing Government Information Resources</STRONG>. rev. ed. 1993.
<DD>Guide to good citations.

<P>

<DT><KBD>Ref JL 1851 .A25  1989</KBD><BR>
<STRONG>The Dictionary of Contemporary Politics of South America</STRONG>. 1989.
<DD>Defines South American political organizations and political concepts.

<P>

<DT><KBD>Ref JA 61 .C66 1992</KBD><BR>
<STRONG>Encyclopedia of Government and Politics</STRONG>. 1992.
<DD>Discusses many facets of political theory and political institutions.

<P>

<DT><KBD>Ref JN 1 .E85  1996</KBD><BR>
<STRONG>The Europa Yearbook</STRONG>. 1959 - .
<DD>Current year in Reference; excellent current information on countries.

<P>

<DT><KBD>Ref JC 571 .H785 1992</KBD><BR>
<STRONG>Human Rights Watch World Report, 1992- .</STRONG>
<DD>Surveys the U.S. government's human rights policy in other countries and analyzes human rights development in those countries.

<P>

<DT><KBD>Ref JX 1226 .P55 1988</KBD><BR>
<STRONG>The International Relations Dictionary</STRONG>. 1988.
<DD>Guide to the technical language of international relations.

<P>

<DT><KBD>Ref F 1401 .L3476</KBD><BR>
<STRONG>Latin American and Caribbean Contemporary Record</STRONG>, 1981- .
<DD>Organized into 4 parts, subdivided by countries or topic; great source for current overview.

<P>

<DT><KBD>Ref DT 1 .A3</KBD><BR>
<STRONG>Africa contemporary record; annual survey and documents</STRONG>, 1974-1975,1977- .
<DD>Organized into 4 parts, subdivided by countries or topic; great source for current overview.

<P>

<DT>These <STRONG>newspapers</STRONG> are retained in the Library's collection; all are on microfilm in the Microforms Room:
<DD><DL>
    <DT><STRONG>Christian Science Monitor</STRONG>, 1960- .
    <DD><KBD>Ref AI 21 .C46</KBD> <STRONG>Index</STRONG>, 1960- .
    <DT><STRONG>The Times, London</STRONG>, 1790- .
    <DD><KBD>Ref AI 21 .T35</KBD> <STRONG>Index</STRONG>, 1790- .
    <DT><STRONG>New York Times</STRONG>, 1850- .
    <DD><KBD>Ref AI 21 .N44</KBD> <STRONG>Index</STRONG>, 1850- .
    <DT><STRONG>Philadelphia Inquirer</STRONG>, 1991- .
    <DD><STRONG>Index</STRONG>- See a librarian for access to the index on Dialog.
    <DT><STRONG>Wall Street Journal</STRONG>, 1958- .
    <DD><KBD>Ref HG 1 .W258</KBD> <STRONG>Index</STRONG>, 1958- .
    <DT><STRONG>Washington Post</STRONG>, 1979- .
    <DD><KBD>Ref AI 21 .W3</KBD> <STRONG>Index</STRONG>, 1979- .
    </DL>

<P>

<DT><KBD>Ref JA 61 .O95 1993</KBD><BR>
<STRONG>The Oxford Companion to Politics of the World</STRONG>. 1993.
<DD>Guide to international relations and national domestic politics throughout the world.

<P>

<DT><KBD>Ref JL 195 .P64 1982</KBD><BR>
<STRONG>Political Parties of the Americas</STRONG>. 1982.
<DD>Use this for overviews of major political happenings in a country and for descriptive paragraphs about parties.

<P>

<DT><KBD>Ref JA 51 .P64 vol.3 1995</KBD><BR>
<STRONG>Political Risk Yearbook</STRONG>. 1995.<BR>
Volume 3 - South America.
<DD>Forecasts risks in business and investment by country.

<P>

<DT><KBD>Ref Folio HA 935 .S79 Vol.31, Pts. 1 &amp; 2</KBD><BR>
Committee on Latin American Studies, UCLA. <STRONG>Statistical Abstract of Latin America</STRONG>.
<DD>Extensive statistical information arranged by subject.
</DL>
