<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">
<center><H2>Political Science 221 - Latin American Politics</H2></center>
<center><H4>Winter 1997, Prof. Margaret Mart&iacute;n</H4></center><br>

<H3>Muse - Online Catalog</H3>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.library.carleton.edu/muse/muse.html">About Muse</A>
<LI><A HREF="telnet://muse.library.carleton.edu">Jump Directly to Muse</A>
</UL><P>
To identify which political science periodicals are owned by the Gould Library,
perform the following steps on
Muse:
<P>
<OL>
<LI><STRONG><KBD>N &gt; NUMBERS</KBD></STRONG>
<LI><STRONG><KBD>C &gt; CALL numbers (Library of Congress)</KBD></STRONG> (use
<STRONG><KBD>PER</KBD></STRONG>)
<LI><STRONG><KBD>L &gt; LIMIT this Search</KBD></STRONG>
<LI><STRONG><KBD>S &gt; Words in the SUBJECT</KBD></STRONG>
<LI>(use <STRONG><KBD>politic* science</KBD></STRONG>)
<LI><STRONG><KBD>F &gt; Find items with above limits</KBD></STRONG>
</OL>

<HR>
<H3>Indexes and Abstracts</H3>
<DL>
<DT><KBD>GovDocRef JX 1417 .A45</KBD><BR>
<STRONG>American Foreign Policy Index</STRONG>, (CIS) 1993- .
<DD>Detailed indexing of publications from the U.S. government.

<P>

<DT><KBD><A HREF="/electronic/cd-rom/cd-rom.html#ethnic">CD-ROM</A></KBD><BR>
<STRONG>Ethnic News Watch</STRONG>, 1990.
<DD>Index and full text database articles from ethnic and minority publications published in the U.S.; many in Spanish.

<P>

<DT><KBD>Electronic/Networked</KBD><BR>
<STRONG><A HREF="/electronic/online/firstsearch.html">FirstSearch</A></STRONG>
<DD>FirstSearch is an electronic source that provides access to about 50 databases including Articles First, Economic Literature, Newspaper Abstracts, and Periodicals Abstracts.  You can reach this resource on MUSE /Other Resources /FirstSearch; or go to the library's web page. 

<P>

<DT><KBD><A HREF="http://www.library.carleton.edu/electronic/online/index.html">http://www.library.carleton.edu/electronic/online/index.html</A></KBD><BR>
<STRONG>HAPI, Hispanic American Periodicals Index.</STRONG>
<DD>Major index of over 200 Latin American scholarly jornals.

<P>

<DT><KBD>Ref JA 26 .I5</KBD><BR>
<STRONG>International Political Science Abstracts</STRONG>
<DD>Abstracts of Political Science journal articles.

<P>

<DT><KBD><A HREF="/electronic/cd-rom/cd-rom.html#pais">CD-ROM</A> (1972-  ) &amp;  Ref H 1 .P8 (1915-  ) &amp; <A HREF="/electronic/online/firstsearch.html">FirstSearch</A> (most recent 10 yrs.)</KBD><BR>
<STRONG>PAIS: Public Affairs Information Service/International</STRONG>, 1915 - .
<DD>Subject index to periodical articles, books, reports, governmental and intergovernmental publications on issues of public policy.

<P>

<DT><KBD><A HREF="/electronic/cd-rom/cd-rom.html#ssci">CD-ROM</A></KBD><BR>
<STRONG>Social Science Citation Index</STRONG>, 1990.
<DD>Huge interdisciplinary index; keyword searching; citation searching; includes book reviews.

<P>

<DT><STRONG><A HREF="/electronic/online/uncover.html">UnCover</A></STRONG>, 1990.
<DD>UnCover is an electronic index to articles from over 14,000 English language periodicals.  This service covers 1988 to date. Access is available on MUSE/other Resources/UnCOVER or go to the librarys web page.

<P>

<DT><KBD>CD-ROM</KBD><BR>
<STRONG>USFAC/U.S. Foreign Affairs</STRONG>, 1990.
<DD>Provides full-text access to official transcripts and country info released by the State Dept.

<P>

<DT><KBD>online catalog</KBD><BR>
<STRONG>Wilson Journal Citation Indexes</STRONG>, 1990 - .
<DD>seven periodical indexes loaded directly on our online catalog and available to you anytime you are using Muse.  At the Muse Main Menu screen select <KBD>J</KBD> and search using Muse commands.

<P>

<DT><KBD>Ref HQ 1111 .W65</KBD><BR>
<STRONG>Women Studies Index,</STRONG>, 1989 - .
<DD>Indexes 82 periodicals, comprehensive indexing of scholarly titles.
</DL>




<H3>Area Studies &amp; Topical Approach</H3>
<DL>
<DT><KBD>USFAC CD-ROM &amp; <A HREF="http://www.state.gov/www/background_notes/arabgnhp.html">http://www.state.gov/www/background_notes/arabgnhp.html</A></KBD><BR>
<STRONG>Country Studies &amp; Background Notes</STRONG>.
<DD>Overviews of countries published by the Department of State.

<P>

<DT><KBD><A HREF="/electronic/cd-rom/cd-rom.html#fbis">CD-ROM</A></KBD><BR>
<STRONG>FBIS Index</STRONG>. 1991- 1996.<BR>
<KBD>Gov Doc Fiche PrEx7.10: Latin America</KBD><BR>
<STRONG>FBIS (Foreign Broadcast Information Service)</STRONG>.<BR>
<KBD>Gov Doc Fiche PrEx 7.13:LAM</KBD><BR>
<STRONG>PRS (Joint Publications Reference Service)</STRONG>.
<DD>Full text translations of major broadcast media and major print media originating in countries around the world; CD-ROM index for FBIS; see a librarian.

<P>

<DT><KBD><A HREF="http://www.library.carleton.edu/electronic/online/index.html">http://www.library.carleton.edu/electronic/online/index.html</A> &amp; Ref F 1408 .H23</KBD><BR>
<STRONG>Handbook of Latin American Studies</STRONG>. 1935- .
<DD>Critical annotations of books, articles, pamphlets, maps, documents; many in Spanish; the basic and most important index for this region.

<P>

<DT><KBD>Ref Folio F 1408 .L3865 1992</KBD><BR>
<STRONG>Latin America and the Caribbean: a critical guide to research sources</STRONG>. 1992.
<DD>An interdisciplinary guide to reference and bibliographic sources on these regions.

<P>

<DT><KBD>Ref HX110.5 .V36 1991</KBD><BR>
Vanden, Harry E. <STRONG>Latin American Marxism: a bibliography</STRONG>. 1991.
<DD>Works about Latin American Marxism or by Marxist authors listed by time period and country.

<P>

<DT><KBD>Ref F 1410.5 .L38 1992</KBD><BR>
<STRONG>Latin American Military History: an annotated bibliography.</STRONG>. 1992.
<DD>Covers the history of the military in Latin America from the 1500s to present.

<P>

<DT><KBD>Ref F 1408 .L388 1990</KBD><BR>
R.A. McNeil and B.G. Valk., eds. <STRONG>Latin American Studies: a Basic Guide to Sources</STRONG>. 2nd ed. rev. 1990.
<DD>Annotated listing of resources; arranged by subject; Carleton may not have some sources.

<P>

<DT><KBD>Ref HV6431 .M498 1993</KBD><BR>
Mickolus, Edward F. <STRONG>Terrorism, 1988-1991.</STRONG>. 1993.
<DD>A chronology of terrorism and a selectively annotated bibliography.

<P>

<DT><KBD>Ref F 2308 .W32 1990</KBD><BR>
Waddell, D. A. G. <STRONG>Venezuela</STRONG>. 1990.
<DD>Contains annotated entries on works dealing with economy, politics, religion, and culture.

<P>

<DT><KBD>Ref HQ 1870.9.B96 1986</KBD><BR>
<STRONG>Women in the Third World: a historical bibliography</STRONG>. 1986.
<DD>Arranged by broad geographical area; annotated.
</DL>

<a name="ency"></A>
<h3>Encyclopedias, Guides, and Related Sources</h3>

<DL>
<DT><KBD>Ref HV 6243 .A45 1996</KBD><BR>
<STRONG>Amnesty International Report, 1976- .</STRONG> 1996.
<DD>Reports covering human rights information for each year; arranged by country.

<P>

<DT><KBD>Ref JL 1851 .A25  1989</KBD><BR>
<STRONG>The Dictionary of Contemporary Politics of South America</STRONG>. 1989.
<DD>Defines South American political organizations and political concepts.

<P>

<DT><KBD>Ref JA 61 .C66 1992</KBD><BR>
<STRONG>Encyclopedia of Government and Politics</STRONG>. 1992.
<DD>Discusses many facets of political theory and political institutions.

<P>

<DT><KBD>Ref JN 1 .E85  1996</KBD><BR>
<STRONG>The Europa Yearbook</STRONG>. 1959 - .
<DD>Current year in Reference; excellent current information on countries.

<P>

<DT><KBD>Ref JC 571 .H785 1992</KBD><BR>
<STRONG>Human Rights Watch World Report 1992</STRONG>.
<DD>Surveys the U.S. governments human rights policy in other countries and an analysis of human rights development in those countries.

<P>

<DT><KBD>Ref JX 1226 .P55 1988</KBD><BR>
<STRONG>The International Relations Dictionary</STRONG>. 1988.
<DD>Guide to the technical language of international relations.

<P>

<DT><KBD>Ref F 1401 .L3476</KBD><BR>
<STRONG>Latin American and Caribbean Contemporary Record, 1981 - 1989</STRONG>.
<DD>Organized into 4 parts, subdivided by countries or topic; great source for current overview.

<P>

<DT>Indexes to <STRONG>Newspapers</STRONG> kept on microfilm:<BR>
<DD><UL>
    <LI>Ref AI 21 .C46 <STRONG>Christian Science Monitor</STRONG>, 1960- .
    <LI>Ref AI 21 .T35 <STRONG>The Times London,</STRONG>, 1790- .
    <LI>Ref AI 21 .N44 <STRONG>New York Times</STRONG>, 1850- .
    <LI>Dialog         <STRONG>Philadelphia Inquirer</STRONG>, 1991-  .(see a librarian)
    <LI><STRONG>Minneapolis Star-Tribune</STRONG>, 1926 - ; Full text on <A HREF="/electronic/cd-rom/cd-rom.html#star">CD-ROM</A>, 1986- .
    <LI>Ref HG 1 .W258 <STRONG>Wall Street Journal</STRONG>, 1958- .
    <LI>Ref AI 21 .W3  <STRONG>Washington Post</STRONG>, 1979- .
    </UL>

<P>

<DT><KBD>Ref JA 61 .O95 1993</KBD><BR>
<STRONG>The Oxford Companion to Politics of the World</STRONG>. 1993.
<DD>Guide to international relations and national domestic politics throughout the world.

<P>

<DT><KBD>Ref JL 195 .P64 1982</KBD><BR>
<STRONG>Political Parties of the Americas</STRONG>. 1982.
<DD>Use this for overviews of major political happenings in a country and for descriptive paragraphs about parties.

<P>

<DT><KBD>Ref JA 51 .P64 1995</KBD><BR>
<STRONG>Political Risk Yearbook</STRONG>. 1995.<BR>
Volume 1 - North & Central America<BR>
Volume 3 - South America.
<DD>orecasts risks in business and investment by country.

<P>

<DT><KBD>Ref Folio HA 935 .S79 Vol.31, Pts. 1 &amp; 2</KBD><BR>
Committee on Latin American Studies, UCLA. <STRONG>Statistical Abstract of Latin America</STRONG>.
<DD>Extensive statistical information arranged by subject.
</DL>
