<h3>Background Sources</h3>

<DL>
<DT><kbd>Ref DR 10 .A65</kbd><br>
<strong>The American Bibliography of Slavic & East European Studies</strong>, 1957- .
<DD>Primarily English-language books, articles, reports, and book reviews.

<P>

<DT><kbd>Ref HA 17.D45</kbd><br>
<strong>Demographic Yearbook</strong>, 1977-   .
<DD>Statistics sent to the UN; arranged by continent and country.

<P>

<DT><kbd>Ref HB 849.2.P74143 1985</kbd><br>
Pressat, Roland. <strong>The Dictionary of Demography.</strong>
<DD>Use to identify terms and people.

<P>

<DT><kbd>Ref JN 1.E85</kbd><br>
<strong>The Europa Yearbook.</strong>
<DD>Current year in Reference; excellent current information on countries.

<P>

<DT><kbd>Ref Folio HB 3530.5 .W54 1984</kbd><br>
Wilkie, Richard W. <strong>Latin American Population and Urbanization Analysis.</strong>
<DD>A resource for maps and statistics, 1950-1982.

<P>

<DT><kbd>Ref Folio HA 40 .C8 U59</kbd><br>
<strong>UNESCO. Statistical Yearbook</strong>, 1964- .
<DD>Current year in Reference; covers education, technology, culture and the media.

<P>

<DT><kbd>Ref HC 59.7 .W659</kbd><br>		
<strong>World Development Report</strong>, 1978-   .
<DD>Each volume focuses on a broad topic, such as Development and the Environment.  1986 volume, part II focuses on trade and pricing policies in world agriculture.

<P>

<DT><kbd>Ref HC 59.W667</kbd><br>
<strong>World Resources (year)</strong>, 1986-   .
<DD>Overviews of current situations in the world; arranged by topic; discusses particular projects.

<P>

<DT><kbd>Ref HC 59.W667</kbd><br>
<strong>World Resources (year)</strong>, 1986-   .
<DD>Overviews of current situations in the world; arranged by topic; discusses particular projects.
</DL>

