<a name="in-ab">
<h3>Indexes and Abstracts-General</h3>

<DL>
<DT><kbd>Gov Doc Ref </kbd><br>
<strong>ASI (American Statistics Index)</strong>, 1974-   .
<DD>Comprehensive coverage of reports generated by government agencies containing statistics.

<P>

<DT><strong>Wilson Journal Citation Indexes</strong>
<DD>Seven periodical indexes (1991- ) loaded directly on our online catalog and available to you anytime you are using Muse.  At the Muse Main Menu screen select  J  and search using Muse commands.

<P>

<DT><strong>UnCOVER </strong>
<DD>An electronic index to articles from over 14,000 English language periodicals.  This service covers 1988 to date.  Access is available on MUSE/other Resources/UnCOVER or on the VAX at the $ prompt, type Telnet database.carl.org, then choose UnCOVER.

<P>

<DT><strong>FirstSearch</strong>
<DD>An electronic source that provides access to about 40 databases. The password is changed periodically, and can be obtained at the Information Desk in the Reference Room. You can reach this resource on MUSE/other Resources/FirstSearch or on the VAX at the $ prompt, type
<DD>Telnet fscat.oclc.org .
<DD>NEW! Web access is available on the Libe Resources Web Page
<DD>http://www.library.carleton.edu/resources.html .

<P>

<DT><kbd>Ref Folio HA 155.I53</kbd><br>
<strong>IIS (Index to International Statistics)</strong>, 1983-   .
<DD>Covers international publications including the UN; The University of MN has the fiche file, 1985 to date, 	Main Reference, Wilson Library.

<P>

<DT>CD-ROM<br>
<strong>Monthly Catalog of U.S. Government Publications</strong>, 1976-   .
<DD>Covers all documents available at the time of their printing; cumulative paper version (1917-1989) available 	in Gov Doc Ref.

<P>

<DT>CD-ROM & <kbd>Ref H 1.P8</kbd><br> 
<strong>PAIS:  Public Affairs Information Service Bulletin</strong>, 1915-  .
<DD>Subject index to articles, books, reports, documents on issues of public policy.

<P>

<DT>CD-ROM<br>
<strong>Social Science Citation Index</strong>, 1972-    .
<DD>Multidisciplinary; cited reference capability.
</DL>

<P>

