<H3>Selected Web Links for Methods of Social Research</H3>
<DL>
<P>
<DL>
<DT><A HREF="http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/">Inter-university Consortium for Political and Social Research</A>
<DD>The Inter-university Consortium for Political and Social Research (ICPSR), located within the Institute 
    for Social Research at the University of Michigan , is a membership-based, not-for-profit 
    organization serving member colleges and universities in the United 
    States and abroad. ICPSR provides access to the world's largest archive of computerized 
    social science data.
<P>
<DT><A HREF="http://www.carleton.ca/~cmckie/research.html">Research Engines for the Social Sciences</A>
<DD>A central jumping off point for literature and data searching for sociologists
    and serious students in related disciplines.Developed in a graduate research design 
    seminar at Carleton University in Ottawa. 
<P>
<DT><A HREF="http://www.soc.umn.edu/~edwards/soclinks.htm">Resources for Social Researchers</A>
<DD>Links for publications, data information, research organizations, graduate student
    information, and graduate institutions. Maintained by a University of Minnesota graduate student.
<P>
<DT><A HREF="http://www.yahoo.com/Social_Science/Sociology/">Yahoo:Social Science:Sociology</A>
<DD>The jumping off point to +200 WWW sites on sociological topics.
<P>
<DT><A HREF="http://www.yahoo.com/Social_Science/Sociology/Indices/">Yahoo:Social Science:
     Sociology:Indices</A>
<DD>Links to six directories of sociology sites on the Web. Includes the
    <A HREF="http://www.w3.org/pub/DataSources/bySubject/Sociology/Overview.html">WWW Virtual Library on Sociology</A>, 
    maintained by Dr. Samuel R. Brown at Seton Hall University, the 
    <A HREF="http://www.wcsu.ctstateu.edu/socialsci/socres.html">Sociology Internet Resources</A>, 
    maintained by the Department of Social Sciences at Western Connecticut State University, and the  
    Virginia Tech Library's <A HREF="http://refserver.lib.vt.edu/refhtml/subjects/Sociology/sociology.html">
    Sociology Resources on the Internet</A>.
<P>
</DL>
</DL>
<P>
<HR SIZE=3>
<P>
<H2>Selected Paper Resources for Methods of Social Research</H2>
<P>
This list is intended to introduce you to some of the paper materials we have on social research methods.  
It is not a complete list, but merely a sampling.  All items listed below are located in the Reference
Collection on Level 4 unless otherwise noted.  Please don't hesitate to ask a librarian if your aren't
finding what you need here.
<P>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="#in-ab">Indexes and Abstracts--General</A>
<LI><A HREF="#subj">Indexes and Abstracts--Subject</A>
<LI><A HREF="#biblio">Subject Bibliographies</A>
<LI><A HREF="#misc">Miscellaneous</A>

</UL>

<HR ALIGN="center" WIDTH=50%>
<P>
<!-- ############### Indexes and Abstracts--General  -->
<a name="in-ab">
<h3>Indexes and Abstracts--General</h3>
<P>
Turn to indexes and abstracts to find more information on your topic.  If you want to know whether 
Carleton subscribes to a particular journal, perform a <STRONG><KBD>T > TITLE</KBD></STRONG> search in Muse 
using the exact title of the journal you're looking for.
<P>

<DL>

<DT><kbd>Ref E 173 .A51</kbd><br> 
<strong>America: History and Life</strong>, 1964- .
<DD>Index to 2,000 scholarly journals.  See also <A HREF="/electronic/cd-rom/cd-rom.html#am">
    American: History and Life</A> on CD-ROM.

<P>

<DT><kbd>Gov Doc Ref</kbd><br>
<strong>CIS:  Congressional Information Service</strong>, 1970- .
<DD>Excellent indexing with abstracts covering all documents of Congress (hearings, acts, bills, laws, 
reports, etc.).

<P>

<DT><kbd>Microfiche Z 5055 .A53</kbd><br>
<strong>Dissertation Abstracts</strong>, 1963- .
<DD>Section A covers Humanities & Social Sciences; on microfiche after 1979.  This resource is also
    available on <A HREF="/electronic/online/firstsearch.html">FirstSearch</A>. 

<P>

<DT><kbd>Gov Doc Reference (1917- )</kbd><br>
<strong>Monthly Catalog of U.S. Government Publications</strong>. (GPO)
<DD>Basic index to U.S. government publications. The years July 1976-present of this resource are also 
    available online via <A HREF="/electronic/online/firstsearch.html">FirstSearch</A>.

<P>

<DT><kbd>Ref H 1 .P8 (1915-  )</kbd><br>
<strong>PAIS: Public Affairs Information Service/International</strong>, 1915-  .
<DD>Subject index to periodical articles, books, reports, governmental and intergovernmental 
    publications on issues of public policy. Also available on <A HREF="/electronic/cd-rom/cd-rom.html#pais">
    on CD-ROM</A>.  The most recent 10 years, known as PAIS Decade, is available on
    <A HREF="/electronic/online/firstsearch.html">FirstSearch</A> 

<P>

<DT><kbd>Ref AI 3 .S62</kbd><br>
<strong>Social Sciences Index</strong>, 1974- . (continues: <strong>Social Sciences and 
Humanities Index</strong>, 1907-1974)<br>
<DD>Selective indexing to more scholarly articles than <STRONG>Reader's Guide</STRONG>. 
The years 1974-present are also available on <A HREF="/electronic/online/firstsearch.html">FirstSearch</A>. 

</DL>

<HR ALIGN="center" WIDTH=50%>
<P>
<!-- ############### Indexes and Abstracts--Subject  -->
<a name="subj">
<h3>Indexes and Abstracts--Subject</h3>

<DL>

<DT><kbd>Ref GN 1 .A15</kbd><br>
<strong>Abstracts in Anthropology. </strong><br>Carleton has: 1974-  (St. Olaf 
has: 1970-  )
<DD>Basic index in the field; covers books, articles, and papers.

<P>
<DT><kbd>Ref GN 1 .A67</kbd><br>
<strong>Anthropological Literature: an Index to Periodical Articles and Essays</strong>. 1983- .
<DD>Library has:  1983 & 1990- present in <EM>paper</EM> and 1984-1989 on <EM>microfiche</EM>.  See
also <A HREF="/electronic/online/anl.html">Anthropological Literature</A> online.

<P>

<DT><kbd>Ref Folio HM 1 .C65</kbd><br>
<strong>CRIS: Combined Retrospective Index set to Journals in Sociology, 1895-1974.</strong>
<DD>A classified listing with keyword indexing from journals not covered in past indexes.

<P>

<DT><kbd>Ref F 1408 .H23</kbd><br>
<strong>Handbook of Latin American Studies</strong>, 1935-  .
<DD>Critical annotations of books, articles, pamphlets, maps, documents; many in Spanish; the 
    basic and most important index for this region.
    Also available <A HREF="/electronic/online/hla.html">online</A>.

<P>

<DT><kbd>Ref HM 15 .I594</kbd><br>
<strong>International Bibliography of the Social Sciences: Sociology</strong>, 1955-  .<BR>
<DT><kbd>Ref GN 304 .I593</kbd><br>  
<strong>International Bibliography of the Social Sciences: Anthropology</strong>, 1955-  .
<DD>Comprehensive research listing; subject index; international coverage.

<P>

<DT><kbd>Ref HM 1 .S67</kbd><br> 
<strong>Sociological Abstracts</strong>, 1952- .
<DD>Basic Index in this discipline.  Online version covering 1963-present is 
    available <A HREF="/electronic/online/firstsearch.html">FirstSearch</A>. 

<P>

<DT><kbd>Ref HQ 1111 .W65</kbd><br>
<strong>Women Studies Abstract</strong>, 1972- .
<DD>Indexes scholarly and popular publications not covered by more mainstream indexes.

</DL>


<HR ALIGN="center" WIDTH=50%>
<P>
<!-- ############### Subject Bibliographies  -->
<a name="biblio">
<h3>Subject Bibliographies</h3>
<P>
Subject bibliographies are lists of materials on a particular topic.  They should save you time because the 
author has done the tedious work of searching catalogs and indexes to find information on the topic. 
Many bibliographies also contain evaluations of the works that they mention.  Listed here are several general 
titles, but note that we have bibliographies soley on individual topics as well. (Try a keyword search on 
Muse to find some.  For example,
type: <STRONG><KBD>sociology bibliography</KBD></STRONG> to find some bibliographies on sociology.)  
<P>

<DT><kbd>Ref Folio HQ 536 .B46 1984</kbd><br> 
Benson-von der Ohe, Elizabeth. <strong>An Annotated Bibliography of US
Scholarship on the History of the Family</strong>. 1986.
<DD>

<P>

<DT><kbd>HM 1 .A763</kbd><br>
<strong>Annual Review of Sociology</strong>, 1975- .
<DD>Overviews of current topics in bibliographic essay form; topics vary in each volume; good place to start.

<P>

<DT><kbd>Ref E 185.86 .D355 1986</kbd><br>
Davis, Lenwood G. <strong>The Black Family in the United States</strong>. 1986.
<DD>

<P>

<DT><kbd>Ref E 185.8 .G26</kbd><br>
Gagala, Kenneth L. <strong>The Economics of Minorities</strong>. 1976.
<DD>

<P>

<DT><kbd>Ref HD 7288.72 .U5 M65 1987</kbd><br>
Momeni, Jamshid A. <strong>Housing and Racial/Ethnic Minority Status in
the United States</strong>. 1987.
<DD>

<P>

<DT><kbd>Ref E 184 .S75 L37 1986</kbd><br>
<strong>Latinos in the United States</strong>. 1986.
<DD>

<P>

<DT><kbd>Ref HQ 777.4 .G68 1990</kbd><br>
Gouke, Mary N. and Arline M Rollins. <strong>One-Parent Children, The
Growing Minority:  A Research Guide</strong>. 1990
<DD>

<P>

<DT><kbd>Ref HC 110  .P6 C44</kbd><br>
Chalfant, H. Paul. <strong>Sociology of Poverty in the United States</strong>. 1985.
<DD>

</DL>

<HR ALIGN="center" WIDTH=50%>
<P>
<!-- ############### Miscellaneous  -->
<a name-"misc">
<h3>Miscellaneous</h3>

<DL>

<DT><kbd>Ref HB 849.2 .P74143 1985</kbd><br>
Pressat, Roland. <strong>The Dictionary of Demography</strong>. 1985.
<DD>

<P>

<DT><kbd>Ref HM 17 .E5 1992</kbd><br>
<strong>Encyclopedia of Sociology</strong>. 1992. 4 vols. 
<DD>

<P>

<DT><kbd>Ref Folio GN 550 .E53 1991</kbd><br>
<strong>Encyclopedia of World Cultures</strong>. 1991. 6 vols.
<DD>Prepared under the auspices of HRAF; overview of cultural groups with a short bibliography.

<P>

<DT><kbd>Ref HM 261 .G3</kbd><br>
<strong>The Gallup Poll</strong>.
<DD>

<P>

<DT>Microfiche and CD-ROM (1995-)<BR>
<strong>HRAF:  Human Relations Area Files</strong>.
<DD>A collection of information on about 325 primitive, historical and contemporary 
    cultures; on microfiche; paper indexes on shelves in the Microforms Room.  See also 
    <A HREF="/electronic/CD-ROM/CD-ROM.html#ehraf">Electronic Human Relations Area Files</A>.

<P>

<DT>GovDocs: Smithsonian Institution Publications
<DD><kbd>SI 2.1</kbd><strong> Bureau of American Ethnology.  Annual Reports</strong>.
<DD><kbd>SI 2.3</kbd><strong> Bureau of American Ethnology. Bulletin</strong>. 1887-1967.
<DD><kbd>SI 1.33</kbd><strong> Contributions to Anthropology</strong>.
<DD><kbd>SI 1.16</kbd><strong> Institute of Social Anthropology. Publications</strong>.
<DD><kbd>SI 1.7</kbd><strong> Smithsonian Miscellaneous Collections</strong>.
<DD><kbd>SI 1.1</kbd><strong> Smithsonian Year</strong>. (formerly <strong>Annual Report</strong>)
<BR>
<BR>
</DL>

<P>

To identify which sociology-related periodicals are owned by the Gould Library, perform the following steps on
Muse:
<P>
<OL>
<LI><STRONG><KBD>N > NUMBERS</KBD></STRONG>
<LI><STRONG><KBD>C > CALL numbers (Library of Congress)</KBD></STRONG> (use <STRONG><KBD>PER</KBD></STRONG>)
<LI><STRONG><KBD>L > LIMIT this Search</KBD></STRONG>
<LI><STRONG><KBD>S > Words in the SUBJECT</KBD></STRONG>
<LI>(use <STRONG><KBD>socio*</KBD></STRONG>)
<LI><STRONG><KBD>F > Find items with above limits</KBD></STRONG>
</OL>
<P>
</DL>
