<H3>Selected Web Links for Ethnography of Latin America</H3>
<DL>
<DL>
<DT><A HREF="http://www.yahoo.com/Regional/Regions/Central_America/Countries/">Central American Countries</A> and 
    <A HREF="http://www.yahoo.com/Regional/Regions/Latin_America/Countries/">Latin American Countries</A>
<DD>Here you'll find links to information on 7 Central American and 25 Latin American countries.
<P>
<DT><A HREF="http://www.globalnt.com/">Global Net Latin America Directory</A>
<DD>An extensive directory of WWW servers in Latin America and other related sites.  Warning:  It appears all
    text is in spanish and portuguese.
<P> 
<DT><A HREF="http://www.library.law.miami.edu/~smith/latin.html#South American and Caribbean Newspapers">
     South American and Caribbean Newspapers</A>
<DD>Links to nearly 40 Web-based newspapers published in South American and Caribbean nations.  Maintained by
    the University of Miami Law Library. 
<P>
<DT><A HREF="http://lanic.utexas.edu/las.html">WWW Virtual Library: Latin American Studies</A>
<DD>A superb clearinghouse for Internet-accessible information on Latin America.  Maintained 
    by the Latin American Network Information Center at the University of Texas at Austin.
<P>
<DT><A HREF="http://www.yahoo.com/Regional/Regions/Central_America/">Yahoo:Regions:Central America</A>
<DD>Nearly 20 links to sites offering information on Central American topics.
<P> 
<DT><A HREF="http://www.yahoo.com/Regional/Regions/Latin_America/">Yahoo:Regions:Latin America</A>
<DD>Over +130 links to sites offering information on Latin American topics.
<P>
</DL>
</DL>
<P>
<HR>
<H2>Selected Paper Resources for Ethnography of Latin America</H2>
<P>
This list is intended to introduce you to some of the paper materials we have on Latin America.  
It is not a complete list, but merely a sampling.  All items listed below are located in the Reference
Collection on Level 4 unless otherwise noted.  Please don't hesitate to ask a librarian if your aren't
finding what you need here.
<P>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="#in-ab">Indexes and Abstracts</A>
<LI><A HREF="#area">Area Studies Approach</A>
<LI><A HREF="#topic">Topic Approach</A>
<LI><A HREF="#add">Additional Sources</A>

</UL>


<HR ALIGN="center" WIDTH=50%>
<P>
<!-- ############### Indexes and Abstracts  -->
<a name="in-ab">
<h3>Indexes and Abstracts</h3>
<P>
Turn to indexes and abstracts to find more information on your topic.   If you want to know whether 
Carleton subscribes to a particular journal, perform a <STRONG><KBD>T > TITLE</KBD></STRONG> search in Muse 
using the exact title of the journal you're looking for.
<P>

<DL>

<DT><kbd>Ref GN 1 .A15</kbd><br>
<strong>Abstracts in Anthropology</strong>. Carleton has: 1974-  (St. Olaf has: 1970-  )
<DD>A basic index in the field; covers books, articles, and papers.

<P>

<DT><kbd>Ref GN 1 .A67</kbd><br>
<strong>Anthropological Literature: an Index to Periodical Articles and Essays</strong> 
       (Tozzer Library at Harvard). 1983-
       Library has:  1983 & 1990- present in paper and 1984-1989 on microfiche.
<DD>Worldwide coverage of anthropology periodicals and selected edited works.
    Also available <A HREF="/electronic/online/anl.html">online</A>.

<P>
<DT><kbd>Gov Doc Fiche PrEx7.10:  Latin America</kbd><br>
<strong>FBIS (Foreign Broadcast Information Service)</strong>.
<DT><kbd>Gov Doc Fiche PrEx 7.13:LAM</kbd><br>
<strong>JPRS (Joint Publications Reference Service)</strong>.
<DD>Translations of major broadcast media and major print media originating in countries around the world.
    Access to these resources is accomplished through <A HREF="/electronic/cd-rom/cd-rom.html#fbis">
    Foreign Broadcast Information Service (FBIS)</A>on CD-ROM.

<P>

<DT><kbd>Ref F 1408 .H23</kbd><br>
<strong>Handbook of Latin American Studies</strong>, 1935-  .
<DD>Critical annotations of books, articles, pamphlets, maps, documents; many in Spanish; the 
    basic and most important index for this region.
    Also available <A HREF="/electronic/online/hla.html">online</A>.

<P>

<DT><kbd>Ref HM 15 .I594</kbd><br>
<strong>International Bibliography of the Social Sciences: Sociology</strong>, 1955-  .<BR>
<DT><kbd>Ref GN 304 .I593</kbd><br>  
<strong>International Bibliography of the Social Sciences: Anthropology</strong>, 1955-  .
<DD>Comprehensive research listing; subject index; international coverage.

<P>

<DT><kbd>Ref H 1 .P8 (1915-  )</kbd><br>
<strong>PAIS: Public Affairs Information Service/International</strong>, 1915-  .
<DD>Subject index to periodical articles, books, reports, governmental and intergovernmental 
    publications on issues of public policy. Also available on <A HREF="/electronic/cd-rom/cd-rom.html#pais">
    on CD-ROM</A>.  The most recent 10 years, known as PAIS Decade, is available on
    <A HREF="/electronic/online/firstsearch.html">FirstSearch</A> 

<P>

<DT><kbd>Ref HQ 1111 .W65</kbd><br>
<strong>Women Studies Abstract</strong>, 1972- .
<DD>Indexes scholarly and popular publications not covered by more mainstream indexes.

<P>

<DT><kbd>Ref HQ 1180 .W683</kbd><br>
<strong>Women Studies Index</strong>, 1989-  .
<DD>Straight alphabetical author and subject listing of bibliographic citations. Comprehensive indexing of 
scholarly periodicals, selective indexing of popular titles.


</DL>

<!-- ###############put Area Studies Approach here  -->
<HR ALIGN="center" WIDTH=50%>
<P>
<a name="area">
<h3>Area Studies Approach</h3>

<DL>

<DT><kbd>F 1434 .H3/ .E88 - 3rd Level</kbd><br>
<strong>Handbook of Middle American Indians</strong>. 16 vols.
<DD>Coverage includes archaeology, physical and social anthropology, ethnology, ethnohistory, etc.; 
    includes bibliographic sources.

<P>

<DT><kbd>SI 2.3:143  (Gov Docs-3rd Level)</kbd><br>
<strong>Handbook of South American Indians</strong>, 7 vols., 1946-1959. 
<DD>Bureau of American Ethnology, (Bulletin 143); vol. 7 is an index. Encyclopedia type source; 
    bibliographies listed; includes Mesoamerica and the Caribbean.

<P>

<DT><kbd>Ref  F2229.W45 1987</kbd><br>
<strong>The Indians of South America: a Bibliography</strong>.
<DD>Books and reports in several languages about indigenous peoples.

<P>

<DT><kbd>Ref F 1408 .L388 1990</kbd><br>
McNeil, R.A. and B. G. Valk., eds. <strong>Latin American Studies: a Basic Guide to Sources</strong>.  2nd ed. rev.
<DD>Annotated listing of resources; arranged by subject.
	
</DL>

<!-- ###############put Topic Approach here  -->
<HR ALIGN="center" WIDTH=50%>
<P>
<a name="topic">
<h3>Topics Approach</h3>

<DL>

<DT><strong>Agricola</strong>, 1970-  .
<DD>Produced by the U.S. Department of Agriculture; provides selective worldwide coverage.
    Agricola is accessible via <A HREF="/electronic/online/firstsearch.html">FirstSearch</A>. 

<P>

<DT><kbd>Ref HD 1415 .O47 1991</kbd><br>
Olsen, Wallace C. <strong>Agricultural Economics and Rural Sociology: the Contemporary Core Literature</strong>.
<DD>A ranked core list of primary monographs for the Third World and current primary journals.

<P>

<DT><strong>Agris International</strong>, 1975-  .
<DD>Produced by FAO (Food and Agricultural Organization of the UN); best source for indiginous 
    documents as publications are submitted by each country.  Available on
    <A HREF="/electronic/online/dialog.html">Dialog</A>.

<P>

<DT><kbd>Ref JA 61 .C66 1992</kbd><br>
<strong>Encyclopedia of Government and Politics</strong>.
<DD>Main themes and subjects written by experts in the field.

<P>

<DT><kbd>Ref HD 1417 .K37 1986</kbd><br>
Karim, M. Bazllul, comp. <strong>The Green Revolution: an International Bibliography</strong>.
<DD>Arranged by place; subject index; includes books, reports, journal articles.

<P>

<DT><kbd>Ref JC 571 .H785</kbd><br> 
<strong>Human Rights Watch World Report</strong>, 1989-  .
<DD>Surveys the U.S. governments human rights policy in other countries and an 
    analysis of human rights development in those countries.

<P>

<DT><kbd>Ref JA 51 .P64 1996</kbd><br>
<strong>Political Risk Yearbook</strong>.
<DD>Information gathered concerning individual countries that help bridge the gap between 
    academia and the business world.

<P>

<DT><kbd>Ref HQ 1870.9.B96 1986</kbd><br>
<strong>Women in the Third World: a Historical Bibliography</strong>.
<DD>Arranged by broad geographical area; annotated.

<P>

<DT><kbd>Ref HX 1 .Y4</kbd><br>
<strong>Yearbook on International Communist Affairs</strong>, 1970-  .
<DD>Arranged by country; overview of the general political situation and the state of 
    communism within a country; written by experts in the field.

</DL>

<HR ALIGN="center" WIDTH=50%>
<P>
<!--  ################ Additional Sources   -->
