<LI><A HREF="/electronic/CD-ROM/CD-ROM.html#fbis">Foreign Broadcast Information Service</A>
<LI><A HREF="/electronic/CD-ROM/CD-ROM.html#gpo">MARCIVE GPO CAT/PAC Guide to Government Documents</A>
<LI><A HREF="/electronic/CD-ROM/CD-ROM.html#ssci">Social Science Citation Index</A>
</ul>

<H3><A HREF="/instruction/evalsource.html">Tips for Evaluating a Source</A></H3>
<P>
<H3><A HREF="/instruction/eciting.html">Tips for Citing Internet Sources</A></H3>
<P>
<H3>Reference Sources in Anthropology</H3>

<ul>
<li><a href="#in-ab">Indexes and Abstracts-General</a>
<li><a href="#in-ab2">Indexes and Abstracts-Subject</a>
<li><a href="#area-ap">Area Studies Approach</a>
<li><a href="#top-ap">Topic Approach</a>
<li><a href="#additional">Additional Sources</a>
<li><a href="#www">WWW Sites</a>
</ul>

<a name="in-ab">
<center><h3>Indexes and Abstracts-General</h3></center>

<DL>

<DT><strong>Wilson Journal Citation Indexes</strong>
<DD>Seven periodical indexes (1991- ) loaded directly on our online catalog and available to you anytime you are using Muse.  At the Muse Main Menu screen select  J  and search using Muse commands.

<P>

<DT><strong>UnCOVER </strong>
<DD>An electronic index to articles from over 14,000 English language periodicals.  This service covers 1988 to date.  Access is available on MUSE/other Resources/UnCOVER or on the VAX at the $ prompt, type Telnet database.carl.org, then choose UnCOVER.

<P>

<DT><strong>FirstSearch</strong>
<DD>An electronic source that provides access to about 40 databases. The password is changed periodically, and can be obtained at the Information Desk in the Reference Room. You can reach this resource on MUSE/other Resources/FirstSearch or on the VAX at the $ prompt, type <kbd>Telnet fscat.oclc.org</kbd>.  Web access is available on the Libe Resources Web Page http://www.library.carleton.edu/resources.html .

<P>

<DT>CD-ROM (1981- .); Dialog search (1972- .)<br>
<strong>SSCI: Social Sciences Citation Index</strong>, 1972-   .
<DD>Huge interdisciplinary index; keyword searching; citation searching; includes book reviews..

<P>

<DT><kbd>Ref H 1 .P8(paper) and CD-ROM index area</kbd><br>
<strong>PAIS: Public Affairs Information Service/International</strong>, 1915-   .
<DD>Subject index to periodical articles, books, reports, governmental and intergovernmental publications on 	issues of public policy.

<P>

<DT>CD-ROM<br>
<strong>USFAC/U.S. Foreign Affairs.</strong>
<DD>Provides full-text access to official transcripts and country information released by the State Dept.

<P>

<DT>Ref Folio HA 155 .I53<br>
<strong>IIS: Index To International Statistics</strong>,1983-   .
<DD>Guide to statistical publications of international intergovernmental organizations (including the UN); 
INDEX in one volume with ABSTRACTS in the second volume; a microfiche set of the full text of the 	documents listed is available at the University of Minnesota.

<P>

<DT><strong>United Nations documents</strong>: 
<DD>Carleton has some publications published by the UN; see a reference librarian or Carolyn Sanford for assistance; easiest access to many of these, which are available at the University of	Minnesota, is through IIS.

</DL>

<P>

<a name="in-ab2">
<center><h3>Indexes and Abstracts-Subject</h3></center>

<DL>
<DT>Ref GN 1 .A67<br>
<strong>Anthropological Literature</strong>, an Index to Periodical Articles & Essays, v.6, 1983-  . 
<DD>(v.5, 1983 and 1989 to date in paper; 1984-1988 on microfiche.)	Worldwide coverage of 1000+ periodicals.

<P> 

<DT><strong>International Bibliography of the Social Sciences.</strong><br>
<strong>SOCIOLOGY</strong>, 1955-  .  Ref HM 15 .I594<br>
<strong>ANTHROPOLOGY</strong>, 1955-  .  Ref GN 304 .I593
<DD>Comprehensive listing of research; classified arrangement with subject index; international in coverage.

<P>

<DT>FirstSarch & <kbd>Ref HM1 .S67</kbd>(1963- )<br>
<strong>Sociological Abstracts</strong>, 1952-   .
<DD>Main index to journal articles.

<P>

<DT><kbd>Ref HQ 1111 .W65</kbd><br>
<strong>Women Studies Abstracts</strong>, 1972-  .
<DD>Arranged by broad subject;  slightly more detailed subject index; some abstracts are included; popular and 	scholarly periodicals indexed.

<P>

<DT><kbd>Ref HQ 1180 .W683</kbd><br>
<strong>Women Studies Index</strong>, 1989-  .
<DD>Indexes 82 periodicals, comprehensive indexing of scholarly titles.
</DL>

<P>

<a name="area-ap">
<center><h3>Area Studies Approach</h3></center>

<DL>

<DT><kbd>Ref DS 501 .B49</kbd><br>
<strong>Bibliography of Asian Studies</strong>, 1980-  .
<DD>Arranged by categories under geographical sections; use table of contents for access; materials often 	difficult to obtain.

<P>

<DT><kbd>Gov Doc D101.22:550</kbd>-  (3rd Level)<br>
<strong>"Country Studies"</strong>
<DD>Compiled by the Foreign Area Studies section of The American University and published by the 	Department of Defense; covers all aspects of a country; includes a bibliography; revised infrequently with 	the most recent version now appearing on the CD-ROM USFAC.

<P>

<DT>CD-ROM<br>
<strong>FBIS Index</strong> (1991- )<br>
<kbd>Gov Doc Fiche PrEx7.10:  Latin America</kbd><br>
<strong>FBIS (Foreign Broadcast Information Service)</strong><br>
<kbd>Gov Doc Fiche PrEx 7.13:LAM</kbd><br>
<strong>JPRS (Joint Publications Reference Service)</strong>
<DD>Full text translations of major broadcast media and major print media originating in countries around the 	world; CD-ROM index for FBIS; see a librarian.

<P>

<DT><kbd>Ref F 1408 .H23</kbd><br>
<strong>Handbook of Latin American Studies</strong>, 1935-  . 
<DD>Critical annotations of books, articles, pamphlets, maps, documents; many in Spanish; the basic and most 	important index for this region.

<P>

<DT><kbd>Ref DT 3 .I58</kbd><br>
<strong>International African Bibliography,</strong>, 1974-    
<DD>Arranged by area of descending size; 1980 to date issues have  subject and ethnic group indexes.

</DL>

<P>

<a name="top-ap">
<center><h3>Topic Approach</h3></center>

<DL>

<DT><kbd>Ref HD 1417 .K37 1986</kbd><br>
<strong>Karim, M. Bazllul, comp.</strong>
<strong>The Green Revolution: An International Bibliography.</strong>   
<DD>Arranged by place; subject index; includes books, reports, journal articles.

<P>

<DT>FirstSearch.<br>
<strong>Agricola</strong>, 1972-    
<DD>Produced by the U.S. Department of Agriculture; provides selective worldwide coverage.

<P>

<DT>Dialog File -  see a librarian.<br>
<strong>CAB Abstracts</strong>, 1972-  .    
<DD>Comprehensive indexing to international publications; covers developing countries extensively.

<P>

<DT>Dialog File 203 - see a librarian for an online search.<br>
<strong>AGRIS International</strong>, 1975-  .    
<DD>Produced by FAO (Food and Agricultural Organization of the UN); best source for indigenous documents since publications are submitted by each country.

<P>

<DT>Dialog File 91 - see a librarian for an online search.<br>
<strong>Population Bibliography</strong>, 1966-  .  
<DD>International in scope with emphasis on developing countries.

</DL>

<P>

<a name="additional">
<center><h3>Additional Sources</h3></center>

<DL>

<DT><kbd>Ref HD 1415 .O47 1991</kbd><br>
Olsen, Wallace C.<br>
<DD><strong>Agricultural Economics and Rural Sociology</strong>: the Contemporary Core Literature.	Contains a ranked core list of primary monographs for the Third World, current primary journals a	additional information.

<P>

<DT><kbd>Ref F 1408 .L388 1990</kbd><br>
McNeil, Robert A. and Valk, Barbara G., eds.<br>
<strong>Latin American Studies</strong>: a Basic Guide to Sources, 2nd ed. revised.
<DD>Overviews of current situations in the world; arranged by topic; discusses particular projects.

<P>

<DT><kbd>Ref FOLIO HQ 1150 .S73 1991</kbd><br>
Schmittroth, Linda, ed.<br>
<strong>Statistical Record of Women Worldwide</strong>
<DD>Arranged by broad subject; many charts not divided by country; others are, such as fertility rates from 1989 	to 2020; subject index has entries by geographic area.

<P>

<DT><kbd>Ref FOLIO HC 10 .W827 1992-93</kbd><br>
<strong>World Resources (1992-93)</strong>
<DD>Produced by the UN; broad overviews ("Poor Countries", "Food and Agriculture") and tables of statistics 	which are arranged by country.

<P>

<DT>Ref Room<br>
<DD><strong>Yearbooks</strong> for specific countries or continents.

</DL>

<P>

<a name="www">
<center><h3>World Wide Web Sites</h3></center>

<strong>United Nations:</strong> 		URL: <a href="http://www.undcp.org/unlinks.html">http://www.undcp.org/unlinks.html</a><br>

<strong>Latin American Studies:</strong> 	URL: <a href="http://lanic.utexas.edu/las.html">http://lanic.utexas.edu/las.html</a><br>

<strong>Economic Democracy Info Netwrk:</strong>     URL: <a href="http://garnet.berkeley.edu/">http://garnet.berkeley.edu/</a><br>

<strong>Inter-American Socioeconomic Data:</strong>  URL: <a href="http://www.iadb.org:80/IDB/TheRegion.html">http://www.iadb.org:80/IDB/TheRegion.html</a><br>

<strong>Asian Studies:</strong>		URL: <a href="http://coombs.anu.edu.au/WWWVL-AsianStudies.html">http://coombs.anu.edu.au/WWWVL-AsianStudies.html</a><br>

<strong>African Development Studies:</strong>	   URL: <a href="http://WWW.WORLDBANK.ORG/html/ibads/IBADS.html">http://WWW.WORLDBANK.ORG/html/ibads/IBADS.html</a><br>

<P>
