<HEAD>
<TITLE>MACINTOSH OPERATING SYSTEM</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">

<CENTER><H1>Macintosh Operating System</H1></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3>Presentors:  Michael Current, Mark Heiman, and Terry Metz</H3></CENTER>
<HR>
<P>
<DL>
<DT><STRONG>DATES AND TIMES:</STRONG>
    <P>
    <PRE>
            No sessions currently scheduled.
    </PRE>
<DD>All training sessions will be held in the Center for Mathematics and Computing (CMC) room #102.
    <BR>
    <BR>
<DT><STRONG>PURPOSE:</STRONG>
<P>
<DD>Macintosh desktop computers are one of the primary work tools for the majority
of Gould Library staff (as well as for our library users). 
<P>
The purpose of this workshop is to give you hands-on experience and tips for using your Macintosh
computer more effectively (i.e., doing the &quot;right&quot; tasks) and efficiently
(i.e., doing the &quot;right&quot; tasks &quot;well.&quot;)
<P>
NOTE: Because the skills levels, needs, and interests of attendees will vary, the overall content
will also vary.  Questions are encouraged, so come armed with your list.
Arrive early if you feel you need basic information or later for more advanced tips.  We
expect this workshop will spawn more specific workshops at later dates.
<BR>
<BR>
<DT><STRONG>WHO SHOULD ATTEND:</STRONG>
<P>
<DD>Anyone who wants to learn improve their knowledge of using their Macintosh computer.  Attendees should
have basic &quot;point-and-click&quot; skills.
<BR>
<BR>
<DT><STRONG>TIME BUDGET:</STRONG> (subject to revision)
<P>
<DD>Hour One: (1:00-2:00) - Fundamental Level
<UL>
 
        <LI>basic orientation to the Macintosh operating system (how to
          manage files; understand basic features such as control
          panels, extensions; fundamental troubleshooting etc.)
</UL>
<P>
<DD>Hour Two: (2:00-3:00) - Intermediate Level 
<UL>
        <LI>orientation to Macintosh system 7.5 and the PowerMacintosh
         (i.e., what are the the new features and how can I take
         advantage of them?)
            
</UL>
<P>
<DD>Hour Three: (3:00-4:00) - Advanced Level 
<UL>
        <LI>networking and filesharing
        <LI>Q & A for applications such as Word, Excel, and FileMaker        
</UL>
</DL>
<BR>
<BR>
<P>
<HR>
<P>
<CENTER><A HREF="/instruction/index.html">Return to the Library Instruction Page</A></CENTER>
