<HEAD>
<TITLE>
FirstSearch
</TITLE>
<HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">
<CENTER><H1>FirstSearch</H1></CENTER>
<P>
<strong>FirstSearch</strong> is a service that permits users to search many databases.  
You must have an <A HREF="http://www.library.carleton.edu:8001/firstsearchpswd.html">
authorization number and a current password</A> to access Firstsearch.  This password
changes irregularly.  Ask at the <A HREF="/reference/infodesk.html">Information Desk</A> 
to obtain the current password or follow the password link on this page.
<P>
<IMG SRC="/images/new.gif" ALT="[New!]">You may now <A HREF="/ils/#firstsearch">
electronically submit ILS requests</A> for library materials identified on the 
FirstSearch service. 
<P>
FirstSearch permits users to order 
photocopies of articles listed in selected databases from 
commercial document delivery services.  Those who wish to use this 
document ordering service may do so at their own expense. The 
Library does not act as an agent of FirstSearch, and this feature 
is not part of Interlibrary Services. This document delivery
service may be of interest to those who need to pay copyright 
royalty fees.
<BR>
<BR>
<CENTER><STRONG><A HREF="http://www.oclc.org/oclc/man/6928fsdb/6928toc.htm">A Complete List and Description of FirstSearch Databases</A>
<P>
<A HREF="telnet://fscat.oclc.org">Launch a Telnet Session to FirstSearch</A>
<P>
<IMG SRC="/images/new.gif" ALT="[New!]"><A HREF="http://www.ref.oclc.org:2000/html/fs_pswd.htm">FirstSearch Web Access</A></STRONG></CENTER>
<BR>
<BR>
<hr>
<P>
<CENTER><A HREF="index.html">Return to the Online Databases Page</A></CENTER>
