<head>
<title>Interlibrary Resource Sharing Groups</title>
<link rev="made" href="mailto:mcurrent@carleton.edu"> 
<META HTTP-EQUIV="Expires" CONTENT="01 Sep 1997">
<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">
</head>

<body>
<h2 align=center>Interlibrary Resource Sharing Groups</h2>
<p>
The Carleton College Library is a member of several different interlibrary resource sharing groups:
<dl>
<dt><a href="http://www.oclc.org/">OCLC Online Computer Library Center</a>
<dd> Furthering access to the world's information and reducing information costs are OCLC's major goals. Founded in 1967, OCLC pioneered the computer revolution in libraries when it introduced a computer system that enabled libraries to rapidly and efficiently catalog books and order custom-printed catalog cards. Today, OCLC provides a spectrum of services to over 22,000 libraries and their users in 63 countries.</dd>

<p>
<dt>
<a
href="http://www-MINITEX.lib.umn.edu/">MINITEX Library Information
Network</a>
<dd>
The MINITEX Library Information Network is a program of the 
Minnesota Higher Education Coordinating Board (HECB) with the 
mission of facilitating resource sharing among libraries and 
reducing the cost of providing access to information for residents 
throughout Minnesota, North Dakota, and South Dakota.  
<p>
<dt>
<a href="/obegroup/obe.html">Oberlin Group</a>
<dd>
The Oberlin Group is an affiliation of library directors from over sixty highly-competitive liberal arts colleges in the United States. This affiliation was nurtured by Bill Moffett, former library director at Oberlin College in Oberlin, Ohio, hence the name of the group. Mr. Moffett believed it would be benefitial for library directors at these various institutions to share common interests and concerns in order to better fulfill their missions.
</dd>
<p>
<dt>
SELS - SouthEast Library System
<dd>
The multi-county multi-type library system for the following Minnesota counties: Dodge, Fillmore, Freeborn, Goodhue, Houston, Mower, Olmsted, Rice, Steele, Wabasha, Winona
</dd>
<p>
<DT><A HREF="http://www.copyright.com/">Copyright Clearance Center</A>
<DD>
Copyright Clearance Center (CCC) is a not-for-profit organization created at the suggestion of Congress to help organizations like Carleton comply with U.S. copyright law. Through its collective licensing programs, CCC provides authorized users with a lawful means for making photocopies from its repertoire of more than 1.75 million titles. 
</dd>


</dl>




