<head>
<title>Commercial Document Suppliers</title>
<link rev="made" href="mailto:mcurrent@carleton.edu"> 
<META HTTP-EQUIV="Expires" CONTENT="01 Oct 1997">
<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">
</head>

<body>
<h2 align=center>Commercial Document Suppliers</h2>

<p>The InterLibrary Services office can obtain materials for you from virtually any library in North America, usually within 7-10 days.  (On rare occasions requests can take much longer to fill.)

<p>
If you cannot obtain what you need through ILS, or if you <em>must</em> obtain what you need in fewer than 7 days, and you're also willing to spend a little money to get it, you may wish to turn to a commercial document supplier.

<p>This page provides information about major document suppliers who would be happy to do business with you.
<hr>
<h3 align=center>Suppliers of virtually any document:</h3>
<dl>

<dt>UMI <strong><a href="http://www.umi.com/infostore/">InfoStore</a> </strong>
<dd>Can supply copies of virtually any journal article, dissertation, technical report, conference proceeding, or any other document.
<p> 
<dt>KR <strong><a href="http://www.dialog.com/dialog/krinfo/source-one/sourc1.html">SourceOne</a> </strong>
<dd>Delivers all kinds of documents, including patents, journal articles, proceedings, standards, and more. 
<p>
<dt> <strong><a href="http://www.ebscodoc.com/">EBSCOdoc</a> </strong>
<dd>A full service document delivery company. Can provide any document in the public domain, including article photocopies and book purchases.
<p>
<dt> <strong><a href="http://portico.bl.uk/dsc/">British Library Document Supply Centre</a> </strong>
<dd>BLDSC provides a rapid and comprehensive document delivery service to researchers and scholars in all kinds of organizations. Though particularly strong in science, technology and medicine, the BLDSC collects material in all subject areas. 
</dl>

<hr>
<h3 align=center>Suppliers of articles from a broad range of journals:</h3>
<dl>

<dt>CARL <strong><a href="http://www.carl.org/uncover/">UnCover</a></strong>
<dd>An online article delivery service, a table of contents database, and a keyword index to nearly 17,000 periodicals. 
<p>
<dt>ISI <strong><a href="http://www.isinet.com/prodserv/tga/tgadoc.html">The Genuine Article</a> </strong>
<dd>Provides five-year, full-text article coverage from the 7000+ titles covered by ISI's multidisciplinary database offering users access to a comprehensive collection of the world's scholarly science, social sciences, and arts and humanities journals.
</dl>
<hr>
<h3 align=center>Field-Specific Document Suppliers:</h3>
<dl>
<dt> <strong><a href="http://www.edrs.com/">ERIC Document Reproduction Service</a> </strong>
<dd>EDRS is the document delivery component of the Educational Resources Information Center (ERIC).  The ERIC database is the world's largest index to journal articles and documents in education.
<p>
<dt> <strong><a href="http://www.fedworld.gov/ntis/">National Technical Information Service</a> </strong>
<dd>NTIS is the official resource for government-sponsored U.S. and worldwide scientific, technical, engineering, and business-related information.
<p>
<dt> <strong><a href="http://info.cas.org/Support/dds.html">Chemical Abstracts Service Document Detective Service</a> </strong>
<dd>CAS DDS provides print copies of documents, journal articles, patents, and dissertations. Available material extends beyond what is selected for CAS databases and publications. 
<p>
<dt> <strong><a href="http://www.ei.org/">Engineering Information Inc.</a> </strong>
<dd>Ei Document Delivery Service can provide virtually any article or conference paper in the field of engineering.
<p>
<dt><strong><a href="http://www.individual.com/">Individual, Inc.</a></strong>
<dd>Supplies articles from over 350 wire services and other sources covered in the BusinessNews database on FirstSearch.
<p> 
<dt> <strong><a href="http://www.cisti.nrc.ca/cisti/cisti.html">Canada Institute for Scientific and Technical Information</a> </strong>
<dd>Copies or loans are available from CISTI's collection of journals, books, conference proceedings and technical reports.  Scientific conference proceedings are a specialty.

</dl>

