<head>
<title>Reference Desk</title>
</head>
<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">
<center><H1>Reference Desk</H1></center>
<p>
If you need help or advice in using library resources at Carleton College, your first 
stop should be at the <strong>Reference Desk</strong>, located in the Gould Library, 
level 4, near the CD-ROM workstations.  Telephone requests for reference assistance
can be made to the Reference Desk number at <STRONG>646-4264</STRONG>.
<P>
During the academic year, a professional librarian is normally available to help you at the 
Reference Desk during the following times:
<PRE>
<STRONG>
                 Monday-Thursday            10-noon   1-5 p.m.  7-10 p.m.

                 Friday                     10-noon   1-5 p.m.

                 Sunday                     1-5 p.m.  7-10 p.m.

</STRONG>
</PRE>
If you have complex or in-depth information needs, feel free to contact one of our 
<A HREF="/staff/staffdir.html#ref">professional staff</A> directly for consultation by
appointment.  
<P>
During the summer and break periods, the Reference Desk is not staffed.  However, feel 
free to ask a member of our professional staff for help.  Librarians' offices are 
located along the west end of level 4, near the Reference Desk.
<P>
