<HEAD>
<TITLE>About These HTML Exercises
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">
<hr size=7>
<CENTER><H1>About These HTML Exercises</H1></CENTER>

<p>

You do not have to re-key all the text in these exercises.  
Simply copy and paste the text into your text editor.  Then add tags where you believe they belong.
Follow the answer links to compare your work.
<p>
<HR SIZE=3>
<P>
<A HREF="exercise1.html">Go to Exercise 1,</A> 
<A HREF="exercise2.html">2,</A>
<A HREF="exercise3.html">3,</A>
<A HREF="exercise4.html">4,</A>
<A HREF="exercise5.html">5,</A>
<A HREF="exercise6.html">6,</A>
<A HREF="exercise7.html">7,</A>
<A HREF="exercise8.html">8,</A>
<A HREF="exercise9.html">9,</A>
<A HREF="exercise10.html">10,</A>
<A HREF="exercise11.html">11</A>
