<HEAD>
<TITLE>Carleton College Library HTML: Exercise 5 - Nested Lists
</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">
<HR SIZE=7>
<CENTER><H1>Exercise 5 - Nested Lists</H1></CENTER>
<P>
This exercise includes use of a <A HREF="exercise1.html#head">header</A> and a <A HREF="#nest">nested list</A>.
<P>
<HR SIZE=3>
<P>
<H3><A NAME="nest">Creating Nested Lists:</A></H3>
"Nested lists" simply means lists <STRONG>within</STRONG> lists.  It's possible to have:
<UL>
<LI>lists within 
	<UL><LI>lists within
			<UL><LI>lists within
					<UL><LI>lists within
							<UL><LI>lists within
									<UL><LI>lists, etc.
									</UL>
							</UL>
					</UL>
			</UL>
	</UL>

</UL>
<HR SIZE=3>
<P>
<HR ALIGN="center" WIDTH=50%>
<CENTER>Write HTML required to produce:</CENTER>
<HR ALIGN="center" WIDTH=50%>
<P>

<H1>U.S. Senators for Five Upper Midwestern States</H2>
<Ol>
<LI>North Dakota
	<Ul>
	<LI>Sen. Kent Conrad (D)
	<LI>Sen. Byron L. Dorgan (D)
	</UL>
<LI>South Dakota
	<UL>
	<LI>? (D)
	<LI>Sen. Thomas A. Daschle (D)
	</UL>
<LI>Iowa
	<UL>
	<LI>Sen. Charles E. Grassley (R)
	<LI>Sen. Tom Harkin (D)
	</UL>
<LI>Wisconsin
	<UL>
	<LI>Sen. Herb Kohl (D)
	<LI>Sen. Russell D. Feingold (D)
	</UL>
<LI>Minnesota
	<UL>
	<LI>Sen. Paul D. Wellstone (DFL)
	<LI>Sen. Rod Grams (R)
	</UL>
</OL>
<P>
<HR SIZE=3>
