<HEAD>
<TITLE>Carleton College Library HTML and Web Site Resource: Learning about Graphics
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">
<hr size=7>
<CENTER><H1>Learning About Graphics</H1></CENTER>
<HR>
<P>
<UL>
		<DL>
			<DT><A HREF="http://www.algonet.se/~dip/indexa-z.htm">Digital Picture Guide</A>
			<DD>by Thomas Lindstr&ouml;m from Kolmarden, Sweden.  This resource is a guide to making images
			    look good in digital media.  Caution:  The site is very graphics-intensive.  Therefore, pages
			    download slowly.  Also, page backgrounds are garish.
			<P>
			<DT><A HREF="http://www.reiworld.com/royalef/toolbox.htm">GIF Animation on the World Wide Web</A>
			<DD>from the <A HREF="http://www.reiworld.com/royalef/galframe.htm">1st Internet Gallery of GIF Animation</A>.
			<P>
			<DT><A HREF="http://www.webdiner.com/annexe/gif89/snowstp1.htm">
			     Gif89A Animations Tutorial</A>
			<DD>from the <A HREF="http://www.webdiner.com/utensil.htm">Web Diner</A>.
			<P>
			<DT><A HREF="http://www.widearea.co.uk/designer/compress.html">GIFs and JPEGs</A>
			<DD>excerpt from an article appearing in the online magazine 
			    <A HREF="http://www.widearea.co.uk/designer/">Creating Graphics for the Web</A>.
			<P>
            <DT><A HREF="http://www.public.iastate.edu/~stark/gutil_sv.html">The Graphic Utilities' Site & Version FAQ</A>
			<DD>by Brian Stark, and undergraduate student at Iowa State University.  This resource lists software tools
			    needed to handle various graphical file formats.  Use it to answer:  1) What is the newest version of 
			    a particular graphic utility?  2) On what ftp site can this version be found?  3) What types of files 
			    does it handle?
			<P>
			<DT><A HREF="http://www59.metronet.com/dev/graphics.shtml">Graphics</A>
			<DD>from the <A HREF="http://www59.metronet.com/dev/">Web Engineer's Toolbox</A>.
			<P>
			<DT><A HREF="http://www.execpc.com/inp/imaging.html">Imaging</A>
			<DD>From InterNetworking Publishing, a commercial firm.  This source is a good introductions to the issues
			    involved in handling images on Web pages.
			<P>
		    <DT><A HREF="graphicstop10.html">Top 10 Rules for Creating Graphics for the Web</A>
			<DD>According to Susan Jurist, visual arts librarian at the University of California, San Diego.  Very easier
			    to understand for the beginner.
			<P>
		    <DT><A HREF="http://www.cica.indiana.edu/graphics/image.formats.html">Understanding Image File Formats</A>
			<DD>From the Center for Innovative Computer Applications at Indiana University.  This resource contains a 
			    list of many of the most common image file formats, as well as information about what software supports 
			    each format.  Writing level is rather technical. 
			<P>
		    <DT><A HREF="http://www.cowan.edu.au/ecuwis/docs/ecudocs/images.html">Using Graphics in your HTML</A>
			<DD>A Guide from Edith Cowan University in Perth, Australia.  Tends to empahsize Windows over Macintosh.
			<P>
		</DL>

</UL>
<P>
