<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Carleton College Library HTML and Web Site Resource: Netscape Specific HTML Extensions and HTML 3.0
</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">
<hr size=7>
<CENTER><H1>Netscape Specific HTML Extensions and HTML 3.0</H2></CENTER>

Netscape Communications Corporation started it all by introducing additions beyond the
HTML 2.0 specifications that could be read by their browser, which is used by about 70% of those 
browsing the Web.  Now Microsoft has <STRONG>its</STRONG> HTML extensions 
and the HTML 3.0 specification is under discussion.<p>

Browsers which do not "understand" Netscape HTML enhancements will skip over them.
Be aware, however, that your pages will not look the same on other browsers.<p>

Another warning:  Netscape's bells and whistles can be a dangerous tool in the hands
of those without a sense of aesthetics.  Check the <A HREF="http://www.meat.com/netscape_hos.html">
"Netscape Enhanced Hall of Shame"</A> for (good and bad) examples.<p>

<h4>This page is a summary of basic Netscape enhancements.  For more information, see 
<A HREF="advancenetscape.html">Netscape HTML Enhancements for Graphics</A> in this tutorial, Netscape's <A HREF="http://www.netscape.com/assist/net_sites/html_extensions.html">
Extensions to HTML 2.0</A> and <A HREF="http://www.netscape.com/assist/net_sites/html_extensions_3.html">
Extensions to HTML 3.0</A>,
and <A HREF="http://www.netscape.com/assist/net_sites/impact_docs/index.html">High Impact Documents</A> pages, and
the proposed <A HREF="http://www.hp.co.uk/people/dsr/html3/Contents.html">HTML 3.0 specifications</A>.
</H4>
<P>
<HR size=3>
<P>
<H3>Basic Netscape Enhancements include:</h3>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="#list">control over "list" elements</A>
<LI><A HREF="#image">image:</A> <UL>
	<LI><A HREF="#imalign">alignment</A>
	<LI><A HREF="#imsize">sizing</A>
	<LI><A HREF="#imborder">borders</A>
	<LI><A HREF="#imspace">spacing</A>
	</UL>
<LI><A HREF="#center">centering</A>
<LI><A HREF="#font">fonts</A>
<LI><A HREF="#hr">horizontal rule options</A>
<LI><A HREF="#char">character formats</A>
<LI><A HREF="#foot">footnotes</A>
<LI><A HREF="#sound">sounds</A>
<LI><A HREF="#color">colors</A>
<LI><A HREF="#align">alignment</A>
<LI><A HREF="#marq">marquees</A>
<LI><A HREF="#ban">banners</A>
<LI><A HREF="#fig">figures</A>
</UL>
<br>

</UL>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="list">List Elements</A></H3>
<DL>

<DT><B><TT>&lt;UL&gt;</tt></B>
<DD>By adding a TYPE tag to the UL element,
    you can specify whether you want a TYPE=disc, TYPE=circle, or TYPE=square
    as your bullet.
<P>
<DT><B><TT>&lt;OL&gt;</tt></B>
<DD>By adding a TYPE tag to the OL element, you can specify
    whether the want your list items marked with: capital letters (TYPE=A),
    small letters (TYPE=a), large roman numerals (TYPE=I), small roman
    numerals (TYPE=i), or the default numbers (TYPE=1).
<P>
   By adding a START tag to the OL element, you can specify that
   the list should start at a value other than 1. 
   Always use an arabic number to specify the value.  The TYPE tag will
   adjust the display.  START=5 will
   display either an 'E', 'e', 'V', 'v', or '5' based on the TYPE tag.
<P>
<DT><B><TT>&lt;LI&gt;</tt></B>
<DD>Adding the

    TYPE tag to the LI element takes the same values
    as either UL or OL depending on the type of list you are in, and
    changes the list type for that item, and all subsequent items.
    You can also change the count in an ordered list by using a VALUE element.
</DL>
<HR>

<H3><A NAME="image">Basic Image Enhancements</A></H3>
<DL>

<DT><A NAME="imalign"></A><noBR><B><TT>&lt;IMG ALIGN=left&gt;</tt> and <tt>&lt;IMG ALIGN=right&gt;</tt></B></noBR>
<dd>ALIGN=left moves the image into the next available space at the left margin.
Subsequent text will wrap around the right hand side of that image.
ALIGN=right aligns the image with the right margin and the text
wraps to the left.
<P>

<DT><A NAME="imsize"></A><B><TT>&lt;IMG WIDTH=value HEIGHT=value&gt;</TT></B></noBR>
<DD>The WIDTH and HEIGHT tags (units=pixels) speed up display of the document, but also 
    can be used to distort images.<p>
<P>
<DT><A NAME="imborder"></A><B><TT>&lt;IMG BORDER=value&gt;</tt></B>
<DD>This controls the thickness of the border
    around an image displayed.  Warning: setting BORDER=0 on images that
    are also part of anchors may confuse your users as they are used to a 
    colored border indicating an image is an anchor.
<P>
<DT><A NAME="imspace"></A><B><TT>&lt;IMG VSPACE=value HSPACE=value&gt;</tt></B>
<DD>VSPACE controls the vertical space above and below the image, while
    HSPACE controls the horizontal space to the left and right of the image.
</DL>
<HR>

<H3><A NAME="center">Centering</A></H3>
<DL>
<DT><b><TT>&lt;CENTER&gt; and &lt;CENTER&gt;</b></b>
<DD>Everything (images and text) between these tags will be centered in
the browser window.
</DL>
<HR>

<H3><A NAME="font">Fonts</A></H3>
<DL>
<DT><B><TT>&lt;FONT SIZE=value&gt;</TT></B> <DD>Yo<FONT
SIZE="+1">u</FONT> c<FONT SIZE="+2">a</FONT><FONT SIZE="+4">n</FONT> <FONT
SIZE=7>c<FONT SIZE=6>h<FONT SIZE=5>a<FONT SIZE=4>n<FONT SIZE=3>g<FONT
SIZE=2>e</FONT></FONT></FONT></FONT></FONT></FONT> the FONT size.  Valid
values range from 1-7.  The default FONT size is 3.  The value given to size
can optionally have a '+' or '-' character in front of it to specify that it
is relative the the document baseFONT.  The default baseFONT is 3, and can be
changed with the BASEFONT element.<p>

<DT><B><TT>&lt;BASEFONT SIZE=value&gt;</tt></B>
<DD>This changes the size of the BASEFONT that all relative FONT
changes are based on.  It defaults to 3, and has a valid range of 1-7.
<P>
<DT><B><TT>&lt;FONT COLOR=#rrggbb&gt;</tt> and <tt>&lt;FONT FACE="name [,name2] [,name3] "&gt; </tt></b>
<DD>COLOR sets the hex color of the text.  FACE sets the font.  A list can be specified, which will try
    alternates if the font is not installed on the user's system.  If no specified fonts are available,
    the default font will be used. 
</DL>
<HR>

<H3><A NAME="hr">Horizontal Rules</A></H3>
<DL>
<DT><B><TT>&lt;HR SIZE=number&gt;</tt></B>
<DD>The SIZE tag lets  you indicate the thickness of the rule.

<P>
<DT><B><TT>&lt;HR WIDTH=number|percent&gt;</tt></B>
<DD>The WIDTH tag lets you specify an exact width in pixels, or a relative
    width measured in percent of document width.
<P>
<DT><B><TT>&lt;HR ALIGN=left|right|center&gt;</tt></B>
<DD>These tags allow you to specify the alignment of the rule.
<P>
<DT><B><TT>&lt;HR NOSHADE&gt;</tt></B>
<DD>Use the NOSHADE tag when you want a solid bar without any fancy
    shading.
</DL> 
<HR>

<H3><A NAME="char"></A>Character Formats</H3><UL>
	<LI><b><tt>&lt;BIG&gt;</tt> <big>and</big> <tt>&lt;/BIG&gt;</tt></b>
	<LI><b><tt>&lt;SMALL&gt;</tt> <small>and</small> <tt>&lt;/SMALL&gt;</tt></b>
	<LI><b><tt>&lt;SUB&gt;</tt> <sub>and</sub> <tt>&lt;/SUB&gt;</tt></b>
	<LI><b><tt>&lt;SUP&gt;</tt> <sup>and</sup> <tt>&lt;/SUP&gt;</tt></b>
	<LI>HTML 3
	</UL>


<HR>

	
<A NAME="sound"><H3>Sounds</H3>
<ul>
<LI><b><tt>&lt;BGSOUND SRC="URL"&gt; or &lt;BGSOUND SRC="URL" LOOP=5&gt;</tt></b><UL>
	<LI>Hear a background sound when you open a page or
	<LI>Gives pages a "soundtrack"
	<LI><tt><B>LOOP=n</B></tt> or <tt><B>LOOP=INFINITE</B></tt>
	<LI>Takes .wav, .au or .mid format sounds
	<LI>IExporer
	</UL><br>
</UL>
<HR>
	
<A NAME="color"><H3>Colors</H3>	
<ul>
<LI><b><tt>&lt;BODY BACKGROUND="URL"&gt;</tt></b><UL>
	<LI>Specifies a background picture, which is tiled
	<LI>HTML 3 (supported by Netscape, IExporer)
	</UL><br>
	
<LI><b><tt>&lt;BODY BGCOLOR=#rrggbb&gt;</tt></b><UL>
	<LI>Sets a background color the the page
	<LI>rrggbb is the hexadecimal number
	<LI>Netscape, supported by IExporer
	</UL><br>
	
<LI><b><tt>&lt;BODY BACKGROUND="URL" BGPROPERTIES=FIXED&gt;</tt></b><UL>
	<LI>Specifies a watermark, a background picture that does not scroll
	<LI>IExporer
	</UL><br>
	
<LI><b><tt>&lt;BODY TEXT=#rrggbb LINK=#rrggbb ALINK=#rrggbb VLINK=#rrggbb&gt;</tt></b><UL>
	<LI>Sets the text, link, active link and visited link colors
	<LI>rrggbb is the hexadecimal number
	<LI>Netscape
	</UL><br>
</UL>
<HR>

<A NAME="align"><H3>Alignments</H3>	
<ul>
<LI><b><tt>&lt;BODY LEFTMARGIN=n&gt;</tt></b><UL>
	<LI>Specifies the left margin of the body of the page.
	<LI>Set to "0" the left margin will be on the left edge
	<LI>in pixels
	<LI>IExporer
	</UL><br>
	

<LI><b><tt>&lt;BODY TOPMARGIN=n&gt;</tt></b><UL>
	<LI>Specifies the top margin of the body of the page.
	<LI>Set to "0" the left margin will be on the top edge
	<LI>in pixels
	<LI>IExporer
	</UL><br>
	
<LI><b><tt>&lt;BR CLEAR=LEFT, RIGHT or ALL&gt;</tt></b><UL>
	<LI>Inserts vertical space so the next text displayed will be past floating images
	<LI>HTML 3
	</UL><br>

<LI><B><TT>&lt;P ALIGN=CENTER, RIGHT, LEFT or JUSTIFY&gt; and &lt;/P&gt;</tt></B><UL>
	<LI>HTML 3
	</UL>
</UL>

<HR>

<H3><A NAME="marq">Marquees</H3>
<ul>
<LI><B><TT>&lt;MARQUEE&gt; and &lt;/MARQUEE&gt;</tt></B><UL>
	<LI>Specifies scrolling text
	<LI><TT><B>ALIGN=TOP, MIDDLE</B></TT> or <TT><B>BOTTOM</B></TT> aligns text with marquee
	<LI><TT>BGCOLOR=#rrggbb</TT> specifies background color for marquee
	<LI><TT><B>DIRECTION=LEFT</B></TT> or <TT><B>RIGHT</B></TT> specifies which direction the text should scroll
	<LI><TT><B>HEIGHT=n</B></TT> or <TT><B>HEIGHT=n%</B></TT> Height of marquee in pixels or as a % of screen height
	<LI><TT><B>HSPACE</B></TT> specifies horizontal margins, in pixels.
	<LI><TT><B>LOOP=n</B></TT> or <TT><B>LOOP=INFINITE</B></TT> Specifies how many times marquee will loop
	<LI><TT><B>SCROLLAMOUNT=n</B></TT> Specifies number of pixels between each draw of text. (Big number=fast scroll)
	<LI><TT><B>SCROLLDELAY=n</B></TT> Specifies of milliseconds between each draw of marquee text (Big number=slow scroll)
	<LI><TT><B>VSPACE</B></TT> specifies vertical margins, in pixels
	<LI><TT><B>WIDTH=n</B></TT> or <TT><B>WIDTH=n%</B></TT> specifies width of the marquee
	<LI>IExplorer
	</UL><br>
</UL>
<HR>

<H3><A NAME="ban">Banners</H3>
<UL>
<LI><TT><b>&lt;BANNER&gt;</tt></b> and <tt><b>&lt;/BANNER&gt;</tt></B><UL>
	<LI>For Information that doesn't scroll (i.e., company logos)
	<LI>HTML 3
	</UL>
</UL>
<HR>

<H3><A NAME="fig">Figures</H3>
<UL>
<LI><TT><b>&lt;FIG SRC="URL"&gt; &lt;OVERLAY SRC="URL"&gt; &lt;CAPTION&gt; &lt;/CAPTION&gt; &lt;CREDIT&gt; &lt;/CREDIT&gt; &lt;/FIG&gt;</b></tt>
	<LI><TT><b>FIG</tt></B> specifies a graphic
	<LI><TT><b>OVERLAY</tt></B> specifies a graphic to overlay the figure (i.e., a map outline overlays an aerial photo)
	<LI><TT><b>CAPTION </tt></B> specifies a caption (description) for the graphic
	<LI><TT><b>CREDIT </tt></B> specifies the creator the graphic
	<LI>This tag is also used in client-side image maps
	<LI>HTML 3
	</UL>
<P>
<HR>
<P>
