<HR SIZE=7>
<CENTER><H1>Netscape HTML Enhancements for Graphics</H1></CENTER>
<HR SIZE=3>
<P>
Netscape Communications Corporation has introduced many additions to HTML that 
can be read by their browser, which is used by about 70% of those browsing the Web.
Netscape is working to have these additions included in the HTML 3.0 specification.<p>

Browsers which do not "understand" Netscape HTML enhancements will skip over them.
Be aware, however, that your pages will not look the same on other browsers.<p>

Another warning:  Netscape's bells and whistles can be a dangerous tool in the hands
of those without a sense of aesthetics.  Check the <A HREF="http://www.meat.com/netscape_hos.html">
"Netscape Enhanced Hall of Shame"</A> for (good and bad) examples.<p>

<H4>This page is a summary of basic Netscape enhancements.  For more information, see 
<A HREF="netscape.html">Netscape Specific HTML Enhancements and HTML 3.0</A> in this tutorial, Netscape's <A HREF="http://www.netscape.com/assist/net_sites/html_extensions.html">
Extensions to HTML 2.0</A> and <A HREF="http://www.netscape.com/assist/net_sites/html_extensions_3.html">
Extensions to HTML 3.0</A>,
and <A HREF="http://www.netscape.com/assist/net_sites/impact_docs/index.html">High Impact Documents</A> pages, and
the proposed <A HREF="http://www.hp.co.uk/people/dsr/html3/Contents.html">HTML 3.0 specifications</A>.
</H4>
<HR size=3>
<H3>Advanced Netscape HTML Enhancements include:</H3>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="#tables">Tables</A>
<LI><A HREF="#back">Backgrounds</A>
<LI><A HREF="#fore">Foregrounds</A>
<LI><A HREF="#imsize">Image Size</A>
<LI><A HREF="#flips">Low/high resolution flips</A>
</UL>
<HR>


<CENTER>
<H3>
<A NAME="tables"></A>TABLE TAGS<br>
<A HREF="table.html">A Simple Table</A>
</H3>
</CENTER>

<DL>

<DT><FONT SIZE=+1><B>&lt;TABLE ...&gt;&lt;/TABLE&gt;</B></FONT>
<DD>This is the main tag for all the other table tags.<br><UL>
	<LI>Attributes: BORDER. <B>&lt;TABLE BORDER=2&gt;</b>
    <LI>(By default tables have no borders.)</UL>
<P>
<DT><FONT SIZE=+1><B>&lt;TR ...&gt;&lt;/TR&gt;</B></FONT>
<DD>Table Row  <br><UL>
	<LI>Attributes: <TT>ALIGN</TT> and <TT>VALIGN</TT> which, if
    specified, become the default alignments for all cells in this row.</UL>
<P>
<DT><FONT SIZE="+1"><B>&lt;TD ...&gt;&lt;/TD&gt;</B></FONT>
<DD>Table Data <UL>
	<LI>specifies a standard table data cell
    <LI>must appear within table rows  
    <LI>can contain other HTML tags
    <LI>default alignment left</UL>
<P>
<DT><FONT SIZE="+1"><B>&lt;TH ...&gt;&lt;/TH&gt;</B></FONT>
<DD>Table header<br><UL>
	<LI>identical to data cells except:<UL>
		<LI><B>bold</B> 
		<LI>default <TT>ALIGN</TT>=center</UL></UL>
<P>
<DT><FONT SIZE="+1"><B>&lt;CAPTION ...&gt;&lt;/CAPTION&gt;</B></FONT>
<DD>Table caption<ul>
	<LI>inside the <TT>TABLE</TT> but not inside table rows or cells
	<LI>default is <TT>ALIGN</TT>=top but can be set to <TT>ALIGN</TT>=bottom
	<LI>can contain other HTML tags
	<LI>always horizontally centered with respect to the table
</UL>
</DL>

<HR SIZE=4>


<H4>
TABLE ATTRIBUTES
</H4>

<DL>

<DT><FONT SIZE="+1"><B>BORDER</B></FONT>
<DD>used in <TT>TABLE</TT> tag.  <UL>
	<LI>present = borders drawn around all table cells
	<LI>absent = no borders </UL>
<P>

<DT><FONT SIZE="+1"><B>ALIGN</B></FONT>
<DD>inside a <TT>CAPTION</TT> <UL>
	<LI>controls whether the caption appears above or below the table
	<LI>values = <B>top</B> or <B>bottom</B>
	<LI>default = top</UL>
<P>
<DD>inside a <TT>TR</TT>, <TT>TH</TT>, or <TT>TD</TT><UL>
    <LI>controls horizontal alignment of text inside the table cell(s)
    <LI>values = <B>left</B>, <B>center</B>, and <B>right</B></UL>
<P>

<DT><FONT SIZE="+1"><B>VALIGN</B></FONT>
<DD>inside a <TT>TR</TT>, <TT>TH</TT>, or <TT>TD</TT><UL>
    <LI>controls vertical alignment of text inside the table cell(s)
    <LI>can also specify that all the cells in the row should
    be vertically aligned to the same baseline
    <LI>values = <B>top</B>, <B>middle</B> <B>bottom</B>, and <B>baseline</B></UL>
<P>

<DT><FONT SIZE="+1"><B>NOWRAP</B></FONT>
<DD>inside any table cell (<TT>TH</TT> or <TT>TD</TT>)<UL>
    <LI>lines within this cell cannot be broken to fit the width of the cell
    <LI>can result in excessively wide cells</UL>
<P>

<DT><FONT SIZE="+1"><B>COLSPAN</B></FONT>
<DD>inside any table cell (<TT>TH</TT> or <TT>TD</TT>)<UL>
	<LI>specifies how many columns of the table this cell should span
    <LI>default <TT>COLSPAN</TT> for any cell is 1</UL>
<P>

<DT><FONT SIZE="+1"><B>ROWSPAN</B></FONT>
<DD>can appear in any table cell (<TT>TH</TT> or <TT>TD</TT>)<UL>
    <LI>specifies how many rows of the table this cell should span
    <LI>default <TT>ROWSPAN</TT> for any cell is 1</UL>

</DL>

<HR SIZE=4>


<H4>
ADDITIONAL ATTRIBUTES
</H4>

<DL>

<DT><FONT SIZE="+1"><B>BORDER</B>=&lt;value&gt;</FONT>
<DD>controls border thickness
<UL><LI>allows emphasis by setting border to higher number
	<LI>helpful when nesting tables (outer table can have thicker border)
	<LI>setting border to zero saves space (visually)</UL>
<P>

<DT><FONT SIZE="+1"><B>CELLSPACING</B>=&lt;value&gt;</FONT>
<DD>amount of space inserted between table cells<UL>
	<LI>default = 2</UL>
<P>

<DT><FONT SIZE="+1"><B>CELLPADDING</B>=&lt;value&gt;</FONT>
<DD>amount of space between border and contents of the cell
<UL><LI>default = 1</UL><p>

<CENTER>
&lt;TABLE BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0&gt;
</CENTER>

<P>

    gives the most compact table possible.
<P>

<DT><FONT SIZE="+1"><B>WIDTH</B>=&lt;value_or_percent&gt;</FONT>
<DD>When used with TABLE tag
<UL><LI>describes desired width of this table
	<LI>absolute width in pixels or 
	<LI>percentage of document width</UL>
<P>
<DD>When used with <TT>TH</TT> or <TT>TD</TT> tag<ul>
	<LI>describes the desired width of the cell
	<LI>absolute width in pixels or
	<LI>percentage of table width</UL>
</DL>

<HR SIZE=4>



<CENTER><A NAME="back"></A><H3>BACKGROUNDS</H3></CENTER>

<H4>BODY BACKGROUND</H4>

Specifies an URL pointing to an image that is used as the background for a document.
In Netscape 1.1, this image is used to tile the background.

<h4>Format:</h4>
<CENTER>
<NOBR><TT>&lt;BODY BACKGROUND="metal/brushed_aluminum.gif"&gt;</TT><WBR>Document here</WBR><TT>&lt;/BODY&gt;</TT></NOBR><BR>
</CENTER>
<P>
Background swatches can be found on this <A HREF="http://www.netscape.com/assist/net_sites/bg/backgrounds.html">Netscape page</A>.
</P>

<H4>BACKGROUND COLOR</H4>

This attribute (not currently proposed in HTML 3.0) allows you to specify the color
of the background without having to load an image.

<h4>Format:</h4>
<CENTER>
<NOBR><TT>&lt;BODY BGCOLOR="#rrggbb"&gt;</TT><WBR>Document here</WBR><TT>&lt;/BODY&gt;</TT></NOBR><BR>
</CENTER>
<P>
Where <TT>"#rrggbb"</TT> is a hexadecimal red-green-blue triplet used to
specify the background color.
<P>
Color swatches can be found in this <A HREF=" http://www.infi.net/wwwimages/colorindex.html">guide</A>. <p>
To get the "hex" for any RGB color generated in Photoshop, check 
<A HREF="http://www.novalink.com/pei/hex/hex.html">this site</A>.<p>
<HR SIZE=4>

<CENTER>
<H3>
<A NAME="fore"></A>FOREGROUNDS
</H3>
</CENTER>

<H4>BODY TEXT</h4>

To control the color (again the hexadecimal red-green-blue triplet)
of all the document text not colored to indicate a link.<p>

<h4>Format:</h4>

<CENTER>
<NOBR><TT>&lt;BODY TEXT="#rrggbb"&gt;</TT><WBR>Document here</WBR><TT>&lt;/BODY&gt;</TT></NOBR><BR>
</CENTER>
<P>

<H4>LINKED TEXT</h4>

These attributes let you control the coloring of link text.  <UL>
	<LI><TT>LINK</TT> = link
	<LI><TT>VLINK</TT> = visited link
	<LI><TT>ALINK</TT> = active link
	<LI>defaults are <TT>LINK</TT>=blue, <TT>VLINK</TT>=purple, and <TT>ALINK</TT>=red</UL>

<H4>Format:</h4>

<CENTER>
<NOBR><TT>&lt;BODY LINK="#rrggbb" VLINK="#rrggbb" ALINK="#rrggbb"&gt;</TT><WBR>Document here</WBR><TT>&lt;/BODY&gt;</TT></NOBR><BR>
</CENTER>
<P>

<H4>Example of Complete Tag</h4

<CENTER>
<TT>&lt;BODY BGCOLOR="#000000" TEXT="#F0F0F0" LINK="#FFFF00" VLINK="#22AA22" ALINK="#0077FF"&gt;</TT>Document here</WBR><TT>&lt;/BODY&gt;</TT>

</CENTER>

<H4>Additional Notes:</h4><UL>
	<LI>Set colors once in the document (you can't change colors in the middle)
	<LI>Setting a background image slows the perceived speed of document load
	<LI>If <B>Auto Load Images</b> is set to OFF, background images will not load<UL>
		<LI>if background image does not load, and no <TT>BGCOLOR</TT> was specified,
			text color attributes will be ignored.</UL></UL><p>


<HR SIZE=4>


<CENTER><A NAME="imsize"></A><B><H3>SPECIFYING IMAGE HEIGHT/WIDTH</h3>
</B></CENTER>

<UL>
<LI>attributes of the <CODE>IMG</CODE> tag
<LI>specified in pixels
<LI>specifying width and/or height different than the actual size distorts (scales) the image
<LI>format:

<PRE>
    &lt;IMG SRC="foo.gif" WIDTH=413 HEIGHT=356&gt;
</PRE>
</UL>


<HR SIZE=4>

<CENTER>
<H3><A NAME="flips"></A>
LOW/HIGH RESOLUTION FLIP
</H3>
</CENTER>

<UL>
<LI>loads low res image on first pass; loads high res on second pass
<LI>mix & match GIF and JPEG
<LI>can use width & height values
<LI>if images are different sizes and width/height are not specified,k second image is scaled
to fit the dimensions of the first.
<LI>format:

<PRE>
    &lt;IMG SRC="highres.gif" LOWSRC="lowres.jpg"&gt;
</PRE>
</UL>


Here are some examples from the Netscape site: <P>

<UL>
<LI> <CODE>LOWSRC</CODE> is a 7,752-byte JPEG; <CODE>SRC</CODE> is a
     113,164-byte non-interlaced GIF.  They are the same size, 360 by 398,
     and are not auto-scaled.  <A HREF="http://www.netscape.com/assist/net_sites/impact_docs/low1.html">Here.</A>
<LI> <CODE>LOWSRC</CODE> is a 16,721-byte JPEG; <CODE>SRC</CODE> is a
     113,469-byte JPEG.  They are the same size, 642 by 595,
     and are not auto-scaled.  <A HREF="http://www.netscape.com/assist/net_sites/impact_docs/low2.html">Here.</A>
<LI> <CODE>LOWSRC</CODE> is a 6,358-byte JPEG; <CODE>SRC</CODE> is a
     64,714-byte JPEG.  They are not the same size (the <CODE>LOWSRC</CODE>
     image is quite a bit smaller); the <CODE>HEIGHT</CODE> and 
     <CODE>WIDTH</CODE> values of the bigger image are given in the
     <CODE>IMG</CODE> tag, causing the smaller image to be scaled up.
     <A HREF="http://www.netscape.com/assist/net_sites/impact_docs/low3.html">Here.</A>
</UL>
<P>
<HR>
<P>
<CENTER><A HREF="netscape.html">Netscape Specific HTML Enhancements and HTML 3.0</A>
<P>
<A HREF="welcome.html">Main Menu</A></CENTER>
