<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Carleton College LiBRary HTML and Web Site Resource: Quality HTML Authoring
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">
<A NAME="contents">
<HR SIZE=7>
<CENTER><H1>Quality HTML Authoring</H1></CENTER>
<HR SIZE=3>
<OL>
<STRONG>
<LI><A HREF="#element">Essential Elements</A> of a well-designed page
<P> 
<LI><A HREF="#design">Design Consistency</A>
<P>
<LI><A HREF="#nav">Navigating with Buttons/Icons/Links</A>
<P>
<LI><A HREF="#type">Web Typography</A>
<P>
<LI><A HREF="#practical">Practical Considerations</A>
<P>
<LI><A HREF="#tricks">Tricks to Control Page Format</A>
<P>
<LI><A HREF="#val">Markup Validation</A>
</STRONG>
</OL>
<P>
Links to the <cit><A HREF="http://info.med.yale.edu/caim/StyleManual_Top.HTML">Yale C/AIM WWW Style Manual</A></cit> used by permission of its author, Patrick J. Lynch, MS.
<P>
<HR SIZE=3>
<H3><A NAME="element"></A><A HREF="http://info.med.yale.edu/caim/stylemanual/M_II_5.HTML">Essential Elements</A> of a well-designed page</h3>
<UL>
<LI>Headers<UL>
	<LI>Title - near the top, prominent, informative
	<LI>Subtitle, section title
	<LI>Navigational tool ("banner graphic")</UL>
<LI>Footers<UL>
	<LI>Author's name/institutional affiliation
	<LI>Link(s) to home page and/or related local pages
	<LI>Copyright marks, language, year
	<LI>Last revision date of the page (format: July 18, 1995)
	<LI>URL of document</UL>
<LI>Content<UL>
	<LI>Content overview at a glance
	<LI>Navigational options obvious
	<LI>Scope of the site clear</UL>
</UL>
</OL>
<p><em><A HREF="#contents">Return to Contents</A></em>
<HR SIZE=2>

<H3><A NAME="design"></A><A HREF="http://info.med.yale.edu/caim/stylemanual/M_II_1.HTML">Design Consistency</A></H3>
<UL>
<LI>Balance between text and graphics<UL>
	<LI>Consider the way the eye moves across the (dynamic) page
	<LI>Be aware of "white space"</UL>
<LI>Consistency in placement of navigational tools, functional text<UL>
	<LI>Practicality, predictability balance with visual sensation</UL>
<LI>Page Length
	<LI>Limit to 2 - 3 640x480 screens worth
	
</UL>
</OL>
<p><em><A HREF="#contents">Return to Contents</A></em>
<HR SIZE=2>

<H3><A NAME="nav"></A><A HREF="http://info.med.yale.edu/caim/stylemanual/M_II_8.HTML">Navigation</A>: ease and options</H3>
<UL>
<LI>Balance between text and graphics<UL>
	<LI>Embed hyperlinks in text sections
	<LI>Offer text navigation menus
	<LI>Include graphic navigation menus</UL>
<LI>Maximize Choice<UL>
	<LI>Hyperlinks as "active footnotes"
	<LI>Avoid hierarchical-only navigation
	<LI>Recognize the directional power of navigational tools</UL>
</UL>
</OL>
<p><em><A HREF="#contents">Return to Contents</A></em>
<HR SIZE=2>

<H3><A NAME="type"></A><A HREF="http://info.med.yale.edu/caim/stylemanual//M_II_10.HTML">Web Typography</A></H3>
<UL>
	<LI>Understand type as design element<UL>
		<LI>Strong contrast and distinctive Patterns
		<LI>Relationship of type and empty space</UL>
	<LI>Adding variety to text blocks:<UL>
		<LI><TT>&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;</TT>
		<LI>Lists
		<LI>Tables (Netscapism)</UL>
	<LI>Adding variety to text design:
		<LI>"Graphic" text
		<LI>Use of HTML Headings (duct tape)
		<LI>Character formatting
		<LI>Font size changes (Netscapism)</UL>
</UL>
</OL>
<p><em><A HREF="#contents">Return to Contents</A></em>
<HR SIZE=2>	
<H3><A NAME="practical"></A>Practical Considerations</H3>
<UL>
	<LI>Know your readership (if possible)
	<LI>Design for change<UL>
		<LI>"New" identifiers
		<LI>Modular construction
		<LI>Graphic backbones</UL>
	<LI>Keep file sizes ASAP
</UL>
</OL>
<p><em><A HREF="#contents">Return to Contents</A></em>
<HR SIZE=2>
	
<H3><A NAME="tricks"></A><A HREF="http://www.dsiegel.com/tips/">Tricks</A> to Control Page Format <font size=-1>(Inherently duct tape)</font></H3>
<UL>
	<LI>Single-pixel transparent gif
	<LI>Setting graphic size
	<LI>Left and right "margins"
	
</UL>
</OL>
<p><em><A HREF="#contents">Return to Contents</A></em>
<HR SIZE=2>
<H3><A NAME="val"><A HREF="http://www.charm.net/~web/Vlib/Providers/Validation.html">Markup Validation</A></h3>
<p><em><A HREF="#contents">Return to Contents</A></em>
<P>
<HR>
