<HEAD>
<TITLE>Carleton College LiBRary HTML and Web Site Resource: Additional Resources for Creating Stylish HTML Documents</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">
<A NAME="contents">
<HR SIZE=7>
<CENTER><H1>Additional Resources for Creating Stylish HTML Documents</H1></CENTER>
<HR SIZE=3>
<UL>
<DL>
<DT><A HREF="http://www.earth.com/bad-style/">Bad Style Guide</A>
<DD>Examples of HTML techniques to avoid from Tony Sanders.
<P>
<DT><A HREF="http://www.cs.cmu.edu/~tilt/cgh/">Composing Good HTML</A>
<DD>How to write HTML that will look good on <EM>any</EM> browser.  By Eric Tilton, author of
    <CITE><A HREF="http://www.aw.com/devpress/titles/48959.html">Web Weaving</A></CITE> 
<P>
<DT><A HREF="http://www.nashville.net/~carl/htmlguide/index.html">How Do They Do That with HTML?</A>
<DD>Design Tips for Web pages by Carl Tashian.
<P>
<DT><A HREF="http://cast.stanford.edu/cast/www/class/design.html">Good Design of Web Pages</A>
<DD>Brief excerpt from a Stanford-specific HTML tutorial.  Includes a section on
<A HREF="http://cast.stanford.edu/cast/www/class/design/thumbs.html">What's Good and What's Bad</A>. 
<P>
<DT><A HREF="http://www.w3.org/hypertext/WWW/Provider/Style/Overview.html">Style Guide to Online Hypertext</A>
<DD>From the <A HREF="http://www.w3.org/hypertext/WWW/">World Wide Web Consortium</A> (W3C), this document is
authored by none other than Tim Berners-Lee, the man who <EM>invented</EM> the World Wide Web!
<P>
<DT><A HREF="http://www.visdesigns.com/design/commandments.html">The Ten Commandments of HTML</A>
<DD>A humorous, yet informative, resource. By Sean Howard of <CITE>Visionary Designs</CITE>.
<P>
<DT><A HREF="http://cast.stanford.edu/eecns/www/donts.html">Top Ten Things Not to Do on a Web Page</A>
<DD>Actually, it lists twenty...from Stanford's <A HREF="http://cast.stanford.edu/cast/www/class/class.html">
    Walking the Fine Line to Becoming a Web Master</A>
<P> 
<DT><A HREF="http://www.charm.net/~web/Vlib/Providers/Style.html">The Web Developer's Virtual Library:  Style Guides</A>
<DD>A directory of HTML document style guides.
<P>
<DT><A HREF="http://www.dsiegel.com/tips/">Web Wonk - Tips for Writers and Designers</A>
<DD>Tips for making your HTML pages look great by David Siegel.
<P>
<DT><A HREF="http://www.yahoo.com/Computers_and_Internet/Internet/World_Wide_Web/Page_Design_and_Layout/">
     Yahoo: World Wide Web Page Design and Layout</A>
<DD>Another directory of HTML design resources.
<P>
<DT><A HREF="http://info.med.yale.edu/caim/StyleManual_Top.HTML">Yale C/AIM WWW Style Manual</A> 
<DD>An <EM>excellent</EM> presentation (the best I've found) of HTML design prinicipals by Patrick J. Lynch, MS.  
</DL>
</UL>
<P>
<HR>
