<HEAD>
<TITLE>Carleton College Library HTML and Web Site Resource: Maintaining Your Web Site
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">
<hr size=7>
<CENTER><H1>Maintaining Your Web Site</H1></CENTER>
<HR>
<P>
Visitors expect your site to grow and change every month.  In addition to adding new
information, you'll need to make sure your links continue to function.
<P>
<STRONG>Routine Maintenance:</STRONG>
<UL>
<LI>Check links to make sure they still work.
<LI>Review and update the content of your site.
<LI>Review "hit" statistics and plan to replace unaccessed pages.
</UL>
<P>
<STRONG>Growing a Web Site:</STRONG>
<UL>
<LI>Continue adding <A HREF="http://www.mcp.com/">additional information</A> that may be useful to your audience.
<LI>Add <A HREF="http://www.realbeer.com/">links</A> to Web sites in which your audience might have an interest.
<LI>Take a <A HREF="http://www-personal.umich.edu/~sgupta/hermes/">survey</A> and publish the results.
<LI>Organize the information on your site in a <A HREF="http://www.eat.com/">different way</A>.
<LI>Update <A HREF="http://daily.stanford.org/Statistics.html">statistics</A>, 
<A HREF="http://www.imall.com/dotd/dotd.shtml">prices</A>, 
<A HREF="http://www.btw.com/products/products.htm">product information</A>.
<LI>Run a <A HREF="http://www.redrocks.com/photo/photo.html">contest</A>.
</DL>
<HR>
<P>
<A HREF="welcome.html">Main Menu</A></CENTER>
