<TITLE>Web Search Tools:  Quick Start</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#054BBB" VLINK="#006342">
<hr size=7>
<CENTER><H2>Web Search Tools:  Quick Start</H2></CENTER>

If you have little time (or patience) to spare, the resource below is probably the best place to
head to access tools that'll help you search for information on the World Wide Web.<P>
<hr size=3>
<P>
<DL>

<DT><A HREF="http://home.netscape.com/home/internet-directory.html">Net Directory</A> and 
    <A HREF="http://home.netscape.com/home/internet-search.html">Net Search</A>
<DD>These are from Netscape Communications Corporation and are the same links associated with the Netscape toolbar
    buttons and <STRONG>Directory</STRONG> pull-down menu.  You will arrive at the same information
    regardless of which of these two links you select.  What you will find is a
    chance to try a search as well as a list and brief description
    of 30 premier Web search tools.
     
</DL>
<P>
