<hr size=7>
<CENTER><H2>Web Search Tools:  Print Articles</H2></CENTER>

<P>
<hr size=3>
<P>
<UL>
<DL>

    <DT>Bailes, Lenny.
    <DD>"Search Tools for the Web: Robots, Spiders, and Worms, Oh My!" <STRONG>Online Access</STRONG>, 
        vol. 10, no. 6, June 1, 1995, pp. 51-55.
    <BR>Intended for the beginner, this article discusses primary features of only <STRONG>Yahoo</STRONG> and 
        <STRONG>Lycos</STRONG>.  The article shows its age, thus some details are now dated.

<P>

    <DT>Bernstein, Judith H.
    <DD>"Excite and Yahoo Slug It Out." <STRONG>Netguide</STRONG>, vol. 3, no. 4, April 1996, pp. 24-25.
    <BR>The author describes competition among these two Web search services for advertising revenue.

<P>

    <DT>Bernstein, Judith H.
    <DD>"FAQ: Finding a Needle in a Digital Haystack." <STRONG>Netguide</STRONG>, vol. 3, no. 4, April 1996, pp. 79-80.
    <BR>This is a brief introduction to and description of major Web search tools.

<P>

    <DT>Blake, Paul.
    <DD>"Searching Out and Assessing Web Sites." <STRONG>Information Today</STRONG>, vol. 13, no. 1, January, 1996, pp. 48.
    <BR>This brief article discusses <STRONG>InfoMarket</STRONG>, <STRONG>Yahoo!</STRONG>, <STRONG>Open Text</STRONG>, <STRONG>Lycos</STRONG>, and <STRONG>WebCompass</STRONG>.

<P>

    <DT>Conheim, Wallys W.
    <DD>"The Internet:  Linking Up to a Global Network." <STRONG>Link-Up</STRONG>, vol. 13, no. 1, January/February, 1996, pp. 40-42.
    <BR>This article introduces readers to the basics of Web search tools.  The author ranks <STRONG>InfoSeek</STRONG>, 
        <STRONG>Yahoo!</STRONG>, and <STRONG>Lycos</STRONG> among the better tools.

<P>

    <DT>Conte, Jr., Ron.  
    <DD>"Searching on the Net: Guiding Lights."  <STRONG>Internet World</STRONG>, May 1996, vol. 7, no. 5, pp. 41-44.
    <BR>An excellent, concise introduction to Web search tools that includes recommendations.
    <BR>This article is also available <A HREF="http://www.internetworld.com/1996/05/guiding.html">online</A>.
    
<P>

    <DT>Courtois, Martin P., et al.  
    <DD>"Cool Tools For Searching the Web: A Performance Evaluation."  <STRONG>Online</STRONG>, vol. 19, no. 6, November/December 1995, pp. 14-32.
    <BR>In addition to providing and excellent explanationn of how Web search tools work, this article describes and 
        contrasts the following services:  <STRONG>CUI W3 Catalog</STRONG>, <STRONG>Harvest</STRONG>, <STRONG>Lycos</STRONG>, 
        <STRONG>Open Text</STRONG>, <STRONG>WebCrawler</STRONG>, <STRONG>WWW Worm</STRONG>, and <STRONG>Yahoo!</STRONG>.
    <BR>Recommended.  

<P>

    <DT>Courtois, Martin P.  
    <DD>"Cool Tools for Web Searching: An Update." <STRONG>Online</STRONG>, vol. 20, no. 3, May/June 1996, pp. 29-36.
    <BR>An update of the author's previous article, this work describes and 
        contrasts the following services:  <STRONG>Alta Vista</STRONG>, <STRONG>Excite</STRONG>, <STRONG>Inktomi</STRONG>,
        <STRONG>Magellan</STRONG>, and <STRONG>Point</STRONG>.  It also provides updated information on:  
        <STRONG>InfoSeek</STRONG>, <STRONG>Lycos</STRONG>, <STRONG>Open Text</STRONG>,<STRONG>WebCrawler</STRONG>, and 
        <STRONG>Yahoo!</STRONG>.
    <BR>Recommended.  

<P>

    <DT>Lester, Dan.
    <DD>"Yahoo: Profile of a Web Database." <STRONG>Database</STRONG>, vol. 18, no. 6, December 1995, pp. 46-50.
    <BR>The author provides a fine explanation and analysis of <STRONG>Yahoo!</STRONG>.
    <BR>Recommended.

<P>

    <DT>Makulowich, John S. and Bates, Mary Ellen.
    <DD>"Ten Tips on Managing Your Internet Searching." <STRONG>Online</STRONG>, vol. 19, no. 4, July/August, 1995, pp. 32-37.
    <BR>This article offers no explicit information on Internet search engines. Instead, it's geared primarily toward the librarian 
        or information specialist who performs Internet searches on behalf of non-specialists.  However, some of the authors' advice 
        on developing search strategies may also be of value to end-users, too.

<P>

    <DT>Moody, Glyn.  
    <DD>"Searching the Web for Gigabucks."  <STRONG>New Scientist</STRONG>, vol. 150, no. 2024, April 6, 1996, pp. 37-40.
    <BR>In addition offering an excellent description of how Web search tools work, the author discusses the rapidly
        growing commercial interest in, and competition among, these services.

<P>

    <DT>Notess, Greg R.
    <DD>"On the Nets: The InfoSeek Databases." <STRONG>Database</STRONG>, vol. 18, no. 4, August 1995, pp. 85+.
    <BR>This article offers a description and analysis of <STRONG>InfoSeek</STRONG>.
    <BR>This article is also available <A HREF="http://www.onlineinc.com/database/DB1995/AugDB95/notess.html">online</A>.
    
<P>

    <DT>Notess, Greg R.  
    <DD>"On the Nets: Searching the Web with Alta Vista." <STRONG>Database</STRONG>, vol. 19, no. 3, 
        June/July 1996, pp. 86-88.
    <BR>An evaluation of <STRONG>Alta Vista</STRONG>.
    <BR>This article is also available <A HREF="http://www.onlineinc.com/database/JuneDB/nets6.html">online</A>.
    
<P>

    <DT>Notess, Greg R.
    <DD>"On the Nets: Searching the World-Wide Web: Lycos, WebCrawler, and More." <STRONG>Online</STRONG>, 
        vol. 19, no. 4, July/August 1995, pp. 48-53.
    <BR>This article offers an analysis and comparison of <STRONG>Lycos</STRONG>, <STRONG>WebCrawler</STRONG>, 
        <STRONG>WWW Worm</STRONG>, <STRONG>Harvest</STRONG>, and <STRONG>CUI</STRONG>, along with brief information
        about <STRONG>Yahoo!</STRONG> and <STRONG>InfoSeek</STRONG>.
    <BR>This article is also available <A HREF="http://www.onlineinc.com/onlinemag/OL1995/JulOL95/notess.html">online</A>.
    
<P>

    <DT>Raeder, Aggi.
    <DD>"Cataloging the Web." <STRONG>Searcher: The Magazine for Database Professionals</STRONG>, vol. 3, no. 7, July 1995, pp. 12-19.
    <BR>This article highlights most of the major Web search tools available at the time of its publication.

<P>

    <DT>Randall, Neil.
    <DD>"The Search Engine that Could: Locating World Wide Web Sites Through Search Engines." <STRONG>PC/Computing</STRONG>, vol. 8, no. 9, September 1995, pp. 165-168.
    <BR>Comparisons and ratings 14 of major Web search services, including a guide to help you determine the best search service.  
        The author ranks <STRONG>InfoSeek</STRONG> as the best overall search service.  However, <STRONG>Alta Vista</STRONG> was not 
        examined.
    <BR>This article is also available <A HREF="http://www.zdnet.com/pccomp/features/internet/search/">online</A>.
    
<P>

    <DT>Richardson, Eric C.
    <DD>"Add an Engine." <STRONG>Internet World</STRONG>, vol. 7, no. 5, May 1996, pp. 88-90.
    <BR>This article identifies smaller cousins of search engines such as <STRONG>Alta Vista</STRONG> and <STRONG>Lycos</STRONG>, 
        which can be mounted at most any Web site.
    <BR>This article is also available <A HREF="http://www.internetworld.com/1996/05/engine.html">online</A>.
    
<P>

    <DT>Scolville, Richard.
    <DD>"Special Report: Find It on the Net" <STRONG>PC World</STRONG>, vol. 14, no. 1, January, 1996, pp. 124-130.
    <BR>This article compares and rates the basic features of all the major 
        <STRONG>directories</STRONG>, <STRONG>search engines</STRONG>, and <STRONG>metasearch engines</STRONG>. 
        (Due to its date, it does not cover <STRONG>Alta Vista</STRONG>.)  
        The author rates <STRONG>Excite</STRONG>, <STRONG>InfoSeek</STRONG>, and <STRONG>Lycos</STRONG> 
        are noted as the top three search engines and <STRONG>Yahoo!</STRONG> as the best Directory. 
        He also includes a generic list of tips for using search engines.
    <BR>Highly recommended.
    <BR>This article is also available <A HREF="http://www.pcworld.com/reprints/lycos.htm">online</A>.
    
<P>

    <DT>Stark, Thom.
    <DD>"Casting Your Net on the Web." <STRONG>LAN Times</STRONG>, vol. 12, no. 14, July 24 1995, pp. 109-110.
    <BR>Here you'll find a brief, although somewhat dated, overview of major Web search tools.

<P>

    <DT>Steinberg, Steve G.
    <DD>"Seek and Ye Shall Find (Maybe)." <STRONG>Wired</STRONG>, vol. 4, no. 5, May 1996, pp. 110-114, 172,174,176,178,180, 182.
    <BR>This article examines the struggle information scientists in organizing the vast amount of information on the rapidly 
        growing World Wide Web. Includes in-depth coverage of <STRONG>Yahoo!</STRONG>, <STRONG>Inktomi</STRONG>, and <STRONG>Excite</STRONG>.  
    <BR>Recommended.
    <BR>This article is also available <A HREF="http://www.hotwired.com/wired/4.05/features/indexweb.html">online</A>.
    
<P>

    <DT>Taubes, Gary.
    <DD>"Indexing the Internet." <STRONG>Science</STRONG>, vol. 269, no. 5229, September 8, 1995, pp. 1354-1356.
    <BR>The author describes the hurdles and potential solutions for organizing and retrieving information on the Internet, 
        particularly the World Wide Web.

<P>

    <DT>Ubois, Jeff.  
    <DD>"Agents of Change."  <STRONG>Internet World</STRONG>, vol., 7 no. 5, May 1996, pp. 62-76.
    <BR>Interviews with two computer industry experts on the topic of intelligent agent development.
    <BR>This article is also available <A HREF="http://www.internetworld.com/1996/05/agents.html">online</A>.
    
<P>

    <DT>Venditto, Gus.  
    <DD>"Search Engine Showdown."  <STRONG>Internet World</STRONG>, vol. 7, no. 5, May 1996, pp. 79-92.
    <BR>This article describes and evaluates seven search tools: <STRONG>Alta Vista</STRONG>, 
        <STRONG>Excite</STRONG>, <STRONG>InfoSeek</STRONG>, <STRONG>Lycos</STRONG>, 
        <STRONG>Open Text</STRONG>, <STRONG>Web Crawler</STRONG>, and <STRONG>WWW Worm</STRONG>. 
    <BR>Highly Recommended.  
    <BR>This article is also available <A HREF="http://www.internetworld.com/1996/05/showdown.html">online</A>.

<P>

    <DT>Watson, Ian.
    <DD>"Searching the WWW:  A Quick Comparison of Infoseek, Lycos, Yahoo, Info Market, and WebCrawler." 
        <STRONG>Managing Information</STRONG>, vol. 3, nos. 1/2, January/February, 1996, pp. 38-39.
    <BR>The title accurately describes the scope of this brief article.

<P>

    <DT>Zorn, Peggy, et al.  
    <DD>"Advanced Web Searching: Tricks of the Trade." <STRONG>Online</STRONG>, vol. 20, no. 3, May/June 1996, 
         pp. 14-28.
    <BR>This article evaluates:  <STRONG>Alta Vista</STRONG>, 
        <STRONG>InfoSeek</STRONG>, <STRONG>Lycos</STRONG>, and <STRONG>Open Text</STRONG>.      
    <BR>Highly Recommended.  
    <BR>This article is also available <A HREF="http://www.onlineinc.com/onlinemag/MayOL/zorn5.html">online</A>.
      
<P>
</DL>
</UL>
<P>
