<HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">
<CENTER><H2>MLA International Bibliography</H2></CENTER>

<P>
The <strong>MLA International Bibliography (MLA)</strong> produced by the Modern Language 
Association of America, contains over one million bibliographic citations for items from
over 4,000 journals and series published worldwide.  It indexes journal articles, book 
articles, dissertations, monographs, essay collections, working papers, proceedings, 
and bibliographies.  Topics covered includes literature, languages, linguistics, and folklore.
<P>
Coverage/update frequency:
<UL>
<LI>Covers 1963 to the present
<LI>Adds new records ten times per year; approximately 45,000 records annually
</UL>
<P>
To access MLA International Bibliography online, you must use the special
<A HREF="http://www.library.carleton.edu:8001/mlapswd.html">
username and password</A> assigned to Carleton College and point your Web browser to:
<P> 
<CENTER><STRONG><KBD>http://othello.lib.umn.edu/cgi-bin/webspirs.sh?sp.nextform=top.htm</KBD></STRONG></CENTER>
<BR>
<BR>
<CENTER><STRONG><A HREF="http://othello.lib.umn.edu/cgi-bin/webspirs.sh?sp.nextform=top.htm">Jump Directly to MLA International Bibliography Online</A></STRONG></CENTER>
<BR>
<BR>
<hr>
<P>
<CENTER><A HREF="index.html">Return to the Online Databases Page</A></CENTER>
<BR>
<BR>
<cite>
Maintained by <A HREF="/staff/terry/terry.html">Terry Metz, temetz@carleton.edu</A>
