<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>
UnCover
</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">
<CENTER>
<H1>UnCover</H1>
</CENTER>

<STRONG>UnCover</STRONG> is a peridocial index database to approximately 17,000 
journals.  It's particularly useful when your topic is 
interdisciplinary in nature.
<P>
Searching is free of charge.  UnCover offers document 
delivery service for a fee.  Those who wish to use this 
document ordering service may do so at their own expense. The 
Library does not act as an agent of UnCover, and this feature 
is not part of Interlibrary Services. This document delivery
service may be of interest to those who need to pay copyright 
royalty fees.
<P>
 
<P>
<UL>
<CENTER><STRONG><A HREF="http://www.carl.org/uncover/unchome.html">More Information about UnCover</A></STRONG></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><STRONG><A HREF="telnet://database.carl.org">Launch a Telnet Session to UnCover</A></STRONG></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><STRONG><IMG SRC="/images/new.gif" ALT="[New!]"><A HREF="uncoverweb.html">UnCover Web Access</A></STRONG></CENTER>
</UL>

<HR>

<H4>Features:</H4>
<UL>
<LI>free; no password required
<LI>coverage is 1988 to date for most titles
<LI>discipline content breakdown:
  <UL>
  <LI>Humanities 14%
  <LI>Social Sciences 33%
  <LI>Science, Technology, Medicine 53%
  </UL>
<LI>4000 citations added daily
<LI>document delivery added daily
</UL>

<H4>Access:</H4>
<UL>
<LI>from any computer with Vax access, logon to your Vax account and proceed
  <UL>
  <LI><strong><kbd>$telnet database.carl.org</kbd></strong>
  <LI>select <strong><kbd>VT100</kbd></strong> (#5)
  <LI>choose <strong><kbd>UnCover</kbd></strong> from the options list
  <LI>press <strong><kbd>enter</kbd></strong> when asked for a password or profile
  </UL>
<LI>from the PowerMacs in the library's electronic reference area
  <UL>
  <LI>click on the UnCover icon
  <LI>proceed as listed above
  </UL>
<LI>from Muse 
  <UL>
  <LI>choose <strong><kbd>R</kbd></strong> for other resources
  <LI>select <strong><kbd>UnCover</kbd></strong>
  <LI>proceed as listed above
  </UL>
</UL>

<H4>Searching:</H4>
<UL>
<LI><strong><kbd>N (Name)</kbd></strong>  authors of articles or articles about specific people
<LI><strong><kbd>W (Word)</kbd></strong> words can be from the title, subtitle, or summaries
<LI><strong><kbd>B (Browse)</kbd></strong> browse the table of contents for specific issues of journals
<DD>or 
<LI>Quick Search Options - use at any time to avoid the menu screens
<UL>
<LI><strong><kbd>//n <DD>Tony Hillerman
	<DD>Garrison Keillor/New Yorker
<LI>//W <DD> biodiversity act
<DD>Wellstone
<DD>AIDS Scientific American
<LI>//t <DD>far eastern economic review</kbd></strong>
</UL>
</UL>

<H4>Commands:</H4>
<UL>
<LI><strong><kbd>//exit</kbd></strong> - fast exit
<LI><strong><kbd>q</kbd></strong> - begin new search
<LI><strong><kbd>*</kbd></strong> (the wildcard character, for braoder searches) - reptil* = reptiles, reptillia, reptillian
<LI><strong><kbd>and, or, but, not</kbd></strong> - to expand or limit a search
<LI><strong><kbd>h</kbd></strong> - history of your search
<LI><strong><kbd>?</kbd></strong> - help (context sensitive)
<LI><strong><kbd>&lt;control&gt; h</kbd></strong> - backspace
<LI><strong><kbd>e</kbd></strong> - examine table of contents
</UL>
<P>
