<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Wilson Indexes</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">
<CENTER>
<H1>Wilson Journal Citation Indexes</H1>
</CENTER>
<P>
Use these indexes to locate journal articles on a topic of interest to you.  If a 
particular article you find is carried in a journal held in the Carleton College 
libraries, Muse will display this information on the screen for you.
<P>
<strong>Note that these indexes cover only articles which have been published since 1991.
</strong>  They are updated monthly.  All of these indexes are also available via <A HREF=
"firstsearch.html">FirstSearch</A>.  <strong>Through FirstSearch, you can search some of 
these indexes as far back as 30 years.</strong>

<P>

<UL>
<LI><A HREF="#ArtIndex">Art Index</A> -Leading publications in the world of the arts.
<LI><A HREF="#BioAgIndex">Biological & Agricultural Index</A> -Leading publications in the world of biology and agriculture.
<LI><A HREF="#BusPerInd">Business Periodicals Index</A> -Popular business magazines.
<LI><A HREF="#GenSciIndex">General Science Index</A> -Leading general science periodicals.
<LI><A HREF="#HumanitiesIn">Humanities Index</A> -An index of articles in the humanities.
<LI><A HREF="#ReadersGuide">Readers Guide Index</A> -Readers' Guide to Periodical Literature.
<LI><A HREF="#SocSciInd">Social Sciences Index</A> -Guide to the literature of the social sciences.
</UL>

<H4>Access:</H4>
<UL>
<LI>from Muse: 
  <UL>
  <LI>choose <strong><kbd>J</strong>> Wilson JOURNAL Citation Indexes</kbd>
  </UL>
</UL>

You'll see the following menu options:
<P>

<pre>
                           Welcome to Wilson database                




                       W > WORDS (in Title and Subject)

                       A > Article AUTHOR
                       T > Article TITLE
                       J > JOURNAL Title

                       S > SUBJECT
                       I > Wilson INFORMATION


                       Q > QUIT
                        Choose one (W,A,T,J,S,I,Q)

</pre>

<hr>
<P>
<P>
<A NAME="ArtIndex">
<H3>ART INDEX</H3>
<P>More than 200 key international, English-language arts
  publications.  Includes periodicals, yearbooks, museum bulletins,
  competition and award notices, exhibition listings, interviews, film
  reviews, and more.

<P>
<A NAME="BioAgIndex">
<H3>BIOLOGICAL & AGRICULTURAL INDEX</H3>
<P>More than 240 international, English-language publications pertaining to biology 
  and agriculture.  Includes a wide range of scientific journals, from popular to 
  professional.
 

<P>
<A NAME="BusPerInd">
<H3>BUSINESS PERIODICALS INDEX</H3>
<P>Over 340 business magazines in accounting, advertising,
  finance, personnel, small business, and more.

<P>
<A NAME="GenSciIndex">
<H3>GENERAL SCIENCE INDEX</H3>
<P> More than 100 journals and magazines from the U.S. and Great
  Britain, covering such subjects as anthropology, astronomy, biology,
  computers, earth sciences, medicine and health, and much more.  Includes
  articles, reviews, biographical sketches, and letters to the editor.

<P>
<A NAME="HumanitiesIn">
<H3>HUMANITIES INDEX</H3>
<P>More than 300 periodicals in archaeology, art, classics,
  film, folklore, journalism, linguistics, music, the performing arts,
  philosophy, religion, world history, and world literature.

<P>
<A NAME="ReadersGuide">
<H3>READERS' GUIDE TO PERIODICAL LITERATURE </H3>
<P>Popular periodicals published in the U.S. and Canada.
  Includes current events and news, fine arts, fashion, education,
  business, sports, health and nutrition, consumer affairs, and others.

<P>
<A NAME="SocSciInd">
<H3>SOCIAL SCIENCES INDEX </H3>
<P>More than 350 international, English-language periodicals
  in sociology, anthropology, geography, economics, political science,
  and law.
<P>
<hr>
<P>
