<HEAD>
<TITLE>
Handbook of Latin American Studies file (HLA)
</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">
<CENTER>
<H1>Handbook of Latin American Studies</H1>
</CENTER>

<STRONG>The Handbook of Latin American Studies (HLA)</STRONG> contains records
    describing books, book chapters, as well as over 1,350 social science and 
    550 humanities journals and conference proceedings published worldwide in the 
    field of Latin American studies.  Most records include abstracts with evaluations.  
    Current access to HLA has been arranged via a <STRONG>trial</STRONG> basis. 
    The Gould Library continues to maintain its paper copy of this 
    resource in the Reference Collection under the call number: 
    <STRONG><KBD>F1408 .H23 (1935- )</KBD></STRONG>
<P>
<PRE>
 SUBJECT COVERAGE    Social sciences and the humanities, in alternate
                     years (e.g., humanities are covered in 1990, social
                     sciences in 1991)

DATES OF COVERAGE    1990 to the present

         SUPPLIER    Hispanic Division, Library of Congress

 UPDATE FREQUENCY    Annually

             SIZE    Over 21,000 records as of April 1995 with
                     approximately 10,000 added at each update

        ABSTRACTS    Over 60% of records contain evaluative annotations
                     by more than 130 contributing subject specialists
</PRE>
<HR>
<H3>Sample HLA Record</H3>
<P>
<PRE>
           TITLE:  The social ecology and economic development of Ciudad
                   Juarez. Edited by Gay Young.
       PUBLISHED:  Boulder:  Westview Press, 1986.
PHYSICAL DETAILS:  171 p. : ill. ; 23 cm.
          SERIES:  Westview special studies on Latin America and the Caribbean.

   OTHER AUTHORS:  Young, Gay.

        SUBJECTS:  Urban Areas -- Mexico.
                   Economic Development -- Mexico.
                   Urbanization -- Mexico -- Ciudad Juarez.
                   Land use, Urban -- Mexico -- Ciudad Juarez.
                   Women offshore assembly industry workers -- Mexico --
                   Ciudad Juarez -- Economic conditions.
                   Mexican-American Border Region -- Urbanization.
                   Ciudad Juarez, Mexico (city) -- Urban Areas.
                   Ciudad Juarez (Mexico) -- Economic conditions.
                   Ciudad Juarez (Mexico) -- Social conditions.

           NOTES:  Includes bibliographies and index.
        CONTENTS:  The development of Ciudad Juarez / Gay Young -- Patterns
                   of urban growth in Ciudad Juarez / Robert H. Schmidt and
                   William J. Lloyd -- Land use structure and the
                   availability of services in Ciudad Juarez / William J.
                   Lloyd -- Household structure and activity in Ciudad
                   Juarez / Gay Young and Susan Christopherson -- Economic
                   change and ideological lag in households of maquila
                   workers in Ciudad Juarez / Kathleen A. Staudt -- Human
                   resources and economic development in Ciudad Juarez /
                   Edward Y. George -- The foreign orientation of the
                   Ciudad Juarez economy / Oscar J. Martinez.

         SUMMARY:  Collection of seven chapters that analyze the Mexican
                   part of the second largest metropolitan agglomeration on
                   the US-Mexican border.  Very timely and useful
                   information on the social, economic, and physical
                   structure of the city.
           NOTES:  Includes index.

            LCCN:  bi 88-1122
            ISBN:  0-8133-7248-8 (soft : alk. paper)
</PRE>
<HR>
