<TITLE>Carleton College Library Instruction Page</TITLE>
</head>
<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">
<P>
<center><H2>Library Instruction Page</H2></center>
<strong>Library Instruction</strong>, commonly referred to as <strong>Bibliographic Instruction</strong>
or simply <strong>BI</strong>, is the education of library users to become effective information retrievers 
and consumers.
<P>
As you might expect, the proliferation of information resources of all types as well as the rapid pace of technological 
change (including concepts such as the <CITE>information superhighway</CITE> and the <CITE>virtual library</CITE>)
are offering unprecedented opportunities and challenges for our students and faculty.
<P>
Contact <A HREF="/staff/carolyn/carolyn.html">Carolyn Sanford</A> or
<A HREF="/staff/terry/terry.html">Terry Metz</A> to arrange for <A HREF="biarrange.html">tailored instruction</A>
for both fundamental skills and for keeping you and your students abreast of the latest information resources in your field.
<P>
Highlighted Instruction Pages:
<P>
<UL>
<LI><IMG SRC="/images/new.gif" ALT="[New!]"><A HREF="eciting.html">Tips on Citing Internet Resources</A>
