<CENTER><H1>Answers to Exercise 4</H1></CENTER>
<HR ALIGN="center" WIDTH=50%>
<PRE>
&lt;HTML&gt;
&lt;HEAD&gt;
&lt;TITLE&gt;HTML Exercises For Beginners - Exercise 4&lt;/TITLE&gt;
&lt;/HEAD&gt;
&lt;BODY&gt;
&lt;H1&gt;Some Internet Terms&lt;/H1&gt;
&lt;DL&gt;
&lt;DT&gt;protocol
&lt;DD&gt;A specific rule, or set of rules, defining how computers will act
when talking to each other.  Protocol definitions range from how bits are placed on a wire to the
format of an e-mail message.
&lt;DT&gt;TCP/IP
&lt;DD&gt;(Transmission Control Protocol/Internet Protocol) One of the
protocols on which the Internet is based.
&lt;DT&gt;PPP
&lt;DD&gt;(Point to Point Protocol) A protocol that allows a computer to
use the Internet with a standard telephone line and a high-speed modem.
&lt;DT&gt;SLIP
&lt;DD&gt;(Serial Line Internet Protocol) Another protocol that allows a computer to
use the Internet with a standard telephone line and a high-speed modem.
&lt;/DL&gt;
&lt;/BODY&gt;
&lt;/HTML&gt;
</PRE>
