<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Answers to Exercise 9
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<hr size=7>
<CENTER><H2>Answers to Exercise 9</H2></CENTER>
<HR>
<ol>
<li>Write the HTML code to show an image (IMAGE.GIF) when the image is in the 
subdirectory named "GIF."<p>

<EM><b>Answer:</EM></b>  <TT>&lt;IMG ALIGN=bottom SRC=&quot;gif/image.gif&quot; ALT=&quot;An Image&quot;&gt;</TT>
<p>
<EM><B>Note:</B>  You may have chosen a different alignment (since none was specified) and/or a different description
for those who do not have graphic browsers.</EM><p>
<p>
<li>Write the HTML code to show the same image with a different alignment of your choice.<p>
<EM><B>Answer:</EM></B>  <TT>&lt;IMG ALIGN=top SRC=&quot;gif/image.gif&quot; ALT=&quot;An Image&quot;&gt;</TT>
<p>
<EM><B>Note:</B>  You may have chosen a different alignment (as long as it was different than your
alignment in #1) and/or a different description for those who do not have graphic browsers.</EM><p>
<p>
<li>Write the HTML code to include a graphic of a red bar across your screen.  Here is a URL:
http://www.cusd.claremont.edu:80/www/icons/redbar.gif<p>
<EM><B>Answer:</EM></B>  <TT>&lt;IMG ALIGN=bottom SRC=&quot;http://www.cusd.claremont.edu:80/www/icons/redbar.gif&quot;&gt;</TT>
<p>
<EM><B>Note:</B>  You may have chosen a different alignment (since none was specified).  When including design 
elements in an HTML file (colored lines, colored balls, etc.), I don't bother with an alternate description.  Those
without graphic browsers won't know they're missing anything.</EM>
<P>
<li>Write the HTML code to include a graphic of an "under construction" image your screen.  Here is a URL:
http://www.library.carleton.edu/webtutorial/at_work.GIF<p>
<EM><B>Answer:</EM></B>  <TT>&lt;IMG ALIGN=bottom SRC=&quot;http://www.library.carleton.edu/webtutorial/at_work.GIF&quot;&gt;</TT>
<p>
<EM><B>Note:</B>  You may have chosen a different alignment (since none was specified).  When including design 
elements in an HTML file (colored lines, colored balls, etc.), I don't bother with an alternate description.  Those
without graphic browsers won't know they're missing anything.</EM>
</OL>
<p>
<HR>
<P>
