<CENTER><H2>Answers to Exercise 10</H2></CENTER>
<HR>
<HTML>
<ol>
<li>Write a link tag that references a file called "linktags" in the same
directory as your HTML document.  Have the text on the screen say "Link Tags."<p>
<EM><B>Answer:  </EM></B> <TT>&lt;A HREF=&quot;linktags&quot;&gt;Link Tags&lt;/A&gt;</TT>
<p>
<p>
<li>Write a link tag for the same file if it is in a different subdirectory
named "HTMLdocs."<p>
<EM><B>Answer:  </EM></B><TT>&lt;A HREF=&quot;HTMLdocs/linktags&quot;&gt;Link Tags&lt;/A&gt;</TT>
<p>
<li>Write a link tag to take people to the URL Primer (http://www.ncsa.uiuc.edu/demoweb/url-primer.html).
Decide for yourself what the text on the screen will say.<p>
<EM><B>Answer:  </EM></B><TT>&lt;A HREF=&quot;http://www.ncsa.uiuc.edu/demoweb/url-primer.html&quot;&gt;(Text 
you chose)&lt;/A></TT>
<p>
<p>
<li>Write the pair of link tags that will take a viewer back to the words "Exercise 1"
in a document (like this one) from the end of Exercise 9.<p>
<EM><B><DL><DT>Answer:  </B>Near the words "Exercise 1" you would enter:<p></EM>
<DD><TT>&lt;A NAME=&quot;Exercise 1&quot;&gt;&lt;/A&gt;</TT><p>
<DD><EM>Where you wanted the link to be, you would enter:</EM><p>
<DD><TT>&lt;A HREF=&quot;#Exercise1&quot;&gt;Return to Exercise 1&lt;/A&gt;</TT>
</DL>
<li>Write a link tag to use the image "image.gif" to link to a file called file.html.<p>
<EM><B><DL><DT>Answer:</EM></B><TT>  &lt;A HREF="file.html"&gt;&lt;IMG SRC="image.gif" ALT="Alternate text"&gt&lt;/A&gt;</TT>
<p>
</ol></ul>
<p>
