<HEAD>
<TITLE>Carleton College Library HTML and Web Site Resource: How to Inform Yourself about the World Wide Web
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">

<hr size=7>

<CENTER><H1>How to Inform Yourself about the Feasibility of Using the World Wide Web 
in Your Organization</H1></CENTER>
<HR>
<P>
<DL>
<DT><STRONG><A NAME="heck">Figure out what the heck the World Wide Web <EM>is</EM>.</STRONG>
<P>
<DD>The World Wide Web is a subset of the Internet which features colorful
    graphics and a convenient way of linking sets of information through hyperlinks.<p>
    It's the <EM>fastest</EM> growing part of the Net, especially attractive to
    businesses because of the way it blends graphics and information.
<P>
Look here for general information:
<P>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.boutell.com/faq/">WWW FAQ</A>
<LI><A HREF=" http://www.vuw.ac.nz/~gnat/ideas/www-primer.html">WWW Primer</A>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.ncsa.uiuc.edu/SDG/Software/Mosaic/Docs/www-info.html">WWW Background Information</A>
<LI><A HREF="http://tecfa.unige.ch/info-www.html">WWW and Internet Manuals</A>
</UL>
</DL>
<HR>

<DL>
<DT><STRONG><A NAME="other">Look at how other organizations are using it.</STRONG>
<P>
<DD>Educational, governmental, non-profit, and commercial organizations are getting on the Web.  
    They're using the power of the Web to collect and distribute information of all kinds.
<P>
Examples of how to use the Web:
<P>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://wings.buffalo.edu/contest/awards/index.html">Best of the Web Award Winners</A>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.owi.com/netvalue/v1i6l1.html">NET.VALUE's Interesting Business Sites on the Web</A>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.ai.mit.edu/people/ellens/non.html">Select Non-profit Organizations on the Web</A>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.yahoo.com/Business/">Yahoo Business and Economy Links</A>
</UL>
</DL>
<HR>

<DL>
<DT><A NAME="how"><STRONG>Figure out how YOU want to use it.</STRONG>
<P>
<DD>As you look at sites like the ones listed above, note what you like and don't like about them.
    Pay attention to the ways people are organizing information, the media they use, the frustrations
    you encounter.  These will all help you decide how best to apply this technology for your needs.
</DL>
<P>
<HR>
<P>
<CENTER><A HREF="sitedesign.html">Back to Designing Your Web Site</A>
<P>
<A HREF="welcome.html">Main Menu</A></CENTER>
