<HEAD>
    <TITLE>CD ROMS from the US Department of Commerce</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<H2><CENTER>CD ROMS from the US Department of Commerce </CENTER>
</H2>
<P><CENTER>Carleton College Government Documents Electronic Media List</CENTER>
<P><HR SIZE="6"><HR>



<H3><A NAME="RTFToC3"></A>NTDB, the NATIONAL TRADE DATA BANK: THE EXPORT
CONNECTION. </H3>
<H4></A>C 1.88: (year/month/CD) </H4>
U.S. Department of Commerce , 1990- . (monthly)<BR>
<BR>
The National Trade Data Bank (NTDB) provides trade information about industries
and countries worldwide. Eighteen agencies contribute the best of their
international trade and export promotion information to this monthly disc.
<UL>
  <LI>Compatible: PC.
  <LI>Documentation 
  <UL>
    <LI>BROWSE USERS GUIDE July 1992 printed from disc 
    <LI>AGENCY DESCRIPTIONS Feb. 25,1993 printed from disc 
    <LI>ROMWARE USERS MANUAL Aug. 1992 printed from disc 
    <LI>REFERENCE GUIDE MANUAL 
    <LI>CONTENTS.TXT Feb., Mar printed from disc 
  </UL>
</UL>


<HR>
<H3><A NAME="RTFToC5"></A>NESE-DB, THE NATIONAL ECONOMIC, SOCIAL, &amp; ENVIRONMENTAL
DATA BANK: THE FEDERAL CONNECTION. </H3>
<H4>C 1.88/2 </H4>
U.S. Department of Commerce, 1992- (monthly). Current Month disc in CD-ROM
magazine. <BR>
<BR>
This disc contains federal information about the U.S. economy, population,
health and environmental conditions, and government. The disc contains information
from several government agencies, such as the Congressional Budget Office,
etc. 
<UL>
  <LI>File Format: ISO 9660 format. 
  <LI>Compatible: PC. 
</UL>
<HR>

<H3><A NAME="TRCKSRVY"></A>TIUS, 1992 TRUCK INVENTORY AND USE SURVEY. </H3>
<h4>C 3.233/6:992 </H4><BR>
<BR>
U.S. Department of Commerce <BR>
<BR>
The Truck Inventory and Use Survey (TIUS) provides data on the physical
and operational characteristics of the Nation's truck population. The data
available for individual trucks include weight and type of ownership. The
following data are also available: leasing information (type, length, and
options), major use and principal products carried (including percent of
mileage carried hazardous material), maintenance information, and equipment
data (engine, brake type, power steering, fuel, conservation equipment,
body and vehicle type, size class, and cab type), vehicle make, cubic inch
displacement, annual and lifetime miles, and TIUS gross vehicle weight rating
(TIUGVW) code. <BR>
<BR>
The microdata file is representative of all private and commercial trucks
in the United States. Each record indicates the state in which the truck
is registered and whether the home base is inside or outside a Metropolitan
Statistical Area (MSA).
 <ul>
 <LI>File Format: ASCII format. 
 <LI>Compatible: PC.
 <LI> Documentation: Technical Documentation on Disc
   </UL>
   <HR>
   
 <h3>  <A NAME="MM4MD"></A>MM4-1990 METEOROLOGY DATA </H3>
<h4>C 55.281/2-2:M56/V.1-6; V.7-12</H4> 
<BR>
U.S. Department of Commerce <BR>
<BR>
For description see <A HREF="Abstracts/C55.281.2-2M56/mm4md.abst.html">ABSTRACTS.</A>
<UL>
<LI>File Format: ASCII format.
<LI>Compatible: DOS, UNIX; ZCAT Compression/Decompression Software On Disc. 
<LI>Documentation: Technical Documentation on Disc </UL><HR>

<h3><A NAME="SCBGR"></A>Southern California Bight Expert Reports </H3>
<h4>C 55.54: B48</H4> 

<BR>
This CD contains material generated in support of the Southern California
Bight Natural Resource Damage Assessment conducted by the Federal and State
Trustees from 1991 to 1994. The damage assessment was conducted to determine
the effects of DDT and PCBs on the natural resources of the Bight. This
CD was produced to provide easy access to the results of the damage assessment
and to facilitate broad public review and use of the work. U.S. Department
of Commerce <BR>
<BR>
<UL>
<LI>Acrobat reader File Format:PDF files 
<LI>Compatible: Macintosh & Windows; Acrobat Reader 2.0 Software provided 
<LI>Documentation: Technical Documentation on Disc
</UL>


<hr>
<h3><A NAME="SOCB"></A>Survey of Current Business</H3>
<h4>C 55.59/1:994</H4> 
<BR>
This CD contains PDF files of the 1994 issues of the Survey of Current Business the monthly journal of the Bureau of Economic Analysis. In addition it contains 42 major Survey Articals from 1987-93. The files are fully searchable. <BR>
<BR>
<UL>
<LI>Acrobat reader File Format:PDF files 
<LI>Compatible: Macintosh & Windows; Acrobat Reader 2.0 Software provided 
<LI>Documentation: Technical Documentation on Disc
</UL>



</UL><!--footer--><HR><A HREF="THELIST.html">Return to table of contents.
