<HEAD>

<TITLE>CD ROMS from the Bureau of the Census</TITLE>


</HEAD>
<BODY>
<CENTER><H2>CD ROMS from the Bureau of the Census
</H2>
Carleton College Government Documents Electronic Media List</CENTER>
<HR SIZE="6">
<HR>
<H3>
<A NAME="RTFToC7">COUNTY
AND CITY DATA BOOK 1988, STATISTICAL ABSTRACT SUPPLEMENT.
</A></H3>
<H4>
<A NAME="RTFToC8">C
3.134/2:C83/2/988/CD
</A></H4>

U.S. Department of Commerce, 1989- .
<P>
Summary data on population, households, vital statistics, crime, income, labor
force, elections, and more. Contains both census date and current estimates for
states, countries, and communities with populations over 2,500. 
<UL><LI>File Format: dBase; menu-driven software installed.
<LI>Compatible: PC or Macintosh 
<LI>Paper Copy: Gov Doc Ref. C3.134/2:C83/2/988.
<LI>Documentation: Technical Documentation Printed from Disk and On-line help
<UL><LI>HELP FILES printed from software floppy </UL></UL>

<HR><H3>
<A NAME="RTFToC9">STATISTICAL
ABSTRACT OF THE UNITED STATES 1993
</A></H3>
<H4>
<A NAME="RTFToC10">C&nbsp;3.134/7:993</A></H4>
Bureau of the Census.<P>
The 1993 Statistical Abstract on CD-ROM, like the book, is a statistical
reference and guide to over 250 statistical publications and sources from
government and private organizations.<P>
This CD has 1,500 tables and charts from over 250 sources. Text and tables can
be viewed or searched with the software. Tables and charts cover these subjects
in 31 sections and 2 appendices:
<UL><LI>agriculture 
<LI>banking, finance and insurance 
<LI>business enterprise 
<LI>communications 
<LI>comparative international statistics 
<LI>congressional district profiles (ap vii)
<LI>construction and housing 
<LI>domestic trade and services 
<LI>population 
<LI>national defense and veterans affairs 
<LI>health and nutrition 
<LI>education 
<LI>elections 
<LI>energy 
<LI>federal government finances and employment 
<LI>foreign commerce and aid 
<LI>forests and fisheries 
<LI>geography and environment 
<LI>income, expenditure and wealth 
<LI>labor force, employment and earnings 
<LI>law enforcement, courts and prisons 
<LI>manufacturers 
<LI>mining and mineral products 
<LI>parks, recreation and travel 
<LI>population of MSAS (ap ii)
<LI>prices 
<LI>outlying areas 
<LI>transportation -- air and water 
<LI>transportation -- land 
<LI>science 
<LI>social insurance and human services 
<LI>state and local government finances and employment 
<LI>state rankings 
<LI>vital statistics 
</UL>

<UL><LI>File format:
<LI>Compatible: PC 
<LI>Documentation: On line Assistance and small manual and full manual printed
from disc 
<UL><LI>USERS MANUAL printed from disc 
<LI>TEXTWARE LITE USERS MANUAL printed from disc </UL></UL>
<HR><H3>
