POPULATION SURVEY ANNUAL DEMOGRAPHIC FILES.
</A></H3>
<H4>
<A NAME="RTFToC19">C
3.224/12:989-991;:988-990;:990-992;991-993
</A></H4>
<P>
Bureau of the Census, 1991- .
<P>
These files cover regions, SMSAs, and all states. They present unsummarized
information about individuals within households (family characteristics,
marital status, education, poverty status, work experience, income, noncash
benefits, migration), labor force data, etc. A <a href="abstracts/CPS/variables1994.html">list</a> of the feilds is provided on the CD
<p>
For the 1994 survey the census bureau changes some of the aspects of the survey. These changes can be found on the 1994 CD. Also the 1994 CD is labled Income and Poverty:1993.
<P>
No retrieval software is available from the Census Bureau. In other words,
these files are raw ASCII, A user should be somewhat familiar with this type of
document, bring his/her own floppies and extract only selective variables.
Personal software which will read such hierarchical microdata in raw ASCII
records may also be required.
<UL><LI>Files: ASCII format.
<LI>Compatible: PC.
