CENSUS FILES.
</A></H3>
<H4>
<A NAME="RTFToC39">C
3.279.
</A></H4>
Bureau of the Census, 1992 discs.
<P>
The TIGER allows all relevant geographic information about an area to be
entered into a computer-readable database. The file contains data for all 1990
census map features (such as roads, railroads, and rivers), feature names and
classification codes, alternate feature names, the associated 1980 and 1990
census geographic codes and FIPS (Federal Information Processing Standards)
codes, such as those for census tracks, blocks, cities, and townships, and
within the urban core of each metropolitan area, address ranges and ZIP codes
for streets.
