<HR><P>
<H3><A NAME="RTFToC40">TIGER CENSUS TRACT STREET INDEX</A>
</H3>
<H4>

C 3.279/2:CD-CTSI-V.2-()
</H4>
Item:154-E-1<P>
Bureau of the Census
<P>
The file contains Federal Information Processing Standards (FIPS) State,
county, county subdivision, and place codes and the 1990 census tract numbers
for each side of the street  within the areas of counties containing city-style
addresses.  It provides the street name, including prefix and/or suffix
direction (north, southeast, etc.) and street type (street, avenue, lane,
etc.), the address range for that portion of the street located within a
particular census tract, corresponding census tract number, ZIP code, and
Congressional district code.
<P>
The ZIP, FIPS county subdivision, and place codes are useful in determining the
correct census tract number when streets with identical names and ranges exist
in different parts of the same county.
<UL>
<LI>File format:dBase III
<LI>Compatible:  PC. 
<LI>Documentation: On line Assistance and small manual 
</UL>


