<HR><H3>
<A NAME="RTFToC45">CENSUS
OF POPULATION AND HOUSING SUMMARY TAPE FILES.
</A></H3>
<H4>
<A NAME="RTFToC46">C
3.282:990-1A; C 3.282:990-1C
</A></H4>
Bureau of the Census, 1990- .
<P>
<B>STF 1A. </B>States, counties, county subdivisions, places, census
tracts/block numbering areas (BNAs), block groups (BGs). Also, Alaska Native
areas, State parts of American Indian areas, state parts of Native American
areas, and congressional districts of the 101st Congress.<P>
<P>
<B>STF 1C.</B> U.S., regions, divisions, states (including summaries such as
urban and rural), counties, communities of 10,000 or more inhabitants, county
subdivisions of 10,000 or more inhabitants in&nbsp;selected states,
metropolitan areas (MAs), urbanized areas (UAs), Native American and Alaska
Native areas.
<P>
Both files include information on household relationship, sex, race, age,
marital status, Hispanic origin, housing units per structure, rooms per unit,
owned or rented, value of home or rent monthly, congregate housing, and vacancy
characteristics. STF 1C is the "National" file; that is, one file released for
the entire nation rather than separate files for states. This does not have the
very small area found in the 1A and 1B files. For working with larger areas
within a state (e.g. counties) or across the nation, 1C is the file to use.
Each STF disc contains a "general profile" feature that gives you the core
population and housing characteristics for the geographic entities on disc.
<UL><LI>File format: dBase III.
<LI>Compatible: PC.
<LI>Documentation: Technical Documentation available both printed and on
disc.
<UL><LI>Summary Tape File 1,TECHNICAL DOCUMENTATION C 3.282:990/doc 
</UL></UL>


<HR><H3>
<A NAME="RTFToC47">CONGRESSIONAL
DISTRICTS OF THE UNITED STATES SUMMARY TAPE FILE 1D and SUMMARY TAPE FILE 3D.
</A></H3>
<H4>
<A NAME="RTFToC48">C
3.282:cd 90-1D-3D
</A></H4>
Bureau of the Census
<P>
The Congressional Districts of the United States, 103rd Congress on CD-ROM
(Summary Tape File 1D) (Summary Tape File 3D) files contain two data sets
Summary Tape File 1D (STF 1D) and Summary Tape File 3D (STF 3D).
<P>
<B>STF 1D</B> contains 100-percent data.  Population items include age, race,
sex,marital status, Hispanic origin, household type, and household
relationship.  Population items are cross tabulated by age, race, Hispanic
origin, or sex.  Housing items include occupancy/vacancy status, tenure, units
in structure, contract rent, meals included in rent, value, and number of rooms
in housing unit.  Housing data are cross tabulated by race or Hispanic origin
of householder or by tenure.
<P>
<B>STF 3D</B> contains sample data weighted to represent the total population.
In addition, the file contains 100-percent counts and weighted and unweighted
sample counts for total persons and total housing units.  Other population and
housing items are listed below.  Please see the List of Tables chapter for a
complete listing.
