<UL><LI>File format: dBase III 
<LI>Compatible: PC.
<LI>Documentation:
<UL><LI>TECHNICAL DOCUMENTATION for the tape file C 3.282/2:990/doc 
<LI>TECHNICAL DOCUMENTATION for the STF 3 on CD-ROM printed from STF 3A disc 
</UL>
</UL>

<HR><H3>
<A NAME="RTFToC55">CENSUS
OF POPULATION AND HOUSING BLOCK STATISTICS (STF3C)
</A></H3>
<H4>
<A NAME="RTFToC56">C
3.282/3:CD 90-1 B4
</A></H4>
Bureau of the Census.
<P>
Contains the same material as the Census of Population and Housing Summary
above. Sample data for the same geographical areas is available on STF 1C.
<UL><LI>File Format: dBase III 
<LI>Compatible: PC.
<LI>Documentation:
<UL><LI>TECHNICAL DOCUMENTATION for the tape file C 3.282/2:990/doc 
<LI>TECHNICAL DOCUMENTATION for the STF 3 on CD-ROM printed from STF 3A disc 
</UL>
</UL>

<HR><H3>
<A NAME="RTFToC57">THE
CONGRESSIONAL DISTRICT OF THE UNITED STATES
</A></H3>
<H4>
<A NAME="RTFToC58">C
3.282/4:104-2
</A></H4>

Bureau of the Census
<P>
The Congressional Districts of the United States, 104th Congress on CD-ROM
contains two data sets Summary Tape File 1D (STF 1D) and Summary Tape File 3D
(STF 3D).  Both files are described in this abstract and other chapters of the
technical documentation.
<P>
<B>STF 1D</B> contains 100-percent data.  Population items include age, race,
sex,marital status, Hispanic origin, household type, and household
relationship.  Population items are cross tabulated by age, race, Hispanic
origin, or sex.  Housing items include occupancy/vacancy status, tenure, units
in structure, contract rent, meals included in rent, value, and number of rooms
in housing unit.  Housing data are cross tabulated by race or Hispanic origin
of householder or by tenure.
<P>
<B>STF 3D</B> contains sample data weighted to represent the total population.
In addition, the file contains 100-percent counts and weighted and unweighted
sample counts for total persons and total housing units.  Other population and
housing items are listed below.  Please see the List of Tables chapter for a
complete listing.
<P>
This only diffrence between this file and C 3.282:CD 90-1D-3D is the new data
for the six states(Georgia, Louisiana, Minnesota, South Carolina and Virginia)
which redisticted for the 104th congress elections.
<P>
The CD also contains the 104th Congressional District Atlas maps in Map Image
Metafile (MIM) format, the 104th Congressional District Atlas maps in PostScript
format, and MIM viewing software for the six states establishing new districting
plans for the 104th Congress.
 <UL>
<LI>File format: dBase III+, Level 2 Postscrip and MIM map files
<LI>Compatible: DOS, GO Software
<LI>Documentation: Technical Documentation on disc.
</UL>


<HR><H3>
<A NAME="RTFToC59">CENSUS/EQUAL
OPPORTUNITY SPECIAL FILE.
</A></H3>
<H4>
<A NAME="RTFToC60">C
3.283:CD 90-EEO-1;2
</A></H4>
Bureau of the Census.
<P>
This file will provide sample census data to support affirmative action
planning for equal employment opportunity. The file contains tabulations
showing detailed occupations and educational attainment data by age. These data
are also cross-tabulated by sex, Hispanic origin, and race. Information is
available for all counties, MSAs, and communities of 50,000 or more
inhabitants.
<UL>
<LI>File format: dBase III 
<LI>Compatible: PC.
<LI>Documentation: Technical Documentation Printed and on Disc 
<UL><LI>TECHNICAL DOCUMENTATION C 3.283:Eq2/doc 
</UL>
</UL>
<HR>





<H3><A NAME="sp312">COUNTY-TO-COUNTY MIGRATION FLOW FILES
</A></H3>
<H4>
C 3.284:CD 90-MIG-01;02
</H4>
Bureau of the Census (Jan 1995)<BR>
Item: 154-F-3     95-010-E<BR>
SubTitle:Special Project 312
<P>
The County to County Migration CD set houses data on migration between 1985 
and 1990.  The data are compiled using information from the 1990 Census of 
Population and Housing.  As part of the 1990 Census, respondents were asked 
where they lived in 1985.  Using the 1985 and 1990 residences reported by the 
respondents we can tabulate the number of persons who moved from any one 
place to another between these years.  The County to County Migration data
is based on such tabulations.
<P>
The CD set consists of two CD-Roms.  One CD-Rom is labelled "In-Migration" while
the other is labelled "Out-Migration".  Both include the software for viewing
data.  However the data stored on each CD is different.  The difference is in the
direction of movement represented by the data. For the "In-Migration" disk
destination is first chosen and the data on people moving into that area can be
viewed, including there origin can be viewed. For the "Out-Migration" disk a
origin is chosen and then data on the people moving out, including there
destination can be viewed. See the <A HREF="Abstracts/SP312/ABSTRACT.ASC.html">abstact</A> for a list of the data available.
 <UL>
<LI>File format:Mix of dBase III, binary and ascii
<LI>Compatible: DOS.
<LI>Documentation: Technical Documentation on Disc 
</UL>
<HR>
 

<H3>
<A NAME="RTFToC61">1990
CENSUS of POPULATION AND HOUSING PUBLIC USE MICRODATA SAMPLES (PUMSA)
</A></H3>
<H4>
<A NAME="RTFToC62">C
3.285:CD 90-PUMSA
3.285:CD 90-PUMSAB
</A></H4>
Bureau of the Census (August 1993)<BR>
Reissued Febuary 1995.
<P>
The Public Use Micro data Samples (PUMS) file contains housing unit and person
records drawn from the full census sample. The 'A' Sample contains records for 5
percent of the population, and the 'B' Sample contains records for 1 percent of
the population. Each record is 231 characters in length and contains information
coded from the 'long form' questionnaire. This is weighted raw data, not summary
data. As such it is useful only for doing analysis. The 1995 reissue corrects the
GROUP QUARTERS RECORDS which had incorrect migration and place of work data.  The
only feilds effected were POWSTATE, POWPUMA, MIGSTATE AND MIGPUMA. The old disks have been kept as lending copies. The fields
which each record type contains are listed in two separate files:

<A HREF="Abstracts/PUMSA/PUMSA.house.html">Housing Fields</A> and 
<A HREF="Abstracts/PUMSA/PUMSA.person.html">Person Fields</A><P>

<UL><LI>File format: ASCII 
<LI>Compatible: PC. 
<LI>Paper copy:See<A HREF="Abstracts/PUMSA/PUMSA.abstract.html"> Abstact</A> for related paper documents
<LI>Documentation: <A HREF="Abstracts/PUMSA/PUMSA.toc.html">Technical Documentation</A> Printed and On disc 
<UL><LI>DATA DICTIONARY AND QUICKTAB FOR PUMS APPLICATIONS 
<LI>QUICKTAB DATA DICTIONARY FOR PUMS 
<LI>TECHNICAL DOCUMENTATION C 3.285:P96/doc 
</UL>
</UL>


