<H3>
<A NAME="SSTF14">OCCUPATION AND INDUSTRY
</A></H3>
<H4>
C 3.286:CD 90 SSTF 14
</H4>
Bureau of the Census (March 1995)
<P>

<H4>SUBJECT MATTER DESCRIPTION
</H4>
On this disc, there are two seperate applications.  One application
  is the Alphabetical Index of Industries and Occupations.  This is a
  comprehensive listing of industries and occupations and contains no
  data.  The other application is Occupation by Industry.  This file
  contains breakdowns for a single occupation or a group of occcupations
  by all 236 industries.  Also, the reverse which is an industry or an
  industry group by 501 occupations.
<P>See the <A HREF="Abstracts/SSTF14/SSTF14.abstract.html">abstract</A>
in Technical Documentation for related paper documents
<UL><LI>File format: dBase
<LI>Compatible: DOS 
<LI>Documentation: Technical Documentation is on the disc.
</UL>


