<TITLE>US Department of Defense CD Index</TITLE>


</HEAD>
<BODY>
<CENTER><H2>
CD ROMS from the US department of Defense</H2>
Carleton College Government Documents Electronic Media List</CENTER>
<HR SIZE="6">



<HR><H3>
<A NAME="RTFToC85">
HMC&amp;M (HAZARDOUS MATERIAL CONTROL &amp; MANAGEMENT) and HMIS (HAZARDOUS MATERIAL INFORMATION SYSTEM)
</A>
</H3>
<H4>
<A NAME="RTFToC86">
D 212.16:993/4/PACK-(1,2);:994/1/v.1-2;:994/2/v.1-2
</A>
</H4>
<P>
Department of Defense
<P>
The HMC&amp;M/HMIS discs provide access to six references:
<P>
<OL>
<LI>The Hazardous Material Information System (HMIS) which is the Department of Defense repository for Material Safety 
Data Sheet (MSDS) information,

<LI>The Ships Hazardous Materials List (SHML) which provides ships the capability to maintain an inventory of chemicals
 and substances used aboard ships,

<LI>The Hazardous Material User's Guide (HMUG) which provides protective information to supplement the technical data 
found in the MSDS's,

<LI>The Shipboard Safety Equipment Shopping Guide which provides national stock numbers for common safety equipment and 
personal protective clothing approved for shipboard use,

<LI>The Shelf Life Extension Criteria Manual which provides storage condition and inspection/test instructions for Navy-
managed hazardous material shelf-life items, and

<LI>The Glossary of Hazardous Terms which provides definitions of terms commonly used in MSDSs as well as technical data
on materials.
<P>
</OL>
<P>
The Non-Navy version of the system (HMIS) will access only the HMIS data. The Navy version (HMC&amp;M) will allow access to all references.
<UL>
<LI>File format: ISO 9660.
<LI>Compatible: PC.
<LI>Documentation: on disc.

</UL>
<!--footer-->
<HR>
<A HREF="THELIST.html">Return to table of contents.
</A><P>
