<HEAD>

<TITLE>US Enviromental Protection Agency CD ROM Index</TITLE>


</HEAD>
<BODY>
<CENTER><H2>
CD ROMS from the US Enviromental Protection Agency
</H2>
Carleton College Government Documents Electronic Media List</CENTER>
<HR SIZE="6">
<HR><H3>
<A NAME="RTFToC111">
A GUIDE TO SELECTED NATIONAL ENVIRONMENTAL STATISTICS IN THE US GOVERNMENT
</A>
</H3>
<H4>
<A NAME="RTFToC112">
EP 1.104:ST2/floppy
</A>
</H4>
Environmental Protection Agency, 1994
<P>
The Guide is a directory to selected US. statistical programs which collect frequently sought-after, national-level, time-series environmental statistics, compiled and distributed on a regular basis. Each entry describes a separate statistical program, giving program purpose, data coverage, and collection methods, geographic coverage, agency contacts, pertinent publications, and database access options.
<P>
Statistical coverage in the Guide includes data related to the state-of-the-environment (e.g. air and water quality, status of biotic resources), pressures on the environment (e.g. energy use, mining, transportation, etc.), human health and welfare issues (e.g. exposure to toxic chemicals), and societal responses to environmental problems (e.g. expenditures on pollution abatement). This information was provided by 53 program offices of 23 agencies in six federal departments as well as the Environmental Protection Agency.
<UL>
<LI>File format: Folio Views
<LI>Compatible: DOS; Software
<LI>Documentation: On Disc
<LI>Disk(s): 1 HD Floppy
</UL>
<P>
<hr>
<H3><A NAME="RTFToC113">MUNICIPAL SOLID WASTE FACT BOOK v1.1</A>
</H3>
<H4>

EP 1.104:W28/Floppy; :W28/994/floppy

</H4>
<P>
Environmental Protection Agency 1993
<P>
The "MSW FACT BOOK" is a paperless electronic reference manual containing more than 200 "screens" of useful facts, figures, tables and information about municipal solid waste.
<P>
<UL>
<LI>File format: TOOLBOOK
<LI>Compatible: Windows
<LI>Documentation: Readme file on disc
<LI>Disk(s): 1 HD Floppy
</UL>


<HR><H3>
<A NAME="RTFToC114">
EPADOC
</A>
</H3>
<H4>
<A NAME="RTFToC115">
EP 1.104/2:1/3;1/4;1/5;1/6
</A>
</H4>
<P>
US. Environmental Protection Agency,
<P>
Information on the disc consists of the EPA Documents on CD-ROM (EPADOC) Infobase. The largest portion is the EPADOC Infobase, which contains information from the Office of Administration and Resource Management and the NDPD. The documents included in the EPADOC Infobase are the latest versions available at the time of release. The information and content of each document have not been altered during the paper-to-magnetic file conversion
<P>
Also contains the Agency's Information Systems Inventory (ISI) which contains information on roughly 650 of EPA's current information systems as well as some models and data bases, and is the definitive source of summary information about EPA systems. The ISI, developed in 1984, enhances the Agency's ability to track major information systems and share information across media and program boundaries. The ISI is a menu-driven, microcomputer-based application.
<UL>
<LI>File format: Text Files
<LI>Compatible: PC
<LI>Documentation: On Line Documentation and Printed from disc
<UL>
<LI>TECHNICAL REFERENCE GUIDE printed from disc
</UL>
</UL>

<HR><H3>
<A NAME="RTFToC116">
NATIONAL BIENNIAL RCRA HAZARDOUS WASTE REPORT
</A>
</H3>
<H4>
<A NAME="RTFToC117">
EP 1.104/3/991
</A>
</H4>
<P>
US. Environmental Protection Agency, 1994
<P>
This floppy contains the EPA's 1991 "List of Large Quantity Generators." This list is part of the "National Biennial 
RCRA Hazardous Waste Report (Based on 1991 Data)," published September, 1994.

<UL>
<LI>File format: PKUNZIP self extracting archive of a WordPerfect 5.1 text file.
<LI>Compatible: 1 HD DOS Floppy
<LI>Documentation: Readme File On Disc
</UL>
<P>


<HR>
<H3>
<A NAME="landviewII">
LANDVIEW II: Mapping of selected EPA-Regulated Sites</A>
</H3>
<H4>
EP 1.104/4:CD 92-LV2
</H4>
<P>
US. Environmental Protection Agency, 1995<BR>
Item:431-R-3
<P>
Land View is a geographic refrence, like an atlas. It displays EPAreguated sites,
demographc and economic inofrmation from the 1990 census. It contains census data
drawn from the STF1A and STF3A census files.  LandViewII also includes a subset
of the facilities, sites and monitoring stations represented in five EPA data
bases:

<UL>
<LI>Aerometric Information Retrieval System
<LI>Biennial Reporting System
<LI>CERCLA Information System
<LI>Permit Compiance System
<LI>Toxic Release Inventory
</UL>
They are described in the informational booklet in the CD case.
 The user can search and create thematic maps using the LandView II system.
<UL>
<LI>
File format: compressed binary files
<LI>
Compatible:DOS; LanView II Maping Software
<LI>
Documentation: Booklet in front of Jewl Case.
</UL>
<P>
<HR>


<H3>
<A NAME="AirChief">
Air CHIEF (Clearinghouse for Inventories and Emission Factors)</A>
</H3>
<H4>
EP 1.109:995
</H4>
<P>
US. Environmental Protection Agency, 1995<BR>
Item:431-R-3
<P>
This CD contains four related databases.
Air CHIEF version 4.0 provides EPA emission estimation guidance
documents and databases in the form of infobases that can be quickly
searched using the Folio BoundVIEWS software interface. The PC-based FIRE system contains
EPA's unique recommended criteria and toxic air emission
estimation factors. The TANKS program is designed to estimate emissions of
organic chemicals from storage tanks.  The calculations are
performed according to EPA's AP-42, Chapter 12.  After the user
provides specific information concerning a storage tank and its
liquid contents, the system produces a report which estimates the
chemical emissions for the tank on an annual or partial year (no less
than one month) basis.  The user can also determine individual
component losses by using one of the speciation options available in
the program.  The CD-ROM also contains EPA guidance documents for estimating air
pollutant emissions. More information can be found in the <A HREF="abstracts/airchief.abstract.html">content file.</A>


<UL>
<LI>File format: Folio View, ASCII, and WordPerfect
<LI>Compatible:  DOS
<LI>Documentation: On CD

</UL>
<P>
<HR>






<H3>
<A NAME="RTFToC118">
TOXIC CHEMICAL RELEASE INVENTORY 1986-89 and 1987-92.
</A>
</H3>
<H4>
<A NAME="RTFToC119">
EP 5.22:T65/CD/987-90/corr; /2:987-92
</A>
</H4>
<P>
US. Environmental Protection Agency, 1991- .
<P>
Data reported about 18,000 facilities and hazardous substance fact sheets distributed by EPA that provide health, safety, and ecological toxicity data for specific chemicals. It is a compilation of information which individual businesses and facilities are required to submit about routine and accidental releases of toxic chemicals into the environment (reporting requirements apply to firms with ten or more employees that use or manufacture such substances). Searches can be done by chemical name, chemical category, state, and individual words such as company or city names.
<UL>
<LI>
File format:dBase
<LI>Compatible: DOS
<LI>Documentation: printed and on disc
<UL>
<LI>USERS GUIDE EP 5.22:t65/doc (green book)
<LI>CD-ROM QUICK USERS GUIDE issue with the CD (inside cover of above)
</UL>
</UL>
<P>
