<HR><H3>
<A NAME="RTFToC146">
NATIONAL GEOTHERMAL DATABASE: Natural Uranium Resource Evaluation Data for the Conterminous 
Western United States.
</A>
</H3>
<H4>
<A NAME="RTFToC147">
I 121:1
</A>
</H4>
US. Geological Survey 1991
<P>
This CD-ROM contains geochemical data collected during the survey of the National Uranium 
Resource Evaluation (NURE) Hydrogeo- chemical and Stream Sediment Reconnaissance (HSSR) 
program. The data are from the National Geochemical Data Base. This publication contains 
only data from the conterminous Western United States. The exact area is shown on the back 
of the insert in the CD container. Samples were collected from 153 quadrangles (1 by 2 
degrees) beginning in 1976 and ending in 1980. Data are included for nearly 400,000 records 
representing four predominant sample types: stream sediments, soils, surface water, and 
ground water. Each sample was analyzed for uranium and a subset from as many as 58 other 
elements plus sulfate. The database may be searched by quad, state, latitude, longitude, 
element's parts per billion, sample date, source and treatment of sample, and type of sample 
(water or sediment).
