<TITLE>US Department of Labor CD ROM Index</TITLE>

</HEAD>
<BODY>
<CENTER><H2>
CD ROMS from the US Department of Labor
</H2>
Carleton College Government Documents Electronic Media List</CENTER>
<HR SIZE="6">

<HR><H3>
<A NAME="RTFToC186">
OFFICE OF EMPLOYMENT AND UNEMPLOYMENT STATISTICS DATA
</A>
</H3>
<H4>
<A NAME="RTFToC187">
L&nbsp;2.134:OF2
</A>
</H4>
<P>
The data are in the form of text images, slightly modified from the form in which the data has been published on paper. SearchExpress was chosen as the best currently available engine for accessing the data. It has the ability to export tabular data to a spreadsheet and to freeze row headers on the CRT screen while the user scrolls horizontally to examine a wide table. Please use the SearchExpress on-line help capability to discover its functionality. This version of SearchExpress is a limited "read-only" version - you cannot add to the database.
<P>
The contents of this CD-ROM are described in a global and a detailed table of contents. A search on "global" or "detailed" in SearchExpress should make these available to you. Entries in the detailed table of contents correlate closely to the actual tabular documents on the CD-ROM.
<P>
Because some of the tables are too large to be viewable under SearchExpress, they have been broken into smaller documents. The largest resultant document may be on the order of 5 megabytes long, while most documents are well under one megabyte long. Because SearchExpress scans the document on CD-ROM before making it viewable, there can be a significant delay between selecting a document and being able to view it. Assuming a typical data transfer rate of 375 kb/minute, the largest delay might be about 13 minutes. Please be patient.
<P>
The OEUS recognizes the access inefficiency described above, and investigated the possibility of presenting the information as one or more databases, and found no reasonable, practical solution with the time and resources available.
<UL>
<LI>File format: SEARCH EXPRESS
<LI>Compatible: PC.
<LI>Documentation: Technical Documentation printed from disc and On line help
<UL><LI>TECHNICAL DOCUMENTATION printed from disc.
</UL>



</UL>
<HR><H3>
<A NAME="RTFToC188">
OCCUPATIONAL SAFETY AND HEALTH ADMINISTRATION
</A>
</H3>
<H4>
<A NAME="RTFToC189">
L 35.26:A93-4/PACK;A94-1;A94-2;A94-3;A94-4;A95-1
</A>
</H4>
<P>
Department of Labor, Occupational Safety and Health Administration ,1994
<P>
This CD contains electronic copy of the text of all OSHA Regulations (Standards), selected documents, and technical information from the OSHA Computerized Information System (OCIS). Regulations include all changes published in the Federal Register through February 28, 1994. Only the
<U>
Federal
</U>
<U>
Register
</U>
can be used as the official source for OSHA regulations. The intent of the CD is to facilitate access to the regulations and other information produced by OSHA.
<P>
For a description of each of the databases, refer to the File Descriptions section of the manual. Included are the following:
<UL>
<LI>
New/Additional Materials
<LI>
OSHA Documents
<LI>
OSHA Act of 1970, with revisions
<LI>
Field Operations Manual
<LI>
OSHA Regulations (Standards)
<LI>
OSHA Technical Manual
<LI>
OSHA Regulations (Preambles)
<LI>
Chemical Sampling Information
<LI>
OSHA Federal Register Index
<LI>
Approved Blood Lead Labs
<LI>
Variances
<LI>
Nationally Recognized Testing Labs
<LI>
OSHA SAVEs
<LI>
Library Catalog
<LI>
OSHA Analytical Methods
</UL>
<UL>
<LI>
File format: WordPerfect and others
<LI>Compatible: PC or Macintosh; Select OSHA from menu to start.
<LI>Documentation: On line documentation and printed from Disc
<UL>
<LI>A94-2 USERS MANUAL printed from disc
<LI>A93-4 USERS MANUAL printed from disc
</UL>
</UL>
